title: walnut bread
directions: Toast walnuts on a baking sheet in a 325° oven for 6 to 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool.

title: cherry jubilee
directions: Mix
pudding
with
1/2 cups milk until smooth.
Mix cream cheese,
milk
and	sugar
together and beat well.	Mix pudding, cheese
mixture and Cool Whip together and pour into graham cracker crust. Top with pie filling.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: garlic cheese roll
directions: Mix well and make into a roll.
Roll in chili powder and chill.
Slice thin and serve with Ritz (any) crackers.
This freezes well.

title: swedish corn pudding
directions: Combine corn and eggs.
Stir in milk, cream and butter.
Add green pepper.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Set in pan of hot water.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 1 hour until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: hershey's disappearing cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) round cake pans.
Cream butter, shortening, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Blend in eggs. Combine cocoa, baking powder, flour, baking soda and salt in bowl. Add alternately with milk to batter and blend well.
Pour into pans; bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pans.
Frost with Lickety Split Frosting.

title: pineapple cake filling
directions: To eggs, add other ingredients and cook over low heat until thick.
Stir continuously.
Fill 3 layers of cake.

title: ro-tel tomatoes
directions: Mix together and cook 45 minutes. Put into hot sterilized jars. Seal and process in hot water bath for 10 minutes.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Place water, soy sauce and bouillon cube in saucepan to dissolve bouillon cube.
Reserve juice from water chestnuts and set aside.
Add remaining ingredients to saucepan.
Mix cornstarch with juice reserved from water chestnuts.
Add to saucepan and cover.
Heat over medium heat, stirring often.
Cook until onions and celery are just tender, but still firm.
Makes approximately 8 cups.

title: mincemeat
directions: Cook beef in water, then add all ingredients except raisins and cook for 1 hour.
Add raisins and cook for 1 more hour.
It is now ready to be canned.

title: cheese soup
directions: Melt cheese with half and half in a double boiler.
Add broccoli and milk mixture.
Season to taste.

title: tortilla appetizers
directions: Mix cream cheese and salsa together.
Spread over tortilla, approximately 3 tablespoons of mixture per tortilla.
Roll up tortilla, tightly.
Continue with as many tortillas will use up spread.
Put rolled up tortillas on a plate and cover with plastic wrap.
Put in refrigerator at least one hour. When ready to serve, remove from refrigerator and slice about 3/4 to 1-inch pieces. Serve.

title: million dollar fudge(makes 6 pounds)
directions: Bring oleo, sugar and milk to a full rolling boil in 4-quart saucepan.
Stir constantly.
Boil for 5 minutes; remove from heat. Gradually stir in the chips until melted.
Add remaining ingredients; beat until well blended.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: lemon butter cookies
directions: Mix together; shape into a roll.
Slice thin; place on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Makes 2 rolls.
They freeze well.

title: a love cake for mother
directions: Be careful how you live.
You may be the only Bible some people read.

title: baked lima beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Put to boil in fresh salted water until tender.
Drain.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper, catsup, sugar and vinegar.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex baking dish.
Cover with strips.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: squash and cheese casserole
directions: Parboil squash in salted water 5 minutes; drain and mix in onion and place in casserole.
Beat eggs, salt and pepper and pour over squash.
Top with cheese, then corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crispy ranch chicken
directions: Place potato chips on a sheet of wax paper. Stir in pepper. Coat chicken breasts in mayonnaise.
Roll in chips until coated. Arrange chicken on lightly greased rack of a broiler pan or cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes or until chicken is golden brown and done.
Yields 6 servings.

title: nonie's chili
directions: Brown ground chuck; drain. Add remaining ingredients and simmer about 30 minutes.

title: cookie mix recipe
directions: Stir together the flour, soda and salt; stir in the sugars. Use wire whip or low speed on mixer.
Cut in the shortening with pastry blender until blended.
Thoroughly stir in the oats.
Makes about 20 cups.
Divide in 4.
Put into plastic bags and add to each bag 1/2 cup raisins and 1/2 cup chocolate pieces.
May be stored at room temperature for several weeks or refrigerated.

title: kick the can ice cream
directions: Clean empty 1 pound coffee can with lid.
Clean empty 2 pound 7 ounce or 3 pound coffee can with lid.

title: tan macaroons
directions: Beat egg whites to form
soft peaks.
Gradually beat in brown sugar, vanilla and salt.
Fold
in
pecans
and coconut. Drop by teaspoon onto a greased
cookie
sheet one inch apart. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Turn off oven heat and let stand in the oven for 20 minutes more.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar gradually, beating after each addition.
Add melted butter; add syrup and mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.
Cover pie with pecan halves and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream, if desired.
Yield 6 servings.

title: swiss and ham party sandwiches
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients to make a spread.
Cut rolls in half and spread the mixture on both sides of the rolls.
Place ham and cheese on bottom half of rolls.
Cover with top half of rolls. Wrap in foil and place on baking sheet.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift three times soda in cup of water.
Mix in dry ingredients, mayonnaise and vanilla.
Add nuts if desired.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: beer brisket
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Season meat with salt and pepper and place in a roasting pan.
Top with onion.
Combine chili sauce with sugar, garlic and 1 cup beer; pour over meat.
Bake covered 4 1/2 to 5 hours.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer, basting occasionally.
Remove beef; let stand 10 to 15 minutes.
Slice 1/4 inch thick across the grain.
Degrease the cooking liquid.
Add water (or beef bouillon) if needed to equal 1 cup.
Blend flour and remaining 1/2 cup beer.
Add to cooking liquid.
Adjust seasoning to taste.
Simmer until thick.
Serve sauce on the side. Serves 8-10.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Bake at 325° for 45 minutes (more or less).

title: lulu paste
directions: Beat
softened	cream	cheese,
salt
and
butter.
In saucepan, put eggs, sugar
and vinegar.
Cook until thick.	It will look curled, don't worry.
Pour over cheese mixture.
Add 1/2 cup chopped
onion and chopped green pepper.
Mix well and refrigerate.
Delicious dip served with crackers.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift
together
all
dry ingredients.
Blend eggs, oil, sugar and
vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients to the liquid. Batter will be stiff.
Stir in apples and pecans.
Pour into a greased and
floured
tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Allow cake to cool, then remove from pan.
Cake freezes well.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix sugar, mayo and vinegar until smooth.
Just before serving, pour sauce over broccoli, cheese and cooked bacon.

title: baked corn
directions: Grease baking dish with butter.
Mix ingredients in order given.
Stir in flour or cornstarch for thickening, sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° in preheated oven.

title: tomato juice cocktail
directions: Cook all together, strain and reheat.
Bottle while hot. Makes 6 quarts.

title: southern hush puppies
directions: Beat egg well.
Add buttermilk and mix well.
Stir in cornmeal, salt, baking powder and soda and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful into deep fat and fry until brown.
As each one is brown on both sides, remove from fat and drain on brown paper, then remove and store in warm oven until ready to serve.
Good with chili con carne and Brunswick stew or just plain good.

title: sweet potato muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin tins, 1 1/2-inch in diameter.
Puree the potatoes in blender.
Cream the butter and sugar.
Beat in the eggs and potatoes.
Sift the flour with the baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add the dry ingredients alternately by hand with the milk, chopped nuts and raisins.
Do not overmix.

title: potato casserole
directions: In meat grinder, shred potatoes and carrot.
Place in casserole.
Mix in sour cream and 2 cups of the shredded cheese. Add parsley.
Mix together.
Top with 1/2 cup of shredded cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until cheese on top is bubbling.

title: lemon pork chops
directions: Heat pressure cooker and add oil.
Brown chops.
Top each with lemon slice. Add onion, salt and pepper.
Combine catsup and water.
Pour over chops.
Close and cook 10 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Crush pretzels and mix with 1/4 cup sugar and 3/4 cup melted margarine.
Pat gently in an 8 x 11-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes. Remove from oven and cool.

title: grandma gin's chicken
directions: Put chicken in baking dish; place cheese over chicken.
Mix soup with wine and spoon over cheese.
Sprinkle dressing mix on top and drizzle melted butter over all.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 45 to 55 minutes until brown and bubbly.

title: rudolf snack
directions: Cut off top two corners of bread.
Spread with peanut butter. Use 2 raisins for eyes, 1 M&M for nose and 2 stick pretzels for each antler.

title: best ever lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine the first 3 items in a saucepan; set aside.
Combine egg yolks, water and lemon juice; stir into sugar mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until the mixture thickens. Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter and lemon rind. Spoon into pastry shell.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients except steak sauce and pecans.
Chill in refrigerator just long enough for easy shaping.
Shape into 2 balls.
With spoon, make a deep indentation in top of each ball and fill with 1 tablespoon of steak sauce.
Cover by pressing cheese smoothly over hole.
Roll ball in pecans.
Makes 2 balls.

title: mrs. helen ara's fluffy white icing
directions: Mix all ingredients together except vanilla.
Place in double boiler and beat with electric mixer at high speed for 7 minutes until right consistency to spread. Add vanilla.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Mix all but onions and bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven and cover with onions; bake an additional 5 to 8 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix corn, oil, meal, garlic, salt and pepper to taste and sugar.
Add eggs and chilies.
Layer with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: congealed strawberry dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; mix with other ingredients except whipped cream.
Congeal 1/2 jello mixture; spread whipped cream over top and add remaining jello.
Chill in oiled pan.

title: raisin cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together in a mixer bowl.
Add eggs and flavorings; beat until fluffy.
Sift 3 cups of flour and baking powder together.
Add to creamed mixture with 1 cup of milk.
Beat well.
Mix raisins and a cup of flour together.
Stir into cake mixture.

title: sugarless banana walnut cake
directions: Beat bananas and butter until creamy.
Add eggs and beat well. Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon; add to banana mixture alternating with water, beating well after each addition.
Stir in nuts.
Spoon into a greased 9-inch square pan. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool. Yields 9 servings.

title: chicken and string bean casserole
directions: Place string beans on bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cut chicken into small pieces and place on top of string beans.
Add olives and water chestnuts on top of chicken.
Mix soup and salad dressing together.
Pour this mixture over everything.
Add cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook Minute rice by directions. Saute the onion and mushrooms. Cook the broccoli (drain).
When rice is done, put in the Cheez Whiz, soup, mushrooms, onion (after sauteed) and broccoli (after cooked).
Mix well.
Put into a large casserole dish and cook for 20 minutes. When it is about done, sprinkle on bread crumbs and dried onions.
Put in 1 to 2 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together on low speed for 30 seconds. Mix on medium speed for 2 minutes. Pour into 2 greased 9-inch pans or 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Mix.
Add oats, chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake in 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: lime-apricot salad
directions: In a saucepan, bring pineapple to a boil. Add remaining ingredients. Congeal and serve.

title: coconut pie(creates its own crust)
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add one egg at a time.
Blend well after each addition.
Add flour, milk and coconut.
Pour into a lightly greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lentil and brown rice soup
directions: In a large heavy saucepan, combine all, except parsley, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover pan and simmer, stirring occasionally for 45 to 55 minutes or until lentil and rice are tender.

title: julie's sauce
directions: Stir together all ingredients but Karo syrup; bring to a boil. Boil for 2 minutes, then pour in the Karo syrup and it's done.

title: shrimp scampi new york style
directions: Butterfly shrimp (cut larger portion about 3/4 through) and boil in water until cooked (do not overcook).
Heat the butter and wine and saute the garlic until golden.
Add salt sparingly.
Put shrimp in mixture, add lemon wedges and cook 5 to 10 minutes on medium heat.
Serve hot.

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in crock-pot; sprinkle with salt and pepper (paprika, if desired).
Mix together the white wine, mushroom soup and mushrooms and add to chicken.
Cook on high 3 to 4 hours or on low 7 to 9 hours.
Thirty minutes before ready to serve, blend sour cream and flour and pour into crock-pot.
Stir and serve over rice.

title: lemon chicken breasts with almonds
directions: Marinate chicken breast halves for two hours in lemon juice, olive oil, Dijon mustard, cloves and rosemary, combined in blender until thick.
Remove chicken and reserve marinade.
In large frying pan, melt 2 tablespoons butter.
Add chicken and cook until lightly browned, about five minutes each side.
Remove chicken and set aside.
Scrape reserved marinade into frying pan.
Add chicken broth and cornstarch.
Bring to a boil and cook, stirring, until thick and smooth, about 2 minutes.
Add almonds and lemon peel. Return chicken to pan; heat through and serve with rice.
Garnish with parsley.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Slice 1 roll of cookies; line the bottom of the pan with dough.
Mix softened cream cheese, sugar and eggs until creamy.
Pour over cookies.
Slice the other roll of cookie dough over the top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: super doopers
directions: Scramble egg and fry in skillet.
While frying, place 5 or 6 pieces of sliced sausage in scrambled egg.
Fry until solid on one side.
Then flip egg and sausages to other side.
Fry until solid. Place slice of cheese on bread.
Flip egg out on top of cheese. Sprinkle with seasoned salt for extra flavor.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles until tender.
In a large bowl, mix together tomato sauce, paste, oregano, basil, salt and garlic.
Spread 1/2 cup of sauce over bottom of a 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Mix cooked beef with remaining sauce.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press
sugar
cookie
roll on sheet (sprayed with Pam). Cook at
for
minutes
and cool.
Combine 1 1/2 cups confectioners sugar with 8 ounces cream cheese; mix and spread on cooled cookie.

title: holly taters
directions: Combine these ingredients.
Cut 6 large potatoes into sections, leaving skin on.
Place in bag, a few at a time with mixture and coat each side.
Place in large baking dish or pan. Melt 1 stick of margarine and pour over top.
Bake at 400° for about 45 minutes or until done.

title: microwave vanilla cream pie
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart microwave dish combine sugar, cornstarch and salt; add milk and mix well.
Cook in microwave 6 minutes or until thick, stirring at the end of each minute.
Add this hot mixture slowly to the beaten egg yolks.
Stir well.
Cook 2 minutes or until thick.
Add vanilla and butter.
Cool to room temperature. Coconut may be added.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and add 2 cups boiling water.
Stir. Chill until set.

title: candy bar pie
directions: Melt candy, marshmallows and milk.
Cool.
Fold in Cool Whip and vanilla.
Pour into a graham cracker crust.

title: blueberry bread
directions: Wash and drain blueberries.
Roll in flour and add to remaining ingredients, except butter.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour in a 9 x 11-inch Pyrex dish.
When done, roll butter over top until melted.
Pick holes in top with a fork and cover with foil until cool.

title: sausage dip
directions: Fry sausage and drain well.
Add cheese.
Mix.
Serve with Ritz crackers on the side.
It's good to keep it warm in a small crock-pot.

title: juicy meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly; pack firmly into a loaf pan.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: coca cola salad
directions: Bring to a boil sugar, water, cherry juice.
Add Jell-O and cherries, let stand few minutes.
Add pineapple, nuts and Coca Cola.
Place in mold and refrigerate overnight.

title: **honey cookies
directions: Bring honey and sugar to a boil.
To the hot syrup add first some of the flour, then the beaten eggs, then more flour mixed with the soda.
Bake at 375°.
I roll mine and press pecan half on each cookie.

title: casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; add salt, oregano, onion, pepper, garlic salt, tomato soup and cooked noodles.
Place 1/2 mixture in a greased casserole dish.
Top with slices of American cheese.
Place remainder of mixture on top.
Cover with more cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: smoked sausage scramble
directions: In a large skillet cook potato and onion in oil until tender. Add spinach and sausage.

title: glorified rice salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water; heat to lukewarm until smooth and clear.
Mix all ingredients except whipped topping in a bowl. Fold in topping.
Pour into lightly oiled mold and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Unmold onto lettuce.
May be put in oblong pan and cut into squares to serve.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Melt the chocolate bits and diet margarine in a small saucepan over very low heat.
Allow to cool.
In mixer bowl, beat the egg at high speed for 2 minutes.
Blend in the yogurt, vanilla, sugar substitute and chocolate mixture until well combined.
Stir the flour, soda and salt together and add to the batter.
Beat for 2 minutes, then drop by teaspoonful, about 2 inches apart, on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Yields 42 cookies.

title: oven chicken stew
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, combine 1 teaspoon salt, poultry seasoning, paprika and pepper; mix well.
Rub onto chicken. In a 5-quart Dutch oven, brown chicken in hot oil over medium heat. Remove chicken; drain oil.
Add tomato paste to Dutch oven; stir in chicken broth.
Bring to a boil.
Return chicken to Dutch oven. Stir in carrots, onions and mushrooms.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is tender.
Stir in peas.
Return to stove top over medium-high heat.
In a small bowl, combine cornstarch and water.
Stir into stew; cook until mixture thickens and boils, stirring frequently.
Season to taste with salt.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Drain fruit, reserving liquid, bring liquid to a boil.
Add jello and dissolve.
Measure liquid.
To this add enough Coke to measure 4 cups total.
Stir well and refrigerate.
When it begins to congeal, add cream cheese (which has been thinned with milk to the consistency of whipping cream); mix well.
Add cherries and pineapple (cut in chunks) and nuts.
Congeal again.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Cut cheese in 2-inch squares.
Cut eggs in three pieces.
Cut pickles in 4 pieces.
Grind each item separately so it will be evenly mixed.
Add approximately 3/4 jar of mayonnaise until it spreads easily.
This recipe makes a very large amount.

title: pork casserole with cashews
directions: Fry the strips of pork until lightly browned.
Add other ingredients, except butter and nuts.
Pour into large casserole; dot with butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Sprinkle the crushed nuts over the top and continue baking for 30 minutes.
Add water if casserole seems dry.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Lightly spray cookie sheet with vegetable oil. In a large mixing bowl, cream margarine until soft. Add sugars gradually and beat until creamy. Beat in egg, peanut butter and soda. Add flour slowly to batter, mixing constantly. Add vanilla and mix well. Roll dough into small balls each about the size of a pecan. Place on prepared cookie sheet. Flatten balls lightly with back of tines of a floured fork. Bake 12 to 15 minutes. Makes 30 cookies.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Serve with crackers of bread.

title: pork chops italiano
directions: About 1 3/4 hours before serving, trim pork chops of all excess fat; sprinkle with seasoned salt and pepper.
In large skillet, saute chops until well browned, draining fat as it collects; place chops in a large roasting pan or 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Arrange mushrooms around chops.
Start heating oven to 375°.

In a clean large skillet in salad oil, saute onion, garlic and green peppers until golden; add tomato sauce, 1 teaspoon seasoned salt, 1/8 teaspoon pepper, bay leaf, lemon juice and sage; simmer, covered, until vegetables are almost fork-tender. Pour sauce over chops and bake covered until pork chops are done, about 1 hour.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine eggs and sugar; add oil and pumpkin.
Add water with dry ingredients.
Stir in vanilla, nuts and raisins.
Pour mix into 4 (1 pound) coffee cans, filling half full.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or make 2 loaf pans.

title: chocolate dream dessert
directions: Mix flour, oleo and pecans.
Spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press down evenly and bake 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar, beaten egg yolks and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to first mixture alternately with water.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Melt butter and brown sugar in oven in 9-inch cake pan.When thick, add cut pineapple.
Pour batter over fruit and bake about 35 minutes at 350°.
Remove to dish, turning upside down so fruit will be on top. Serve hot with hard sauce.

title: spicy ginger cookies(yield:  about 100 cookies)
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 375°.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Lightly salt chicken breasts.
Melt butter.
Mix flour, salt and paprika in bag.
Add chicken and shake to coat evenly.
Brown lightly in butter.
Grease an 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Place ham slices in dish; cover with celery.
Place chicken, skin side up, on ham slices.
Add flour left in bag to melted butter; blend well.
Add orange juice.
Remove from heat and add sour cream. Pour over chicken.
Cover baking dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: meat loaf #3
directions: Lightly mix the first 6 ingredients. Form loaf and bake at 350°. Combine while it's starting to bake the last 7 ingredients. Pour sauce over meat loaf. Bake 1 1/2 hours, basting often.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Blend shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat all until light and fluffy.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet and bake.

title: bean salad
directions: Boil vinegar, sugar, oil, water and pepper.
Combine peas, corn, beans, pimento, celery and onion.
Pour liquid mixture over bean mixture.
Cover and put in refrigerator.
Will keep several days.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown onion and bacon together.
Pour rest of ingredients in a roaster.
Add onion and bacon.
Bake 2 hours at 350°.
Serves 30 people.

title: tortilla casserole
directions: Brown the meat in a frying pan until lightly browned. Make spaghetti sauce according to package directions using 1 can tomato sauce. Add this to the meat along with the chili seasoning mix and remaining can of tomato sauce. Cut tortillas into quarters and, in a greased casserole, layer tortillas, meat mixture, cheese and chilis, twice. Bake at 350°f. 180° c. gas mark 4 for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften cream cheese with lemon juice.
Add shrimp and onions. Add enough mayonnaise to dipping consistency.
Season with rest of ingredients.

title: cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in baking dish or pan.
Mix sugar, flour, baking powder and milk together.
Pour over oleo.
Put fresh fruit on top.
Top with 1 cup sugar.
Bake at 325° until batter is done.

title: alaska baked halibut
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, cover bottom with 1/4 can soup.
Lay chunks of halibut in pan.
In small frypan, saute onions in butter.
Add salt, pepper, sour cream and remaining soup.
Pour over halibut.
Cover with grated cheese.
Cover with foil; bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: meat ball stew
directions: Add water.
Cover and cook for 1 hour.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add egg and beat well.
Add raisins and nuts.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add alternately with applesauce, starting and ending with flour mixture.
Bake in 13 x 9 1/2 x 2-inch pan in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: fantastic fudge cookies
directions: Heat oven to
Melt chips and butter in microwave or in double boiler.
When completely melted, remove from heat and add Eagle Brand milk and mix well.
Stir in flour.
Mix in nuts and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake for 8 to	10
minutes.
Cookie
will firm up as it cools; inside will stay soft and chewy.

title: grandma's biscuits
directions: Mix flour and Crisco.
Gradually add milk until mixture is wet.
Roll
on floured surface.
Bake at 500° for 8 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mexican dip
directions: On a round serving platter, layer the following, bean dip, avocados mixed with lemon juice, sour cream mixed with taco seasoning, onions, tomatoes, olives, cheese and jalapenos.
Serve with corn chips.

title: aunt mary's apple cake
directions: In bowl, mix sugar, eggs, oil and apples by hand.
Stir in all dry ingredients until everything is mixed (will be lumpy and almost dry).
Pour/scrape into a 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bean `n' beef crescent pie
directions: In a skillet, brown beef and drain. Add taco seasoning and salsa. Simmer, uncovered, until thickened.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well.
Put in buttered casserole dish. Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp remoulade
directions: Combine all ingredients
except shrimp in blender;
mix for a few seconds until
smooth.
Marinate
the
shrimp in the sauce for several hours before
serving; chill well in refrigerator.
Serve as an appetizer, on lettuce leaves.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mexican roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread on tortillas.
Add garlic and seasoned salt to taste.
Roll tortillas up and refrigerate 2 hours or more.
Slice thin.
Can serve with salsa, too.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Blend together cream cheese and sugar. Blend Cool Whip into cheese mix. Crumble 1/2 cake in bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish. Pour 1/2 cheese mix on top. Pour 1/2 cherries on top of that and repeat with rest of cake, mix and cherries. Chill for several hours before serving.

title: baptist pound cake
directions: Beat together Crisco, butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well after each.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together and add with milk to first mixture; add flavorings. Grease and flour tube pan.
Pour mixture into pan.
Place in cold oven and turn heat to 350° and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until cake tests done.
Let stand for 3 to 5 minutes before removing from pan.

title: strawberry salad
directions: In large bowl combine jello and boiling water, stirring until jello is dissolved.
Stir in strawberries and pineapple.
Fold in bananas. Pour half of mixture into a large serving dish, chill until partially set.
Chill remaining mixture in bowl.
Do not chill until it is set.
Spread sour cream over partially set mixture in serving dish.
Pour remaining mixture over sour cream. Chill until set and firm.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients, adding water, one can at a time. Cook slowly for 1 1/2 hours on low heat.

title: poor man's caviar(eggplant)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake eggplant about 1 hour until soft. Cook onions in 4 tablespoons oil until soft.
Stir in green pepper and garlic and cook 5 minutes.
Put in bowl with eggplant pulp, which has been chopped finely, along with tomatoes, sugar, salt and pepper.
Heat remaining oil in skillet and cook mixture about 1 hour on low.
Add lemon juice. Serve with rye, pumpernickel bread or sesame seed crackers.
Serves about 20 (more or less).

title: crispy baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Rinse and dry chicken.
Season.
Dip each piece in milk.
Shake to remove excess and roll in the crumbs. Let stand briefly so coating will adhere.
Line pan with foil and spray with Pam for easy clean-up.
Place chicken on foil and bake 45 minutes or more.
Crumbs will form a crisp "skin."
(From American Heart Association.)

title: chili frittata
directions: Beat eggs with mixer.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and cottage cheese.
Stir in Jack or Swiss cheese, melted butter and chilies.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden on top and knife comes out clean.
Good with salsa and sour cream.
Serves 20.

title: mom's green rice
directions: Pour rice on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add thawed broccoli on top.
Add water chestnuts and celery.
Mix the cheese into this, then the soup and butter.
Add 2 cans of water.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: garlic cheese bread
directions: Soften butter in bowl.
Crush or chop garlic cloves.
Add garlic and oregano to butter and mix.
Slice bread sideways. Spread mixture on both sides.
Close bread and place in foil in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Open foil, separate bread and place cheese on bread.
Cook until cheese melts.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugars and milk; heat on medium for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour into greased pan. Cool and cut.

title: cheddar-potato-broccoli soup
directions: In 2- to 3-quart saucepan, melt butter.
Add onion; saute 5 minutes.
Add potatoes, water and bouillon.
Cover; bring to boil. Reduce heat to medium and cook just until potatoes are tender, about 15 minutes.
Remove 1 cup of the potato cubes with slotted spoon; set aside.
Pour contents of saucepan into container of electric blender.
Holding lid on securely, blend until smooth; return to saucepan.
Mix in reserved potatoes and the broccoli. Over medium-low heat, gradually add cheese, stirring until heated through and cheese is completely melted.
Season with salt and pepper.
Makes 4 servings (about 5 cups).

title: orange cottage cheese salad
directions: Sprinkle dry Jell-O over cottage cheese and mix.
Add pineapple and oranges; mix.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch container.
"Refrigerate and enjoy!"

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken breasts in salted water until done.
Skin, debone and cut into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients together except potato chips and cheese.
Put in oblong baking dish and pour 1/2 cup chicken broth over mixture.
Top with layer of crushed chips, then grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes uncovered.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken with onion, salt and pepper until tender.
Let chicken cool.
Pick meat from bones and cut into small pieces.

title: whipped cream frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl. Beat at medium speed until good spreading consistency is obtained, about 4 minutes.

title: cherry pecan loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Spray 9 x 5 inch bread pan with vegetable oil and flour sides.
In medium bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
In large bowl, cream margarine and sugar together
Add egg substitute and continue to mix for an additional minute.
Add Equal, applesauce, vanilla and almond extract.
Alternately add flour mixture and Glucerna Shake until ingredients are just moistened. Stir in cherries and nuts.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes or until inserted toothpick comes out clean. Cool completely before slicing.

title: fondue
directions: Grate cheese.
Melt butter in saucepan and add flour, stirring with a wire whisk.
Add milk, stirring rapidly with whisk.
When blended and smooth, add garlic, pepper, nutmeg and wine.
Add Kirsch, if desired.
Serve hot with bread cubes for dipping.
If the sauce is to be used over vegetables, omit the Kirsch.

title: date pudding
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until light.
Add sifted dry ingredients. Stir in dates and nuts.
Turn into greased 8-inch square pan and bake in pan of hot water at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm; top with whipped cream.
Serves 6.

title: creamy lemon cheese pie(no cooking required)
directions: * Warm to room temperature (70°).

title: potato bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Lightly grease baking sheet; set aside. In large bowl combine flour, baking powder, salt and pepper.
With pastry blender cut butter until coarse crumbs.
Stir in mashed potatoes and scallions to make a soft dough.
On lightly floured surface knead dough 3 to 4 minutes.
With rolling pin, on lightly floured surface, roll dough 1/4-inch thick.
With 3 1/2-inch round cookie cutter, cut into rounds.
With spatula, transfer to prepared baking sheet.
Bake 25 minutes until golden brown.
Cool on wire rack 5 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: chili i
directions: Brown meat.
Mix all ingredients.
Cook over low heat for 1 hour.

title: oven porcupines
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix meat, rice, 1/2 cup water, onion, salt, celery salt, garlic powder and pepper.
Shape mixture by rounded teaspoonfuls into balls.
Place meatballs in ungreased baking dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inch.
Stir together remaining ingredients. Pour over meatballs.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake 45 minutes. Uncover; bake 15 minutes longer.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: meltaway bars
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add egg yolk and vanilla. Mix in flour; this will be stiff.
Add 1/2 cup nuts.
Press into well oiled jelly roll pan.
Beat egg white until frothy, then smooth over dough.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup nuts over all.
Pat dough slightly.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until lightly brown. Cool slightly, then cut into bars and finish cooling on rack.

title: beef tortilla casserole
directions: Brown beef, onions and chiles; drain.
Heat oven to 350°. Arrange tortilla chips in the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with beef, then taco sauce, then beans.
Top with cheese.
Bake until hot and bubbly, 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with sour cream.

title: russian salad
directions: Put package of jello into hot water, add marshmallows and cream cheese. Let cool, then add all other ingredients. Stir into jello mixture and pour into mold to gel. Refrigerate until set.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: steamed apple-date pudding
directions: Peel and chop apple.
Set aside.
In blender or food processor, mix dates and apple cider until smooth.
Set aside. Grease and set aside a 2 1/2-quart baking pan, heatproof bowl or mold.
Set aside.
Cream butter and sugar.
Beat until light.
Add and beat in the eggs, then dry ingredients.
Add date mixture. Beat one minute.
Fold in chopped apple and nuts.
Spoon into prepared pan, bowl or mold.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Steam 2 1/2 to 3 hours, following standard procedure for steamed pudding. Serve warm with sauce.

title: corn dogs
directions: Combine flour, corn meal, sugar and baking powder in medium bowl. Combine milk and egg in small bowl. Add to flour mixture; mix just until blended (batter will be thick). Spread batter into shallow plate or dish. Insert skewers into hot dogs. Add oil to 2-inch depth in electric skillet or large skillet; heat to 350 degrees. Dip hot dogs into batter, coating all sides. Add 3 to 4 hot dogs to hot oil, turning after 5 to 10 seconds to set batter. Fry, turning occasionally, until golden brown; drain. Repeat with remaining hot dogs. Serve with mustard and ketchup.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Wash and chop pickles into large pieces.
In same jar the pickles came in, put layer of pickles and part of the sugar. Repeat layers until all is used.
Tie spices in small piece of cheesecloth and put into the middle of the jar.
Heat vinegar and pour over pickles.
Shake well every 30 minutes until sugar is dissolved.
Chill and eat.

title: peanut butter dessert
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients and press 2/3 on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat the powdered sugar, peanut butter and cream cheese until very smooth. Add the whipped Dream Whip.
Spoon half of the mixture over the graham cracker crumbs.

Place the apple slices carefully over the mixture. Sprinkle with the cinnamon. Top with the other half of the mixture. Sprinkle with the remaining graham cracker crumb mixture. Cover pan with foil and chill 24 hours before serving.

title: icebox cake
directions: Mix Jell-O pudding according to directions on box.
Layer graham crackers and pudding in standard size cake pan.

title: melon madness
directions: Place melon cubes in a single layer on a jelly roll pan. Freeze melon cubes at least 1 1/2 hours. Place frozen melon and remaining ingredients in a blender and process until mixture is smooth. Serve immediately.

title: mexican skillet
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet.
Briefly cook onion, green pepper and garlic in oil.
Push to one side of skillet.
Add ground beef and stir until meat is no longer pink.
Stir in chili powder.
Mix all ingredients together well.
Add tomato juice, rice, the liquid from the kidney beans and corn and oregano.
Stir; bring to boil. Cover and reduce heat to low.
Simmer for 25 minutes.
Stir in corn and beans.
Cover and heat for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Cover and heat until cheese is melted.

title: quick apple dessert
directions: Crumble oleo, flour and sugar together.
Place apples in square baking pan and sprinkle Jell-O over apples.
Put flour mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry sour cream cake
directions: Set oven to 350°. Combine first 6 ingredients and mix well. Turn into prepared pan. Sprinkle evenly with berries. Combine the rest and spread evenly. Bake 1 hour or until custard edges is lightly brown.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar gradually.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating each time.
Add vanilla.
Add soda to milk.
Add flour and milk alternately to other ingredients.
Bake in a tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Frost, if desired.
May be frozen.

title: seafood newberg
directions: Cook in top of a double boiler.
Serve on toast, pastry shells or cooked rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: caramel pie
directions: Completely submerge unopened condensed milk in water and boil for 3 hours. Make sure to keep cans covered in water the entire time. Remove from heat and cool for 20 minutes. Open cans. Smooth out on graham cracker crust that is prepared by the directions on the box. Let cool in refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours. When serving, top with Cool Whip and nuts. Yields 1 pie.

title: shrimp batter
directions: Mix and dip your shrimp in it to fry.

title: pasta con broccoli ii
directions: Cook noodles until half done - 4 minutes - drain, leave in pan.
Add cream, butter, garlic, tomato sauce, broccoli.
Bring to a boil, medium heat for 4 to 5 minutes.
Stir in mushrooms. Remove from heat.
Add parmesan cheese.

title: cheddar potato slices
directions: When you are mashing or whipping the potatoes, add cream cheese.
For 5 pounds of potatoes, I put a small package of the Philadelphia cream cheese.
Leftovers stay just fine 2 to 3 days covered in the refrigerator.

title: cheddar cheese chili cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In a medium bowl, whisk together eggs, yogurt and butter.
Add cornmeal, salt, baking powder and soda; mix until just blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Pour into greased 10-inch skillet.
Bake for 40 minutes.

title: crab and rice alfredo
directions: Prepare boil-in-bag rice according to directions; set aside. Combine alfredo sauce, peas, parsley, chives and pimentos in a medium skillet.
Place over medium heat, stirring often until heated through.
Add crab delight and heat an additional 2 minutes.
Serve over hot rice.
Serve with fresh Parmesan cheese.

title: pork loin with tangy sauce
directions: Coat meat with 3 tablespoons each garlic salt and chili powder.
Cook in uncovered roasting pan at 350° for 2 hours and 20 minutes before roasting is done.
Coat it in a sauce made of remaining ingredients which have been brought to a boil.
Serve rest of sauce on the side.

title: pizza just for kids
directions: Roll and flatten biscuits.
Spread on pizza sauce.
Add pepperoni and any other toppings.
Place on slightly greased pan and bake at 375° until pizza crust is golden brown.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Put in pie shell.
Pour pie filling over top; refrigerate and call Boots!

title: lasagna 1
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions, omitting salt and drain.
Brown sausage and hamburger; drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce; set aside.
Combine egg, Ricotta cheese, parsley, oregano, pepper and Parmesan cheese.
Spread 1/2 cup meat sauce in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Layer 1/2 of noodles, 1/2 of Ricotta cheese mixture, 1/2 Mozzarella cheese and 1/3 of remaining meat sauce.
Repeat layers using equal amounts.
Arrange mushrooms and pepperoni on top.
Spoon remaining sauce on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and bake another 5 minutes.

title: mary beckers frozen salad
directions: Mix well and freeze.

title: savory mushroom chops with stuffing
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place pork chops in baking dish and salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with grated cheese.
In small bowl mix cream of mushroom soup, mushrooms and 1/2 cup water.
Spoon over pork chops.
Cover dish and bake for one hour.
In last 20 minutes of baking, prepare Stove Top as directed.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat sugar, buttermilk, Bisquick, butter, vanilla and eggs until smooth. Pour into buttered pie pan. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: violet's porcupine balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, except tomato sauce, and form into balls, 1 or 2 inches across.
Place in a casserole dish and pour tomato soup or sauce over them.
Cook in hot oven for about 1 hour at 350°.
Can use stewed or canned tomatoes.

title: salted peanut chews
directions: Mix until crumbly; pat into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes, or until light brown.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini until tender.
Drain and mix all ingredients. Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: deno's chili (hot)
directions: Let sit on stove and cook slow.
(You may want to cut back on hot sauce and cayenne pepper.)

title: honey glazed carrots
directions: Combine butter, brown sugar and salt in a skillet. Add carrots and simmer until carrots are browned evenly.

title: dip pie
directions: Saute pecans in butter and salt on stove.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Add to sauteed mixture.
Spread in 8-inch or 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: taco-stuffed shells
directions: Cook beef in a large skillet, drain.
Add seasoning packet and water.
Cook on low until thick.
Add refried beans and half the cheese.
Spread 1/2
the salsa in the bottom of a baking dish. Fill shells with meat mixture.
Pour remaining salsa over shells. Cover with tin foil and bake at 350 for 40 minutes.
Top with sour cream and cheese.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, flour, sugar and salt.
Gradually add milk and heat.
Do not boil.
Blend into beaten egg yolks and return to pan.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Stir in vanilla and coconut.
Cool before pouring into baked pie crust.
Use egg whites for meringue.

title: cream of mushroom soup
directions: In skillet, saute sliced mushrooms in butter; place in crock-pot.
Add chicken broth, onion, salt and pepper; stir well. Cover and cook on low setting for 6 to 10 hours, or on High setting for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
About 30 minutes before serving, turn to high setting.
Mix flour and sour cream; add to crock-pot with half and half cream.
Cook until slightly thickened.
Makes 6 servings (about 2 quarts).

title: burnt sugar cake(depression days recipe)
directions: Make burnt sugar liquid by melting 1 c. sugar in an aluminum pan (heavy pan) over high heat. When dark brown, add 1 c. boiling water and boil hard for 5 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil potatoes until tender; peel and mash while still warm. Add cream, butter, nutmeg and sugar.
Whip well! Pour into casserole and top with large marshmallows.
Brown in oven at 400°. Marshmallows should not get too brown (golden color and the dish is done).

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Blend butter and sugar until creamy.
Add 1 egg yolk at a time. Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Add to first mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Add flavoring.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into batter.
Bake in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Cut into small pieces.
Add next four ingredients and stir.
In each flour tortilla add 2 tablespoons of mixture.
Roll with fold down and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread remaining mixture over tortillas.
Sprinkle with 1 cup of Monterey Jack cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until partially brown and bubbling.

title: spaghetti carbonara
directions: In a skillet, saute bacon with butter over low heat, rendering fat and cooking bacon until crisp.

title: spiced fruit compote
directions: Place pears and dried fruit in casserole dish.
Place juice of pears in separate bowl and add cinnamon, cloves, sugar and lemon juice.
Pour over pears and fruit.
Add cinnamon sticks.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
(May put dried fruit in microwave to plump with 1 cup water for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Drain.
Shortens baking time to 30 minutes.)

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and shortening in a large mixing bowl; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs and milk; beat well.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together in a small mixing bowl. Gradually add to creamed mixture, stirring well after each addition.
Shape dough into a ball.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill at least 30 minutes.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place about 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with palm of hand.
Sprinkle with sugar; bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes. Cool on wire rack.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: zucchini bread(serves 4)
directions: Mix all dry ingredients; fold in apples and zucchini.
Add eggs and extract; mix well.
Pour into a sprayed 8 x 8-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
One serving = 1 bread, 1 protein (egg), 1 milk, 1/2 fruit and 1 vegetable serving.

title: dijon pork steaks
directions: Marinate pork chops for several hours.
Broil, turning once.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Cube potatoes in bite size pieces.
In large mixing bowl, pour oil over cubed potatoes, salt and pepper.
Coat potatoes well. Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake, covered, in oven for 45 minutes at 300°.
Uncover and bake for 15 minutes. (During last 15 minutes, you can sprinkle with crushed dry parsley or dry powdered cheese.)

title: hot seafood salad
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients, except cornflakes and butter.
Melt butter and moisten crushed flakes.
Put all ingredients in a casserole dish.
Top with crushed cornflakes and bake for 45 minutes.

title: sausage souffle
directions: Saute and drain sausage and spread in 2-quart baking dish. Layer bread cubes, then cheese.
Beat eggs with salt and mustard. Pour egg mixture over all.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: nanny's pecan pie
directions: Cream butter; add flour, sugar, syrup and pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° until set and toothpick comes out clean.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Mix 1 cup sugar, flour, baking powder and salt together.
Sprinkle mixture over melted margarine.
Drain peaches and add 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg to the juice.
Mix.
Add this mixture to peaches and mix.
Pour peaches and juice mixture over flour mixture in pan. Bake at 350° for about 35 to 45 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: #1 Layer hamburger meat, uncooked.

title: barbecue
directions: Cook beef and pork together in water until tender.
Pull apart.
Add enough water during cooking to have 2 cups stock. Shred meat.

title: matzo farfel muffins
directions: Combine farfel, sugar and salt in a bowl.
Melt shortening in the boiling water and pour over farfel mixture.
Allow to cool. Stir fork beaten egg yolks into cooled farfel mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff, not dry, peaks are formed.
Fold into batter. Spoon batter into 8 well-greased muffin pan wells, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° about 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: calldo verde(potato and kale soup with sausage)
directions: Wash the greens under cold running water.
With a sharp knife trim away any bruised or blemished spots and strip the leaves from their stems.
Bunch the leaves together and shred them into the finest possible strips; set aside.

title: red, white and blue salad
directions: First Layer: Dissolve blackberry Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water. Stir in pie filling (blueberry). Pour into 8 x 12-inch pan. Chill.

title: vegetable dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill 2 hours.

title: tuna salad oliver
directions: Prepare macaroni as per package.
Chill.
Mix macaroni and other ingredients.
Add enough mayonnaise to hold mixture together, but not to make mixture soupy.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Chill. Serve on bed of lettuce.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: Take first four ingredients.
Mix together.
Place in a large pie pan or round pizza pan.
Layer:
Ricotta cheese on crust, browned hamburger, onions peppers, etc., top with spaghetti sauce. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Then add Mozzarella cheese on top. Put back in oven for 5 minutes.
Let set 15 minutes, then cut and serve.

title: family steak
directions: Place steak in a 13 x 9-inch pan and pour mixture over meat and refrigerate for 24 to 48 hours.
Grill.
Sauce may be kept to reuse about 2 weeks.

title: grandmother's cherry delight
directions: Mix
together the flour, melted oleo, pecans and sugar. Pack in	greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 300° or until lightly browned.
Let cool.

title: coconut macaroon cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients and stir in 1 can of coconut. Bake in prepared pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: turkey pot pie
directions: Mix and bake in a 9-inch pie shell, covered with another pie shell.
Make slits in the center.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: tennessee baked ham
directions: Soak ham overnight in cold water.
Drain; wipe dry.
Mix corn meal with brown sugar and pepper.
Add enough water to make a clay like paste.

title: pear mincemeat
directions: Peel and core pears.
Remove seeds but not peelings from oranges, lemon and apple.
Grind and mix with other ingredients. Boil for 1 1/2 hours.
Pack into hot, clean jars and seal.

title: turtle cake
directions: Bake cake per package instructions.
When it is taken out of oven, poke holes in top and pour condensed milk over it.
Top this with Hershey's topping, then top with 3 crushed Heath candy bars and cover with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until serving.
You can also use German chocolate cake mix, caramel ice cream topping and crushed Butterfingers.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion in skillet; drain off fat. Sprinkle meat with 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper. Place 1/2 of chilis in 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Top with meat mixture.
Arrange remaining chilis over meat.

title: leg of lamb with plum sauce
directions: Place lamb, fat side up, on rack in shallow roasting pan. Season with salt and pepper.
Roast in slow oven (325°) for 2 1/2 to 3 hours (meat thermometer 175° to 180°).

title: hot dill pickles
directions: Scrub the veggies well with brush and drain.
Pack in quart jars.
To each jar, add finely cut dill to taste, 1 hot pepper (or two) and 1 clove garlic.
Blend the vinegar, water and salt in a large pot and bring to a boil.
Pour in hot brine to fill the jar. Insert knife blade to expell air bubbles.
Remove knife and seal jar.
This amount of brine will pickle about 3 gallons of veggies. I like to use whatever is left in the garden at final harvest to make a "garden mix" of pickled veggies.

title: pineapple ice box pudding
directions: Melt the butter.
Remove from stove and add pineapple, sugar, crushed wafers and chopped nuts.
Crush enough extra wafers to put a thin layer in bottom of pyrex dish.
Pour mixture in dish and add a thin layer of crushed wafers on top.
Place in refrigerator to cool.
Serve in square blocks with Cool Whip if desired.
This is enough for about 12 servings.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Beat egg yolks and sugar until blended in small bowl.
Stir in flour and salt, blending well.
Add rhubarb.
Pour filling into unbaked pie shell.
Dot with butter as desired (I like 1/2 stick or more).
Bake at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes or until firm.
Let cool.

title: milky way cake
directions: Combine candy and 1 stick margarine in a saucepan. Cook over low heat. Stir constantly until melted; set aside. Cream 2 cups sugar and 1 stick butter in a bowl, then beat in eggs. Sift the flour with soda and add to the creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in candy mixture. Add pecans and mix well. Pour into greased and floured oblong pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour 10 minutes.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Layer dish with vanilla wafers.
Mix Cool Whip, condensed milk, 1/2 package pecans and pineapple (drained).
Pour mixture over vanilla wafers.
Refrigerate until ready to serve, then top with cherry pie filling.

title: pumpkin-nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pans.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Beat in bowl the butter, sugar, flour and salt until fine crumbs.
Remove 1 cup crumbs; set aside.
Mix together and stir warm water, soda and molasses.
Add to flour mixture and beat until smooth.
Pour into a 10 x 14-inch greased and floured pan. Sprinkle the cup of crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: bohemian coffee cake
directions: Sift flour with salt,
and
spices;
set
aside.
Cream sugars,
eggs and oil.
Beat
soda	with
buttermilk.
Add	to creamed mixture, gradually	add dry ingredients; then vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Mix
well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: aunt cora's jumbo raisin cookies
directions: Place raisins in water; bring to a boil for 3 minutes.
Cool; don't drain.
Mix flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spices. Cream shortening; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Beat in Egg Beaters.
Stir in raisins with liquid and vanilla.
Gradually add flour mixture, beating well.
Stir in nuts.

title: alice's potato boast
directions: Place sliced potato on aluminum foil, then place on patty. Next, add onion slice.
Last, place slice of bacon.
Close aluminum foil, crimping edges together, forming a seal.
Bake in oven for 30 to 45 minutes at 350° or you may place these on grill to bake. Great with green salad and baked beans.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat pineapple and add Jell-O (dissolved).
Fold in buttermilk and then Cool Whip.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: beef and beans
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add onions, green pepper and celery.
Mix together the brown sugar, catsup, ginger, cloves and baked beans. Combine everything in a large casserole; bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook big ole hen thets bin plucked clean 'n cut up in small pieces.
Take the pieces 'n mix wid remaining ingredients.
Cook all in a double boiler fur 1/2 hr 'n when sauce iz done add 1 large can uv mushrooms.
Take 9 ounces of spaghetti (1 1/2 boxes) without washin' 'n cook it in chicken broth.
Now put the chicken 'n spaghetti in a casserole in layers 'n kiver wid the sauce...bake slowly fur an hour.

title: smothered gar fish
directions: Combine meal and flour and coat steaks.
Fry in hot oil until done.
Remove steaks and excess oil from skillet, leaving about 2 tablespoons and fish renderings.
Add garlic and onions.
Cook until soft.
Add 2 cups of water; bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Add steaks.
Bring to boil again.
Lower heat, cover and simmer.
Serve with rice.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream the sugar and butter together.
Add the eggs and crushed bananas.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to the creamed mixture.
Add nuts.
Bake in a loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar with blender.
Put crushed cookies at bottom of 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Spoon ice cream on top.
Spoon Cool Whip mixture over it.
Put another layer of cookies, ice cream and Cool Whip mixture.
Freeze.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Break
spaghetti in half.
Cook in boiling salted water until done.
Drain.
While still warm, combine spaghetti with eggs
and Parmesan
cheese.
Pour into a well-greased 10-inch pie plate
and pat
mixture up and around sides with a spoon. Melt
butter
and add onion;	saute until limp.
Stir in sour cream
and
spoon over spaghetti.	Remove sausage from casing, crumble
and
cook	in skillet until done.
Drain; add tomato paste
and water.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Spoon sausage on top of sour
cream
mixture.	Bake at	350° for 25 minutes.
Arrange cheese on top.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: baked fries
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cut potatoes lengthwise about 3/4-inch thick, then cut each slice into 3/4-inch long sticks.
Place potato sticks in large bowl.
Drizzle with oil and toss to coat; sprinkle with herb seasoning and salt and toss again.
Arrange potato sticks in a single layer on nonstick baking sheet or baking sheet coated with nonstick spray.
Bake until potatoes are golden brown, 20 to 25 minutes, turning once after 15 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: baked lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna according to package directions.
Meanwhile cook ground beef in large heavy sauce pan until browned, drain grease. Add onion, garlic, parsley, mushrooms, water, tomato paste, pepper and salt.
Bring to boil, turn heat low and let simmer gently for about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except for Parmesan cheese. Pour into a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove cover and bake for 30 minutes longer.
Serves 12 as a side dish or 8 as a main dish.

title: vegetable toss-up
directions: Serve in season.
In container, layer the greens, cauliflowerets, zucchini, tomatoes and onion.
To make the dressing, in small mixing bowl, stir together the mayonnaise, French dressing, lemon juice, horseradish, Worcestershire and hot pepper sauce.
Fold in the whipped topping.
Spoon dressing over the vegetables.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.
Refrigerate 4 to 6 hours.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: something different cupcakes
directions: Melt chocolate and oleo in heavy pan.
Add pecans.
Stir well until coated.
Take off heat.
Combine sugar, flour, eggs and vanilla.
Mix only until blended.
Do not beat.
Add chocolate and nuts to mixture.
Do not beat.
Put in 18 baking cups in muffin tins.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 325°.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except corn flakes and 1/4 cup of melted margarine.
Stir well and pour into buttered casserole dish.
Mix together corn flake crumbs and remaining 1/4 cup of margarine.
Sprinkle over potato mixture for topping.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: taco joe dip
directions: In a slow cooker, combine the first 8 ingredients. Cover and cook on low for 5 to 7 hours. Serve with tortilla chips. Yield: About 7 cups.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, put melted margarine, a layer of chicken (deboned), a layer of Veg-All, then place sliced eggs on top.
Mix soup and chicken broth; pour over layers.
Mix Bisquick and water.
Thin as for pancakes.
Pour over top and cook for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: fluff pie
directions: Combine gelatin and 1 cup boiling water, stirring 2 minutes or until gelatin dissolves.
Add 1/2 cup cold water.
Chill until the consistency of unbeaten egg white.
Fold in yogurt and Cool Whip. Pour into pie crust.
Refrigerate until firm.
Yield: 1 pie.

title: kouramblethes greek wedding cookies
directions: Cream butter in electric mixer until it is light and fluffy and add confectioners sugar, slowly beating all the time.
Add egg yolks and almond flavoring.
Sift baking powder with sifted flour and fold into mixture and add nuts.
Knead mixture gently, add more flour to keep hands from sticking.

title: fried bread
directions: Stir first five ingredients together.
Then add the flour until dough is elastic.
Cut into pieces.
Flatten out with fingers.
Cut an X in the middle and fry in hot oil until golden brown.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt together.
Pour into dish with melted butter and milk.
Stir.
Pour peaches on top of mixture and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter, add eggs, coconut and pineapple. Pour into an unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350 for 30 minutes.

title: dried beef ball
directions: Mix well and form balls.
May roll in crushed nuts or leftover dried beef.

title: tomato stacks
directions: Cut each tomato in half crosswise and set aside. Cut each bread slice with a 3/12 inch cookie cutter. Toast bread rounds on each side, and set aside. Cook bacon in a large skillet until crisp; drain well, reserving 2 tbsp. bacon drippings in skillet. Crumble bacon and set aside. Saute green pepper and onion in reserved drippings until tender. Stir in salt. Place toast rounds on a baking sheet. Top each toast round with a tomato half, sauteed mixture, cheese, and crumbled bacon. Broil until cheese melts.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: Put oil in 9 x 12-inch pan and coat bottom and sides of the pan.
Add cake mix, water, eggs and pudding.
Stir.
Add chocolate chips and stir.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: one dish pork chop dinner
directions: Trim fat from pork chops.
Brown chops in a large skillet. Add sliced potatoes.
Add onion (sliced) and green beans (drained).
Spread soup on top.
Add 1/4 cup water.
Simmer one hour.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Mix and pat into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish. Chill 30 minutes in freezer.

title: crab dip
directions: Arrange whipped cream cheese on serving dish.
Top with crabmeat.
Spread sauce over top.
Arrange crackers around sides of dish.

title: kum pao chicken
directions: Procedure #4:
Fry marinated chicken cubes for 30 seconds only, then set aside.
Fry sliced chilies until black, then add 1 teaspoon chopped ginger.
Add chicken and marinated mixture together until a little bit thick.
Add sliced water chestnuts and cashew nuts last.

title: chunky onion flavored potatoes
directions: Wash and peel potatoes into quarters, put into a plastic bag which has Lipton onion soup mix.
Shake and spread onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 1 hour until brown and tender.

title: junk salad
directions: Mix all together.
Put in bowl and chill overnight.

title: butterfinger ice cream
directions: Beat eggs at high speed with electric mixer.
Add sugar and peanut butter; beat well.
Stir in candy and evaporated milk; mix well.
Stir in milk.
Pour mixture into can of 5-quart ice cream freezer; freeze.
Let stand 1 hour before serving.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve cool.
Taste better if left mixed overnight in refrigerator.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients alternately with the mashed bananas.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a greased pan.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix stuffing with 1 stick of margarine and set aside.
Saute onions and carrots until soft.
Mix soup and sour cream and then add to squash, carrots and onion.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Mix
this mixture well, then drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet and bake until brown.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Combine ingredients.
Cook 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Cool in pan right side up.

title: favorite broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli as directed on package.
Add cubed cheese; stir until melted.
Melt butter and pour over crushed crackers.
Add cracker mixture to broccoli and cheese; mix well. Bake in 8-inch or 9-inch square casserole at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: triple delight
directions: Mix flour, oleo and chopped nuts.
Press into 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan.
Bake 15 to 25 minutes in oven.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Beat until creamy and then fold in 1/2 of a 12-ounce carton Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled crust.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; drain off fat. Add onions, bell pepper, tomato sauce, ketchup and salt and pepper.

Simmer until onions and peppers are tender. In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, pour in meat sauce. Top with cheese slices. Arrange biscuits on top of cheese slices; brush with butter. Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.

title: little lunch pizzas(makes 1 serving)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cut English muffin in half.
Toast muffin halves on medium toaster setting.
Put muffin halves on cookie sheet.
Top each half with 1 tablespoon pizza sauce and 1 tablespoon cheese.
Bake in oven about 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix soda and applesauce; beat.
Mix sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add to applesauce mix.
Mix spices and flour; add to mixture.
Add nuts, coconut, cherries and raisins to mixture.
Put a little flour on fruits.
Add 1 cup orange juice for moisture. Bake about 2 1/2 hours at 250° or 275°.

title: corn casserole with spaghetti
directions: Dump into casserole and bake 1 hour at 350° covered with foil.

title: cheezy garlic spread
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth and well blended.
Spread on French bread and sprinkle with paprika.
Place on a baking sheet and place under the broiler for a few minutes.
Watch closely, it burns quickly.
The remainder of spread can be refrigerated.

title: chinese hors d'oeuvre(poo-chi)
directions: Mix all ingredients, except rolls.
Place small amount of mixture on each triangle and fold according to package directions. Bake according to package directions.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Beat egg and add corn, oil and milk.
Put in dry ingredients and add peppers and half of the cheese mix.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.
When brown, spread rest of cheese on top and melt.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine chicken, 1/2 of the cheese, onions, soup, seasonings, and chillies in large bowl.
Heat enchilada sauce in medium saucepan.
Dip the tortillas in the sauce long enough for them to become soft, just a few seconds.
Fill tortilla as you would a crepe and roll.
Place in flat baking dish or casserole.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Beat
cake mix, oranges, eggs and oil until well blended. Pour
into
greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans (1
3/4 cups
approximately
each layer).
Bake 25 minutes at 350°. Remove cake from pans as soon as it comes from the oven and cool. (I
bake
two and then the third since I don't have three 9-inch pans.)

title: oven chicken cacciatore
directions: Place zucchini and artichokes in large shallow casserole dish. Add tomatoes and olives.

title: parsnip timbales
directions: Pare the parsnips; leave whole and steam until tender.
Drain. Mash in a food processor or put through a food mill; there should be about 1 3/4 cups.
Beat eggs and milk until blended; stir in the bread crumbs, salt and orange rind; mix well with the parsnip. Turn into 4 (6 ounce) buttered custard cups.

title: pineapple-cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except 1 cup nuts.
Shape into balls. Use sheet of wax paper to roll ball in remaining nuts.
Chill for 12 to 24 hours before serving.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix the cream cheese, brown sugar and vanilla until smooth. Crush the peanuts and mix with the cream cheese mixture. Serve with sliced apples.

title: sandies
directions: Cream butter and sugar substitute; add water and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add flour and pecans.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Shape in balls or fingers.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° for about 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add molasses and milk.
Mix and sift flour, salt and spices and add to mixture alternately with beaten eggs.
Add orange juice, and last, the soda dissolved in warm water.
Beat until smooth.
Bake in a loaf pan in a moderate oven 45 to 60 minutes.

title: peanut butter frappe
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender; process on high until frothy. Serve immediately. Makes 4 (1-cup) servings.

title: gobs
directions: Bake at 450° until firm.
Cream white sugar, eggs and shortening.
Add buttermilk, vanilla and boiling water. Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt, baking soda and cocoa. Mix together ingredients and drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheets.
Cool and spread with filling.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Cook ingredients, stirring constantly until it begins to thicken.
Add 1 large can of cream and vanilla to taste.
You can cook 4 quarts of milk if you want, or just add enough to fill freezer up to bottom part of paddle.
May need to add a little more sugar.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Drain well. Add finely chopped red onion and green pepper.
Add Salad Supreme. Pour zesty Italian dressing over spaghetti and toss well.
Chill before serving.

title: rice pudding
directions: Bring milk to boil, stir in rice and salt.

title: stew stroganoff
directions: Serve over noodles, rice or toast.
Seve with tossed salad. Fast and easy.
Heat beef stew; add sauces until hot.
Add sour cream.
Heat slowly until hot.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Prepare your favorite pie pastry recipe; roll it as thin as possible.
It does not have to look uniform.
Place on a cookie sheet; prick with a fork.
Brush with melted butter; sprinkle with sugar.
Tilt cookie sheet to side and tap on bottom to remove excess sugar.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Cool, then break or cut into pieces.
Layer individual servings with freshly sliced, sweetened strawberries, peaches or your favorite fruit.
Top with whipped cream or a dairy topping.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream margarine with sugar; add eggs one at a time while beating.
Add 1/2 cup milk and beat thoroughly.
Mix wafers, coconut and pecans.
Add this mixture to batter.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325° in tube pan, which has been greased and floured.
Serve hot or refrigerate.

title: chili-chicken casserole
directions: Put 6 tortilla halves (buttered side up) in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
I spray with PAM first.

title: pot roast
directions: Brown roast that has been rubbed with flour, salt and pepper. Sprinkle ove roast the dressing.
Pour over roast the soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, then drop to 250° until done.
(Total cooking time usually takes 1 hour per pound of roast.)

title: cheese cake pie
directions: Put any regular pie crust into a 9-inch pie plate.
Place all remaining ingredients into a blender and run until smooth.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch container and freeze overnight or 6 to 8 hours.
Take out of freezer 10 minutes before cutting into squares and serve on a lettuce leaf.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Blend yams, 1/2 cup of butter, eggs, milk and sugar at low speed.
Spoon into casserole dish.

title: mediterranean chicken
directions: Dredge chicken in flour; set aside.
Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add chicken and cook 3 minutes on each side or until lightly browned.
Add chicken broth and next 3 ingredients.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Stir in artichoke halves and cook until mixture is thoroughly heated.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Spread ground beef in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put Ragu sauce on top. Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top.
Cover with rolls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: gold and white casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Steam carrots for 5 minutes in 1/4 cup water.
With fork, combine carrots, onion, rice, eggs and cheese. Spoon into greased casserole.
Bake 25 minutes.

title: top of stove bread pudding
directions: In a double boiler, put in order; first, brown sugar.
Add buttered bread cubes.
Beat the eggs; add milk, vanilla and salt. Pour over brown sugar which is in bottom of double boiler.
Do not stir.
Cook over boiling water about 1 hour.
Add raisins and coconut.
Cook until done (custard texture).

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and drain well.
Add all ingredients; mix well and refrigerate until you are ready to serve it.
Hollow out a loaf of bread and put dip in center with pieces of bread around the loaf.
(Round loaf such as rye or pumpernickel bread.)
You can use crackers.

title: 1-2-3 cocktail hot dogs
directions: In a 200° electric skillet or frying pan on low heat, mix mustard and jelly until it makes a smooth mixture (no lumps).
Cut hot dogs into bite size pieces and add to the sauce.
If using electric skillet, lower temperature to 175° and allow to heat about 2 hours.
If using a frying pan, you may transfer all ingredients to a crock-pot and let simmer on low for about 2 hours.
To serve, spear on toothpicks.
(A good appetizer.)

title: banana bread
directions: Mix together margarine and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add the mashed bananas.
Sift flour, soda and add to mixture.
Add nuts and pour in greased loaf pan.
Bake on 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: hamburger surprise
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, brown ground beef. Drain.
Add onions and green pepper and cook until tender.
Stir in tomatoes, rice and spices.
Heat through.
Stir in beef bouillon. Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake 1 hour. Shredded cheese may be added over the top prior to the last 10 to 15 minutes of baking, if desired.
If so, uncover and continue baking.

title: sticky buns for dummies!
directions: Grease a tube pan.
Slice bread dough 1/2 inch thick and place in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle pudding and nuts over rolls.
Heat butter and brown sugar until thickened.
Pour over rolls.
Let rise overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: homemade hamburger helper
directions: Brown ground beef and drain excess fat.
Mix gravy packet according to directions on package.
Prepare noodles according to directions on package.
Mix together the ground beef, gravy and noodles and simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine rice, sugar, vanilla, egg and pineapple in saucepan. Bring to a boil over medium-low heat, stirring constantly. Cook for 2 to 3 minutes until egg is cooked. Cool in bowl. Add whipped cream. Chill. Garnish with additional whipped cream and cherry.

title: oriental bean dish
directions: Mix
well;
salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with mushroom soup,
Parmesan
cheese
and
one can fried onion rings. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: no-cook fondant
directions: Stir butter to soften.
Blend in corn syrup, vanilla and salt. Add sugar, blending first with spoon, then kneading with hands. Knead until smooth.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; stir in tomato soup.
Add onions, green peppers and peas.
Boil noodles as directed on package and drain. Mix noodles with hamburger mixture.
Pour in casserole dish. Sprinkle crumbled Ritz crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: green bean bake
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper.
Cook and drain beans, then add to soup mix and 1/2 of the onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until bubbling.
Top with remaining onion rings and bake for 5 minutes more.

title: spanish rice pronto
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and minute rice (right out of the box) in melted butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer uncovered for 5 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix next four ingredients and stir in broccoli.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Top with crackers. Melt margarine and pour over crackers.
Heat in a 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: italian bread
directions: In a small bowl, mix the salt, malt syrup, milk and 2 1/2 cups of water.
Stir to dissolve the malt which is heavy and thick and set aside.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together pepper, avocados (mashed), lemon juice, and salt.
Mix together mayonnaise, sour cream and taco seasoning.

title: peanut oat cookies
directions: In medium bowl, stir flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Mix in oats; set aside.
In large bowl, with mixer at medium speed, beat margarine and peanut butter until smooth.
Beat in sugars until blended.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour/oat mixture, mixing by hand until well combined.
Shape into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 17 minutes or until golden.

title: homemade hot dog chili
directions: Cook onion, beef and sausage together, stirring until lightly browned.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer about 15 minutes, adding a little water as needed.
Make ahead of time.
Chill. Remove and discard fat.

title: pickled bananas (relish)
directions: Boil bananas in their skins until tender, about 12 minutes. Remove skins.
Prepare pickle by combining lime juice, onion, chives, salt and pepper in a bowl.
Slice bananas and add them to juice, coating well.
Cover bowl and let stand at least 2 hours, tossing bananas in mix every 30 minutes.
Before serving, peel, core and chop cucumbers and garnish relish with cucumbers.

title: pink cranberry freeze
directions: Soften cheese.
