Blend in mayonnaise and sugar.
Add fruit and nuts.
Fold in whipped cream to which powdered sugar has been added.
Pour in square pan and freeze at least 6 hours.

title: german chocolate frosting
directions: Boil.
Cook first 5 ingredients until thick.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.

title: scripture cake
directions: Bake in tube or loaf pan in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Look in Bible for ingredients.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix salt,
celery
seed,
sugar
and vinegar; pour over cucumbers, onion and bell pepper.
Refrigerate.
Will keep for 30 days or more.

title: play dough
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Pour food coloring and oil into water mixture.
Add slowly to dry mixture.
Stir constantly over low heat.
Mixture will darken and be less gooey when done.
Let cool!
Have fun!

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Cream sugar and butter. Add eggs, one at a time, and bananas and nuts.
Then add flour, soda and salt.
Bake in well-greased 5 x 8 x 3-inch pan in 350° oven about 45 minutes.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Drain
cucumber
between paper towels.	Mix ingredients together; chill for 30 minutes.

title: jamaican johnny cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients except milk until butter blends in with the flour evenly. Add a little milk at a time until a firm dough is formed. Divide dough into balls about a Tbsp. in size. Knead each one from the outside in for about 30 seconds. Press gently with hands and fry in oil. Drain and serve hot as a meal side or with honey.

title: red pepper jam
directions: Chop peppers fine; sprinkle with salt.
Let stand 3 or 4 hours.
Rinse well, then cover with sugar and vinegar.
Boil slowly until thick, stirring often to prevent sticking.
Pour into hot jars; seal.
Delicious with cream cheese and crackers.

title: chicken canneloni
directions: Coat a medium saucepan with vegetable cooking spray; place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add next 5 ingredients; saute until tender.
Add 1 teaspoon Italian seasoning and next 4 ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook, uncovered, 20 minutes or until reduced to 2 cups.
Set mixture aside.

title: chocolate lunch box bars
directions: Cream butter until fluffy.
Add sugars.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients; add to cream mixture. Stir in oats, semi-sweet chocolate mini chips and chopped nuts. Turn dough into a 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut into bars when cool.

title: sparkling grape fizz
directions: Chill grape juice and ginger ale.
Pour together just before serving.
Makes a pretty wedding punch.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix brown sugar, sugar, shortening and egg together until creamy.
Add flour, milk, salt, soda, vanilla and rhubarb.
Pour mixture in 13x9 pan.
Add topping (recipe to follow). Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: Brown hamburger.
Combine mayonnaise, milk, eggs, cheese and pepper.
To this mixture add chopped onion and hamburger.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken crunch *
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in baking dish.
Bake 40 minutes at 325°.
After baking, sprinkle with 1/3 cup toasted almonds.
Serves 8.

title: beef stew
directions: Put in large saucepan and brown meat well in shortening; add water, onion, salt, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Cover; simmer 45 minutes until meat is tender, occasionally stir.
Add potatoes, carrots, onion, peas, ketchup and wine.
Cover and simmer for about 20 minutes.

title: french pizza slices
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium heat, cook sausage, onion and garlic until tender and sausage is well browned, stirring to break up meat.
Drain off grease.
Add soup, mushrooms and hot pepper sauce.
Heat to boiling; reduce to low heat and simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; cool slightly.
Place bread, cut side up, on baking pan.
Spoon mixture on bread.
Sprinkle on cheese.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until hot.
Cut each bread half into 8 slices and serve.

title: corn scallop casserole
directions: Combine corn and all remaining ingredients, except cheese. Mix thoroughly and turn into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Top with cheese and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until mixture is set and top is golden brown.

title: shortbread
directions: Beat butter and powdered sugar 2 minutes with mixer.
Add flour.
Whip 2 to 3 minutes until creamy.
Drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet.
Top with cherry pieces.
Bake about 15 minutes at 350°.

title: hot pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple (chop in fine pieces).
Mix sugar and flour, add pineapple juice gradually.
Cook until thick and bubbly.
Add chopped pineapple and grated cheese.
Place in buttered casserole. Top with the 2 cups Ritz cracker crumbs mixed with the 1/2 cup melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: champagne punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in hot tea.
Mix all ingredients, except champagne.
Pour champagne in last over ice mold.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Sift next 8 ingredients together.
Add this to the first mixture and beat thoroughly.
Add boiling water, beating well.
Turn into greased 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Put all ingredients in a plastic bag; shake.
Put into baking pan.
Bake, stirring occasionally, for about 40 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: last-minute chili
directions: *All turkey is fine, too.

title: chicken breast casserole
directions: Bone chicken breast halves.
Roll breast and wrap 1 slice of bacon around each.
Line bottom of baking dish with chipped beef. Place breasts on beef.
Mix cream of mushroom soup (undiluted) with carton of sour cream.
Pour over breasts.
Bake 3 hours in slow oven at 275° to 300°.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Combine syrup, sugar, salt, butter and eggs and mix well. Stir in oatmeal and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fudge pie
directions: Put sugar, flour and cocoa in saucepan. Gradually stir in milk. Stir over medium heat until thick. Remove from stove. Stir in butter and vanilla. Pour into baked pie shell. Cover with meringue and brown.

title: banana split pie
directions: Split the bananas, place on pie shell and sprinkle with lemon juice. Spread ice cream over bananas and freeze. Spread whipped topping over ice cream and top with cherries and walnuts. Freeze. When ready to serve, pour fudge sauce over the top.

title: savory supper
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in chili powder.
Add water. Bring to boil.
Stir in macaroni, tomatoes and corn; stir, uncovered, over medium heat for 10 minutes.
Stir in cheese mix. Serve.

title: kenneth's venison steak
directions: Flour steak and sear in large, deep skillet on both sides. Remove from pan. Place onions, peppers, tomatoes and soup in pan. Bring to simmer. Add meat. Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours. Serve over rice.

title: irish bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, salt, soda and powder and put in large bowl.
Add a lump of shortening (the size of an egg), the eggs, sour milk, raisins and caraway and mix until well blended. Bake at 350° in an iron skillet.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: pork-beef sandwiches
directions: Place uncooked meats in roaster.
Season with spices.
Add chopped onions and pepper.
Cover with ketchup and juice.
Place roaster lid on top of foil.
Cook 4 to 5 hours at 350° (until meat forks apart easily).

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, cinnamon.
Add salt and vanilla.
Combine eggs and sugar and add carrots, pineapple, nuts, raisins.
Add moist and dry ingredients.
Lightly grease 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 370° for 50 minutes or until shrinks from sides of pan.

title: chef's choice fruit salad
directions: Line a large bowl with romaine leaves.
Place torn mixed greens in center of bowl.
Arrange apple slices around the edge of the bowl.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Arrange raisins, almonds and carrot in a circular design on top of lettuce.
Cover and chill.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: Brown beef in skillet. Drain and rinse beef in a colander. Return beef to skillet. Add onion and spices with water to cover. Simmer about 30 minutes.
Dip corn tortillas in hot oil to soften. Fill with beef mixture and roll. Place in flat baking dish. Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted. Top with Green Salsa along with avocado or guacamole and sour cream, if desired.

title: hamburger cabbage casserole
directions: Chop cabbage into medium pieces.
Spread in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Brown meat and onion.
Stir in rice, salt and pepper. Spoon over cabbage.
Heat soup and water to boiling.
Pour over top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: southwestern style corn salad
directions: In small bowl, using wire whisk, blend vinegar, honey and cumin; set aside.
In large bowl, combine remaining ingredients; toss to combine.
Pour dressing over salad mixture; toss lightly to coat.
Refrigerate until serving time.
Serves 7.

title: taco dish
directions: Crush chips on serving plate.
(These may be made individually also.)
Add ground beef; then top with salad items.
Combine Open Pit and tomato soup with chilies for sauce.
Add desired amount to salad, then top with cheese and more crushed chips.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt into large mixing bowl. Cut shortening in until mixture looks like grains of rice; stir in cheese. Stir in milk with a fork just to make a soft dough. Place dough on lightly floured surface and knead 6 to 8 times. Roll 1/2-inch thick and cut with floured cutter. Bake at 425° about 10 to 12 minutes, until golden on top.

title: oyster crackers snack(easy and real good)
directions: Mix all together.
Let set for about 5 hours before eating.

title: cheesy salsa dip
directions: Cut Velveeta up into cubes. Place in a microwavable bowl. Microwave on High for 3 minutes. Stir and add salsa and pimentos. Heat again for about 2 minutes. Stir and serve with your favorite corn chips.

title: garam masala(middle eastern spice for dal and other dishes)
directions: Bring the tomato liquid to a boil.
Combine the vinegar, allspice, mustard, cloves, black pepper and red pepper; add to tomato juice.
Cook until thickened, 3 to 4 hours on low heat, stirring to prevent spices and tomatoes burning on burner, in oven or microwave.
When cool, pour into bottles.
Add 1/2 inch olive oil in each bottle and cork.

title: cream of coconut cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box, using whole eggs.
Bake in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
While hot, prick all over with fork.
Mix milk and cream of coconut.
Pour over cake
while cake is still hot. Let cool and put in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Spread with Cool Whip and sprinkle coconut over top.

title: oven fried fish(microwave)
directions: Dip fish in lemon juice.
Combine crumbs, salt and pepper. Coat fish with crumb mixture.
Place in buttered glass dish. Sprinkle with paprika and cover with waxed paper.
Cook 6 to 7 minutes until fish flakes easily.
Let stand 2 minutes before serving.

title: dovie's lemon pie(old family recipe)
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Add flour, mixing well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add lemon, rind and water.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until filling is set in the center.
A layer of sponge cake will be on the top.

title: dip for chips
directions: Blend all ingredients.
You may add a little milk for desired consistency.

title: teriyaki marinade(for steak)
directions: In shallow bowl or plastic bag, combine all ingredients.
Add the steak, coating with the marinade.
Cover tightly and refrigerate for 6 to 24 hours.
Turn occasionally.
Broil or grill.

title: oatmeal raisin pancakes
directions: Heat griddle to 375°.
Grease lightly with oil.
In a bowl combine oatmeal and water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until all particles are moistened.
Pour 1/4 cup batter for each pancake onto hot griddle.
Cook each side 1 1/2 minutes.
Makes 14 to 16 pancakes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put chicken in bottom of 2-quart casserole.
Mix cream of celery soup and milk.
Mix with chicken.
Pour broth over Stove Top stuffing until moist.
Put on top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs together.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: bev's cheese log
directions: Let cheese stand at room temperature to soften; combine cheese, juice, garlic and pepper; beat with beater until fluffy. Stir in nuts; shape in roll.
Sprinkle with chili powder and paprika mixture.
Serve with crackers.

title: navy cake with richmond chocolate frosting
directions: Mix liquids together well in a large bowl.
Add the dry ingredients; beat until smooth.
Bake for about 45 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Let cool.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix well.
I use this on top of meat loaf, chicken and pork. Will keep in refrigerator.

title: squash casserole 1
directions: Boil squash until tender; drain and mash.
Add eggs, onions, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Add melted oleo.
Pour in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until set, about 45 minutes.
Brush with oleo and sprinkle with cracker crumbs and brown to a golden brown.

title: white christmas cake
directions: Cream butter and oleo.
Add sugar.
Add eggs and cream again. Sift flour with baking soda and add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream.
Add vanilla. fold in nuts, dates and cherries. Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Have orange juice, sugar and bourbon mixed in a cup.
When cake is removed from oven, pour juice mixture over cake and let set for 4 to 5 hours.

title: italian spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Cook onions and celery in shortening until clear.
Add hamburger meat; cook until done, but not brown.
Add the rest of ingredients.
Mix with spaghetti and place in a baking dish.
Top with 1/2 pound of cheese, grated. Bake until cheese melts.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water until tender.
Cool and peel and dice each.
Add mayonnaise and allow to chill thoroughly. Add peeled and diced apples and remaining ingredients.
Chill before serving.
Serves approximately 75.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger, add spices, onions, peppers and tomatoes. Simmer together 15 minutes. Then add tomato paste and water and simmer on low 1 hour.
Cook noodles; drain water.

In large pan, cover bottom of pan with sauce, then add a layer of noodles, layer the sauce, spoon cottage cheese in several places, layer of Mozzarella cheese, then layer of noodles, continue as before.
In preheated 350° oven, bake 40 to 50 minutes.
Remove and let stand 15 to 20 minutes before serving.

title: macaroni and cheese(microwave)
directions: Place butter and onion in 2-quart glass casserole.
Microwave for about 3 minutes on Medium-high or until onion is partly cooked.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover with glass lid or Handi-Wrap.
Microwave for 4 minutes on Medium-high.
Stir lightly; recover and continue cooking for 4 to 5 minutes on Medium-high or until piping hot.
Let stand covered, 5 minutes before serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in casserole dish or 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: meat and cheese roll
directions: Combine beef, eggs, bread crumbs, onions, 2/3 cup tomato sauce, salt, pepper and parsley.
Mix well and shape into flat rectangle on a piece of wax paper.
Sprinkle 3 1/2 cups of cheese over meat mixture.
Starting with short edge, roll up like a jelly roll and press ends of roll to seal.
Bake in shallow pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Drain excess fat.
Pour remaining sauce over roll. Garnish with 1/2 cup cheese and green pepper rings.
Bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: linda's breakfast casserole
directions: Fry sausage and onion.
Drain fat.
Layer sausage in pan, 13 x 9-inches.
Layer bread cubes over sausage.
Sprinkle cheese over bread.
Mix eggs, dry mustard, salt and milk.
Pour over top. Refrigerate overnight.
In the morning bake 1 hour at 355° or until firm.
Serves 5.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, bring 1 1/2 quarts water to a boil.
Add broccoli and onion.
Boil 10 minutes.
Add seasonings and cheese; stir until cheese melts.
Add milk, cream and butter.
Stir and heat to boiling.
Slowly add water to flour, stirring constantly, until texture is smooth.
Slowly add to hot mixture, stirring rapidly.
Cook and stir until soup is the consistency of heavy cream.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Mix eggs, flour, milk, Jack cheese and diced chilies together. Pour into buttered casserole.
Pour tomato sauce over top and smooth.
Top with yellow cheese, olives and onions.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: pickled trout
directions: Remove head and tails from fish and cut into chunks.
Wrap chunks of fish in cheesecloth and simmer in salted water for 30 minutes.
Let fish cool, then wrap in dry cloth and chill.
Combine water, spices and vinegar and bring to a boil; cook for 5 minutes. Chill liquid.
Pour over trout and add oil.
Will keep 3 months.

title: white chili
directions: In a crock pot, add navy beans, broth, soup, water, onion, garlic and salt. Cover and cook while preparing chicken. Add shredded chicken, green chilies, cumin, oregano, ground red pepper, cloves. Cook for another 30 minutes. Add some cheese and salsa and simmer.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water.
Mix all other ingredients.
Mix the flour one cup at a time.
Let stand 10 minutes after mixing.
Knead 5 minutes.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Make or cut into biscuits.
Melt margarine and rub on top of biscuits before baking.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until done.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Combine soup, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, salt and vinegar; pour over warm carrots, garnished with sliced peppers and onions.
Sounds weird but delicious and very colorful.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Then bake 30 minutes at 300°.

title: peach dump cake
directions: Pour peaches with juice in cake pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over peaches.
Dot butter over cake mix.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: white christmas chiffon pie
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Mix together in a saucepan the milk, flour and sugar; cook to slightly thicken and dissolve the gelatin in that.
Cool.
Then whip the cream.
Beat the egg whites until stiff and add the cream of tartar.
To the gelatin mixture, fold in the whipped cream and the egg whites.
Add the vanilla and almond extract.
Then fold in the coconut.
Spoon into the pie shells and chill in the refrigerator.

title: sweet and sour red cabbage
directions: Chop red cabbage in thin strips.
In a big pot, brown the oleo.
Add cabbage and stir until it is covered with oleo.
Add the vinegar, salt and sugar.
Cover tightly and cook about 1 1/2 hours, stirring now and then.
Add jelly, and if mixture looks dry, add a couple tablespoons of water.
Serve with roast pork, goose or duck.

title: wet potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes (approximately 1/8-inch thick).
Place butter in frying pan and melt over low heat (do not burn).
Put in potatoes and chopped onion with small amount of water.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until potatoes are tender and water has boiled away.
(If too much water when potatoes are done, turn up heat and watch until water absorbs.)
Do not brown.

title: christmas fruit balls
directions: Bring to a boil in medium saucepan over low heat the following:
brown sugar and evaporated milk.
Keep stirring constantly until sugar dissolves.
Remove from heat.
Add candied fruit, apricots and pecans into the saucepan.
Stir these ingredients well.
Cool.
Then shape into 1/2-inch balls.
Roll in shredded coconut.
Makes 4 dozen balls.

title: tacos
directions: In 2-quart casserole, break up ground beef in very small chunks. Add onion, green pepper and garlic. Cover.
Microwave on High (10) for 5 to 6 minutes, stirring after 3 minutes. Drain well.
Add tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce, pepper, chili powder and salt. Cover and microwave on High (10) for 5 to 6 minutes, stirring after 3 minutes.

title: sweet potatoes souffle
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows; mix with mixer the remaining ingredients and add to melted butter mixture.
Pour into casserole and bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: palestinian kofta
directions: Soak the bread in milk until it is soft, then drain the milk. Wash and properly drain the ground meat and combine the bread, onions, parsley, salt, black pepper, and cinnamon powder with it. Mix thoroughly with your hands.
Shape into balls.
Bake at 350°F on an oiled pan for about 30 minutes.

title: viola scott's lima beans and bacon bake
directions: Cook lima beans in 1 1/2 cups boiling salted water 15 minutes; drain, reserving 1/2 cup of liquid.
In a skillet, fry bacon until half cooked.
With a slotted spoon remove bacon to paper towels to drain.
Cook onion and celery in bacon fat until softened.
Toss together lima beans, onion, celery, cheese, pepper, sauce and reserved liquid.
Turn into a lightly greased casserole dish. Sprinkle top with the crumbled bacon.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven about 30 minutes or until the top is browned.

title: best ever chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine Crisco, sugar, milk and vanilla in a large bowl. Beat until creamy. Blend in egg.
Mix flour, salt and soda together in separate bowl.
Gradually add flour mixture to batter.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded tablespoonful of dough 3-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes. Do not overbake.
Cookies will look light and chewy.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: best ever sugar cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar until well mixed.
Add eggs, syrup and vanilla.
Mix well.
In a separate bowl, measure flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Add to creamed mixture a little at a time, just until blended.
Chill dough for at least 1 hour.
Divide dough into 4 balls and roll out one ball at a time, leaving the rest of the dough in the refrigerator.

Roll dough to 1/4-inch thickness and cut into heart shapes or other shapes; place on an ungreased cookie sheet and bake 5 to 9 minutes in a 375° oven. When lightly browned, remove from oven and place on racks to cool. Frost when completely cooled.

title: easy rump roast barbecue(prep time: 10 minutes; crock-pot: high  6 hours or low 9 hours.)
directions: Place onions in bottom of crock-pot, then place roast on top of onions. Mix Coke and next 7 ingredients. Reserve 1 cup and refrigerate. Pour rest of sauce over roast. Cover with lid and cook by times indicated. When done, remove and shred with forks. Combine reserved sauce (1 cup), ketchup and butter. Heat and serve.

title: squash puffs
directions: Combine ingredients and drop by spoonful into hot oil.
Brown well.
Spoon 4x sugar after draining.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: In a large saucepan, combine bacon grease, sugar, water and vinegar.
Heat at medium heat until it thickens.
Remove from heat; let cool.
Break lettuce up in a large salad bowl.
Crumble cooked bacon over lettuce; pour cooled sauce over lettuce.
Toss and serve.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Mix and heat until melted the oil, margarine, cocoa and water. Bring to boil.
Set aside.
Mix sugar and flour, then pour heated mixture into it.
Beat well.
Mix buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla.
Pour into other ingredients.
Blend well.
Pour into greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: cranberry orange salad
directions: Make jello with jello and hot liquid; when jello thickens, add other ingredients and let set until firm.

title: orange chicken pasta salad
directions: Mix dressing, juice and seasonings in a large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Refrigerate.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine corn meal mix, sugar and onion in bowl.
Add milk and egg to dry ingredients, stirring to combine.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls into hot deep fat (375°), frying only a few at a time.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.

title: baked pancake for two
directions: Melt
butter
in
skillet.
Mix
flour, milk and beaten eggs. Pour
in
skillet.	Top
with nutmeg.
Put in preheated oven at 425° for 20 to 30 minutes.	Serve with sifted powdered sugar and marmalade.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Break spaghetti into small pieces and cook in the chicken broth that has been saved from cooking the chicken for extra flavor.
Cook onions, pepper and celery together in a small amount of margarine until tender.
Grease a large casserole dish (or 2 medium dishes).
Layer half of spaghetti, half of chicken, half of onion mixture and one can of mushroom soup.
Repeat this procedure to make the second layer.
Top with grated cheese and bake about 30 minutes at 375° until cheese melts and is bubbly.

title: yummy coffee cake
directions: Layer the rolls in a lightly greased Bundt pan.
Melt the margarine and pour over the rolls.
Mix the vanilla pudding, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle mixture over rolls.
Top with chopped nuts.
Cover pan with towel and let stand in cold oven overnight or rise 4 hours in a warm place.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Let cool slightly and turn onto plate.

title: cheese straws
directions: Sift flour and baking powder into a bowl.
Cut in cheese and butter with pastry blender.
Add water and mix well.
Fill cookie press.
Form straws on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake and cut into desired length and remove from sheet.
Time: 8 to 10 minutes. Temperature: 375°.

title: collard greens
directions: Check
leaves
of fresh greens carefully.
Remove pulpy stems and
discolored
spots
on	leaves.
Wash thoroughly in several changes
of
water.
You can add a little salt to the last	water. Place
the
greens
in a colander to drain.
Put meat
in a large pot with at least 2 quarts of water, bring to a
boil.
When boiling
good, put the greens in the pot.
You can	cut
them
up first
or
you
can cut them after they've cooked.	Cook
on
low until done, about 2 hours, but you can hardly
cook
collards too long.
You may have to add a little water
as
it
boils
down and it is best to use hot water.
I always
add about a teaspoon of sugar when they have cooked on low	awhile.
When
cleaning greens, cut out most of the stem. When done, take a sharp kitchen knife and fork to cut them.

title: 7-up jello salad
directions: Dissolve and melt jello and marshmallows in hot water.
Add pineapple, bananas and 7-Up; let jell.

title: spiced red cabbage(very good recipe from germany.)
directions: Place cabbage in a large kettle of boiling salted water; boil for 1 minute. Drain. Return to kettle; stir in remaining ingredients. Cover and simmer for 1 hour or until cabbage is tender. Remove bay leaf. Yield: 12 servings.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix
all together and mix well.
Pour into tube pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: jiffy cake
directions: Mix all with a wooden spoon lightly.
Put in a greased Bundt pan and bake at 375° for 45 minutes, or until done.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients and bake at 350° until done.

title: beef-sausage casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter. Brown beef and sausage; drain and mix together. Cook macaroni per package directions; drain.
Mix all together and place in casserole dish. Top with cheese. Bake at 350° until heated through and cheese melts.

title: cabbage stew
directions: Brown meat, onion and pepper together.
Add beans, tomatoes and Ro-Tel.
Chop cabbage on top and simmer until done.

title: panforte di'siena(yield one 8-inch or three 4-inch)
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Line bottom of 8-inch spring-form pan or small 4-inch aluminum pans with parchment paper.
Butter paper and sides of pan.
Mix nuts, fruits, cocoa, spices and flour in large bowl.
Stir honey and sugar in heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring, until sugar is dissolved.
Increase heat to medium-high and cook until candy thermometer measures 248°, firm ball stage. Immediately pour over nut-fruit mixture.
Divide batter between prepared pans using moistened fingers to pat down air pockets. Bake until tops are no longer sticky, about 35 minutes.
Transfer to rack to cool.
Turn cakes out and sift.
Wrap tightly in plastic wrap.
Panforte can be stored in airtight container 1 month at room temperature or 3 months in freezer.

title: zesty tasty meat loaf
directions: Make
a
regular
stew using deer meat.
Add 2 teaspoons garlic and 1 cup red wine.

title: barbecued pork shoulder
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter until tender.
Add catsup, vinegar, water, brown sugar, lemon zest, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, hot sauce and chili powder; cook until hot. Place roast on grill over low coals.
Cover grill; open vent. Grill roast 3 hours, turning occasionally.
Baste roast with barbecue sauce.
Cook 1 hour or until tender, basting frequently with sauce.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: stick to your ribs corn chowder
directions: No salt needed because of ham.

title: dixie delight
directions: Mix all together and freeze.
While freezing, stir often so it won't separate.
Serve by the scoop in a glass and pour 7-Up, Mountain Dew or Sprite over the scoops.
You can add variations of the fruit and the quantities.

title: baked stew
directions: Put all ingredients in casserole dish raw.
Cover tightly and bake at 250° for 4 hours.
Delicious.

title: crab zucchini casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Add onion, zucchini and garlic.
Saute a few minutes until onion is transparent.
Combine with tomatoes, crab, 1 cup cheese, 3/4 cup bread crumbs, salt, pepper and basil.
Mix lightly, but thoroughly.

title: cheesy chicken breast
directions: Wash chicken; dry and salt and pepper.
Cut chunks of cheese for each piece of chicken.
Wrap chicken around the cheese.
Keep rolled up.
Melt butter; add garlic powder and wine, mixed together.
Pour over chicken; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.
Last 10 minutes, sprinkle almonds over the chicken.
May be served with a rice dish.
Makes 12 servings.

title: pocketburgers
directions: Mix ground beef, salt and pepper.
Between sheets of waxed paper, roll out patties 1/4-inch thick.
Center half of patties with small amount of shredded cheese and onion and dash of barbecue sauce.
Top with meat lids.
Press around edges to seal.
Broil over hot coals for 12 to 15 minutes, turning once.
Or, bake under broiler in oven for 12 to 15 minutes, turning once.
Makes three large burgers.

title: cold pea salad
directions: In large bowl, mix all ingredients.
Keep adding mayonnaise until all ingredients are covered well.
Peas can either be left out to thaw or mix frozen if made ahead of time such as the night before.

title: jennifer's favorite dip
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut top of bread out and save.
Hollow out center of loaf.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Place strawberries into pie shell.
Cook sugar, cornstarch, Jell-O and 7-Up in heavy saucepan until thick.
Pour over strawberries in pie shell.
Chill for about 2 hours.
Top with whipping cream or Cool Whip.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar until well blended.
Add oil gradually. Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and spices.
Blend into mixture gradually and thoroughly.
Stir in zucchini.
Grease and flour lightly 2 (8 x 4-inch) loaf pans.
Divide mixture evenly.
Let stand 5 or 10 minutes.
Heat oven to 350°.
Bake for 45 minutes or until toothpick comes clean from center.
Don't overbake.

title: homemade bread
directions: Put 2 packages dry yeast in a cup of very warm water.
Set aside.
Put in saucepan the oleo, milk, sugar and salt.
Heat until oleo is melted.
Remove from heat.
Put in big bowl.
Add 1 cup of cold water.
Stir in yeast.
Add enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Knead on flour surface.
Put in greased bowl and let raise until doubled.
Knead again and put into bread pans and let raise again.
Bake at 375° to 400° until golden brown.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil chicken until cooked.
Combine soup with half of the flowerets; add cream, salt and pepper. Heat.
Dice chicken and add to soup mixture.
Serve mixture over cooked rice.

title: crab spread
directions: Combine all ingredients and spread in greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or spread on bread and heat!

title: cheese cake
directions: All ingredients should be at room temperature.
Blend all together, except eggs.
Add eggs one at a time; mix well.
Flour and grease 10-inch spring-form pan.
Wrap pan in foil.
Put spring-form pan in a pan of hot water (375°).
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or longer.
Remove from water and cool 2 hours.

title: hush puppies
directions: Add milk to make a heavy batter.
Mix well and spoon into hot oil in a deep fryer.
Cook until brown.

title: german kuchen
directions: Every family has something to fall back on when time is short, cupboard bare and you always have the ingredients.

title: pineapple beets
directions: Combine first four ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, until thick (about 2 minutes).
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook over medium heat for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Yields 4 to 5 servings.

title: apple pie filling
directions: Peel, core and slice apples.
Blend water and lemon juice. Fill jars with apple slices.
Mix all other ingredients in large saucepan.
Bring to boil and stir to thicken.
Pour over apples. Process in boiling water bath 20 minutes.
One jar makes 1 large pie; 2 jars makes cookie sheet of bars.

title: chili sauce
directions: Cook all except vinegar until thickened, then add cider vinegar.
Cook down again until thickened.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Combine sugar and flour in a bowl.
Heat margarine, Coca-Cola and cocoa to boiling.
Melt marshmallows in hot mixture.
Pour this over flour mixture.
Add other ingredients and mix well by hand.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured dish at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Ice while hot.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together good and roll in fine nuts.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package, then drain off excess water.
Add broccoli to other ingredients, except crackers.
Put crackers on top and cook at 400° for 25 minutes. (It may take a little longer so that it is firm.)

title: chinese chicken casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in oil till tender. Add chicken, soups, mayonnaise, rice, water chestnuts, and almonds. Mix well. Place in baking dish. Combine cornflakes and margarine, spread on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese balls with pecans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients, cutting the margarine into the mixture.
Roll into balls (1 teaspoon dough for each ball).
Press 1/2 pecan onto top of each ball.

title: quick casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add dry soup mix, tomato sauce, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes. Mix in cooked elbow macaroni.
Place in casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Combine egg, 1/4 cup of the soup, uncooked rice, onion powder and pepper. Add beef; mix well. Shape into 20 meatballs. Place in a large skillet. Mix the remaining soup with Worcestershire sauce, oregano and 1/2 cup water. Pour over meatballs. Bring to boiling; reduce heat. Cover; simmer, stirring often, about 20 minutes or until no pink remains in meat and rice is tender. Skim fat. Pass Parmesan cheese if desired, or sweet and sour sauce poured over is great too. Serves 4 to 5.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix crumbs and melted butter together.
Press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Cream soft butter, sugar and eggs.
Spread over cooled crust.
Lay cut bananas on top of creamed mixture.
Spread pineapple over bananas.
Spread Cool Whip over pineapple and top with nuts.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Mix all except eggs.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat well. Add vanilla and beat.
Bake in greased, floured oblong pan 1 hour and 10 minutes at 300°.

title: baked fish
directions: If fish fillets are large, cut into 5 or 6 serving pieces. Sprinkle both sides of fish with salt and pepper.
Mix butter, lemon juice and onion. Dip fish into butter mixture. Arrange in ungreased square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inch.
Pour remaining butter mixture over fish.
Cook, uncovered, in a 350° oven until fish flakes easily with fork, 25 to 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: rich lemon sauce for gingerbread
directions: In a saucepan,
blend
the
butter,
sugar
and
flour; gradually add the boiling
water.
Add
lemon peel and nutmeg. Boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in the lemon juice. Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and dressing.
Pour over vegetables and mix.
Best to set 3 to 4 hours in refrigerator. Very low in fat grams.

title: kathryn's snack mix
directions: Mix all the ingredients and out it comes.
Hope you enjoy it.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: To Make Crust:
Press crescent rolls out on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake according to directions on package.
Let cool.

title: kentucky stack cake
directions: After sifting flour (you won't use it all) into a large bowl, place softened butter in a well in the center.
Add the sugar and work the soda, salt and pumpkin spice into sugar with the fingers. Add egg and work it together with the sugar and the butter.
Add buttermilk gradually, working in flour as you go, until all buttermilk is used and a soft dough is made.
Divide dough into 7 equal portions and press into greased and floured 9-inch layer cake pans.
Bake layers at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, turning out layers and baking the remaining layers until all dough is baked.
Sift unused flour back into storage container.

title: saucy meat loaf
directions: Add bread to milk and let stand for a couple of minutes.
Mix beef, egg, pepper, Worcestershire and onion.
Shape into loaf and place into baking pan.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Crush chips and spread over bottom of dish.
Spread chicken over chips.
Blend all other ingredients together and pour over chicken.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Gently squeeze broccoli to extract all liquid.
Spread broccoli in pie shell. Sprinkle with cheese.
Beat eggs, salt and pepper.
Beat half and half into eggs until well blended.
Pour into pie shell. Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake 15 minutes before serving.

title: craby cheese dip
directions: Drain crabmeat and combine with remaining ingredients in large bowl.
Taste for seasoning.
Spoon into a 6-cup souffle dish. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot with crackers or crusty bread.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar and beer together.
Knead a few times with spoon.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Pour melted oleo over bread.
Return to oven and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Cream peanut butter, margarine and powdered sugar.
Blend in Rice Krispies.
Form 1-inch balls and place on waxed paper. Refrigerate 1 hour.
Melt chocolate chips.
Dip balls into chocolate and place on waxed paper.
Refrigerate until chocolate hardens.

title: canada treat-confetti candy
directions: Melt chips and margarine in microwave or double boiler.
Then add peanut butter and marshmallows.
Mix.
Put in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cheesy hash browns
directions: Put potatoes in casserole dish and sprinkle with onion powder. Mix sour cream and soup and pour over potatoes.
Mix melted margarine and bread crumbs and spoon over to create another layer. Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° until brown (approximately 20 to 30 minutes).

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots with powdered sugar and salt until tender (do not overcook).
Drain.
Melt butter with cheese over very low heat. Stir to prevent sticking.
Place carrots in flat baking dish and cover with cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with Ritz cracker crumbs. Dot with more butter.
Place in oven and bake until heated through.

title: scrumptious ice cream dessert
directions: Crush cookies in Ziploc bag.
Combine cookie crumbs and butter and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate.
Spoon softened ice cream on crust.
Heat hot fudge so it is warm.
Spread on ice cream.
Spread whipped cream over chocolate layer and sprinkle with nuts.
Freeze 2 hours, then cover with foil.
Keeps for a month.

title: chili dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 10 inch deep dish pie pan or shallow 1 1/2 qt. baking dish.
Spread cream cheese in bottom of baking dish.
Mix chili and salsa until blended, then pour over cream cheese.
Sprinkle with Jack and Colby cheeses.
(Wrap and refrigerate at this point if making ahead.)
Bake 25 to 35 minutes, until bubbling and cheese melts.
Serve hot or at room temperature. Serves 12.

title: spicy spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef with chopped onions.
Stir in remaining ingredients; simmer slowly for 1 1/2 hours.

title: grilled basil chicken
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in container of an electric blender; process 30 seconds.
With motor running, gradually add olive oil in a slow steady stream.
Reserve 1/4 cup basil mixture.

title: zucchini lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Wash and dice zucchini.
Cut lengthwise into 4 slices each, salt and set aside to drain. Brown one pound hamburger and chopped onions and drain.
Rinse off zucchini and pat dry.

title: sour cream casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients (except margarine) and spoon into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour oleo over top.
Bake at 400° about 25 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Fill gallon jar with cucumbers and cover with vinegar; add salt. Let set 6 weeks. Drain and wash twice. Cut into size you want. Put back in gallon jar; pour sugar over cucumbers and let stand until sugar is melted. May leave in gallon jar or put into several smaller jars.

title: lemon-broccoli chicken
directions: In skillet over medium-high heat, cook chicken in hot oil 10 minutes or until browned on both sides.
Drain off fat.

title: icebox pie
directions: Pour Eagle Brand milk in large bowl.
Add lemon juice and mix well.
Add drained pineapple, pecans (broken or whole), coconut and Cool Whip.
Put on graham cracker crust and refrigerate.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mash squash and add 1/4 cup melted butter, salt, pepper, sugar, 1/4 cup cornmeal, eggs and onions.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup cornmeal on top and 1/4 cup melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: denver chocolate pudding
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients.
Melt chocolate and butter, add to sifted mix.
Add milk and vanilla; mix well.
Put into buttered baking pan (9 x 9-inch).
Sprinkle in layers over the top of batter; brown sugar, white sugar then cocoa.
Pour cold water over all.
Bake at 325°. for 40 minutes.
Let stand a little while.
Serve warm with whipped cream or over ice cream.
It will be cakie on top with thick syrup on bottom.

title: smoked sausage and rice
directions: Coat 10-inch skillet with Pam.
Add sausage, onion, pepper and celery; saute until tender.
Add tomatoes, reserved liquid, garlic, thyme and cayenne.
Gently fold in cooked rice.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Mix in order given except cheese.
Bake in covered dish 35 minutes longer for regular rice at 350°.
Take lid off and sprinkle cheese on top.
Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Put cupcake liners in muffin pans.
Beat milk, oil and egg.
Stir in flour, sugar, baking powder and salt, all at once, just until flour is moistened (batter will be lumpy). Fold in blueberries.

title: preacher's cake
directions: Mix the dry ingredients, then balance of mixture.
Mix by hand.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: country vegetable soup (microwave)
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook in microwave for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: 24 hour vegetable salad
directions: In bottom of large bowl, place half the lettuce; sprinkle with a little sugar, salt and pepper.
Layer eggs on top; again sprinkle with salt.
Next layer, put peas and remaining lettuce, bacon and cheese.
Spread mayonnaise over top, sealing to the edge of bowl.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours or overnight.
Garnish with sliced green onion and paprika.
Toss before serving.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: sour cream pie
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together.
Press into a 10-inch spring-form pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: ever ready rolls
directions: Combine scalded milk, sugar, shortening and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add egg.
For about 20 minutes, let yeast soften in 1/4 cup warm water.
Add to milk mixture.
Gradually add flour and knead well.
Place bowl of dough in warm place to rise about 1 hour.
Make out rolls and let rise again or place in refrigerator and use as needed.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Mix first 12 ingredients together. Place in a 2-quart buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle with potato chips.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or longer if needed.

title: west haven cake
directions: Cut the dates in half and pour the hot water over them with the baking soda and let cool. Cream the sugar and shortening. Add dates to creamed mixture and salt if butter is not used.
Add the eggs, vanilla and flour, sifted with cocoa.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle the nut meats and chocolate over the dough in pan.
Bake 40 minutes in moderate oven. Serve with whipped cream.

title: blue ribbon apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into unbaked 9-inch pastry shell.
Pat with butter; cover with pastry shell.
Slit top.
Bake in a hot oven (425°) for 10 minutes.
Turn back to 350°; continue to bake for 30 minutes.
Serve with vanilla ice cream!!!

title: sausage souffle
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and mustard. Add cubed bread and stir.
Add cheese and sausage.
Refrigerate for several hours.
Bake in a glass 8 x 12-inch pan at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Let stand a few minutes before serving.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes and separate potatoes from skin and in large mixing bowl combine potatoes with rest of ingredients.
Refill potato skins with the mixture and bake at 350°.

title: plum pudding
directions: Mix the ingredients all together; then stiffen with flour.
Put pudding in coffee cans after cans are greased and floured.
Cover cans; then place in roasting pan half full of water and put in oven at 250°.
Steam for 3 hours.
Makes two 1 pound puddings.

title: apple bird's nest
directions: Peel apples. Slice thin a quart of them.
Put in a buttered pudding or shallow dish.
Pour over them a cup of hot water.
Make a stiff batter of sour milk, a little salt, butter and flour to form a batter.
Put in last a teaspoonful of soda dissolved in hot water.
If baked in a flat tin pan, it will bake in half an hour, but if in a dish, it will take 3/4 of an hour.

title: skillet casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer 20 minutes.

title: dundee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together in a bowl.
Beat in 1 egg at a time.
Gradually stir in flour, fruits and orange rind.
Pour into a tube pan lined with buttered paper (or baking paper).
Flatten top and decorate with almonds.
Bake in moderate oven until done in center.

title: cherry cheese pizza
directions: Mix pastry sticks according to package directions.
Roll out pastry into a 14-inch circle.
Place on a 12-inch pizza pan and flute edges.
Prick crust.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Blend cream cheese and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Pour into partially baked crust and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Spread cherry pie filling over cheese layer.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Cook chopped cabbage 8 minutes in salted boiling water. Drain.
Put into buttered casserole.
Pour on white sauce and sprinkle on cheese.
Put on green pepper.
Cover with bread crumbs and bacon.
Bake in 375° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Add to juice and bring to a boil.
Pour over ingredients and let stand 2 days.

title: buttermilk mashed potatoes
directions: Place potatoes and 1 teaspoon of salt in saucepan and add enough cool water to cover.
Bring to boil over high heat.
Reduce heat and cook until potatoes are tender.
Drain, reserving few tablespoons cooking liquid.
Place potatoes in large bowl and mash with potato masher or fork until fairly smooth (with some lumps remaining).
Combine buttermilk and baking soda and beat into potatoes with wooden spoon; mix well.
If you prefer creamier potatoes, add reserved cooking liquid.
Stir in butter, 1/2 teaspoon salt and plenty of pepper to taste.

title: annie kate's sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix flour, soda and salt.
Set aside.
Cream sugar, Crisco and margarine.
Add other ingredients except flavorings and beat for 4 minutes.
Add flavorings last.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: chicken a la bet
directions: Add in that order; pour over the chicken.
Cover chicken and cook 30 minutes or until done or in 350° oven, in covered dish, bake for 45 minutes.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Melt butter.
Mix with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat after each egg.
Beat well.
Add flour, baking powder and vanilla. Add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pop-pop's baked rockfish
directions: Place potatoes in baking pan.
Arrange onions on top of potatoes.
Place rock on top of onions.
Put 3 to 4 rings of onions on top of rock and then lay strips of bacon across.
Bake, covered, until fish and potatoes are tender, about 1 hour at 350°.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix together eggs, rice, sugar and milk.
Add raisins, vanilla and nutmeg.
Melt margarine in baking dish, then pour in mixture. Bake, uncovered, in 375° oven for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: the stuff
directions: Layer Cool Whip alternately with cookies, dipped in milk, Cool Whip first and last.
Top with cookie crumbs.
Refrigerate several hours, overnight better.
Freezes well.
Serve in dessert bowls. May use other cookies.
Firm ones work better.
Large round Tupperware cake taker holds 3 packages cookies and 2 (12 ounce) containers Cool Whip.
Serves approximately 10.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in dish in 350° oven.
Sift flour and add sugar and milk in bowl.
Pour batter over melted margarine.
Put can of pie filling on top and bake 35 to 45 minutes or until brown.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Sift flour, measure, resift three times with baking powder, soda and salt.
Cream shortening and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs, vanilla and nuts, mix well.
Add flour mixture in 4 or 5 portions. Divide dough in 4 portions and shape each portion in a roll 1 3/4 inches in diameter.
Wrap in wax paper and chill several hours or overnight until dough is stiff enough to slice.
Cut slices approximately 3/16 inch thick with sharp knife.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in moderate oven, 375°, about 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from pan to cake racks.
Makes 12 to 12 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: tossed broccoli salad
directions: Fry bacon crispy, drain and crumble.
Set aside.
Mix mayo, sugar and vinegar until smooth for dressing.
Toss remaining ingredients together.
Pour dressing mix over salad, adding bacon pieces and blending well.
Chill and serve.
Instead of peanuts you can add hard Chinese noodles just before serving.

title: jell-o cake
directions: While your cake is still hot, use a fork and poke holes all over the top. Let cool. Mix jell-o with 1 c. hot water. Stir to dissolve completely. Pour over cake into holes. Refrigerate for 3 to 4 hours. Mix pudding according to package and pour over top of cake. Refrigerate.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: Brown Rice-A-Roni in margarine.
Saute vegetables with Rice-A-Roni.
Add water and seasoning packet.
Add shrimp and Spam.
Reduce heat, cover and let steam 15 minutes, until liquid is absorbed.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, pineapple, nuts, salt and sugar.
Make 3 layers of potato mixture with marshmallows between each layer.
Top with lots of butter and more sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Yields 10 servings.
This freezes well.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all together and put in greased dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: quick fudge
directions: Melt ingredients in a double boiler.
Add pecans.
Pour into a 9 x 5-inch buttered pan.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: creamed ham, egg and mushrooms(beverly slimm)
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter until lightly browned.
In saucepan, add soup, mushrooms, milk and ham; stir to mix.
Add eggs and stir gently not to crumble eggs.
Heat well and serve over sliced biscuits or toast.

title: corn pudding
directions: Place all ingredients into a blender.
Mix 10 seconds at high speed.
Pour into well-greased dish and bake 45 minutes at 375°. Do not cover.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In medium saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in brown sugar and milk.
Bring to a boil and stir for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat. Stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix in powdered sugar and beat until smooth.
Spread into buttered 9-inch square baking pan. Chill until firm.
It's oohh so good!

title: stuffed peppers 57
directions: Clean out peppers; combine ground beef, onion, rice, 57 sauce and ketchup.
Stuff peppers; arrange in greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberries in almond yogurt
directions: Make several hours in advance.
Wash, hull and drain strawberries (may be halved).
Mix together remaining ingredients. Fold in strawberries.
Spoon into champagne glasses and refrigerate.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: In large bowl, mix well oil, eggs and sugar.
In separate bowl, sift together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and baking powder; add to mixture.
Stir in nuts and chopped apples; mix well. Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle chips on top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: spaghetti dinner
directions: Prepare spaghetti as directed on package.
Brown meat and onion.
Drain.
Stir in spice mix, tomato paste and water or tomato sauce and stewed tomatoes.
Bring to boil.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Place in 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish in layers: 1/2 spaghetti, 1/2 meat-sauce mix; 1/2 cottage cheese; 1/2 broccoli and 1/2 Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until broccoli is done.

title: frozen mint pie
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine Eagle Brand milk, peppermint extract and food coloring.
Fold in whipped cream; pour into crust.
Cover.
Freeze 6 hours or until firm.
Makes 1 pie.

title: squash casserole(freezes well!)
directions: Cook squash with a chopped onion.
Put well drained hot squash in large mixing bowl.
Add egg, margarine, mayonnaise, sugar, half
of the cheese, and half of the crackers.
Season with cayenne pepper, salt, pepper and oregano; mix well.
Put into
a buttered
quart
casserole
dish and top with remaining cheese
and crackers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Crookneck squash or a mixture of crookneck and zucchini may be used.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: susie's tea cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Sift together flour, baking soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Add to mixture and mix.
Stir in nuts.
Chill dough until easy to handle.

title: golden fruit punch
directions: Boil sugar and 4 cups water together to dissolve sugar. Chill.
Add cold fruit juices and remaining water.
Chill.
Just before serving, stir in ginger ale and add ice.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons or 25 servings.

title: josephines
directions: Mix well the chilies, garlic and butter.
Mix well the cheese and mayonnaise.
Cut the rolls into 6 or more slices.
Toast on one side.
On untoasted side, spread chili mixture.
Top with cheese mixture and put under broiler until hot and cheese begins to melt.

title: fettuccine with vodka and tomato sauce(prep:  10 minutes; cook:  25 minutes; serves:  4)
directions: Heat oil in a medium skillet; add onion.
Saute until tender, but not browned, about 5 minutes.
Stir in garlic; saute 1 minute. Add the tomatoes, vodka and red pepper.
Simmer, stirring to break up tomatoes with the side of a spoon, until sauce is reduced and thickened, about 15 minutes.
Stir in cream; simmer, stirring, until sauce is thickened slightly, about 5 minutes.
Season with salt.

title: crazy cake
directions: Mix in pan with spoon.
Do not use mixer.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: chicken and rice scramble
directions: Combine rice and 1/2 cup of bacon drippings; stir for a couple of minutes until hot.
Add rest of ingredients and heat through.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together the Crisco and sugar. Add eggs; beat well. Sift dry ingredients together, then add to creamed mixture alternately with bananas. Blend well. Add nuts.
Pour into greased 5 x 9-inch bread pans. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: no crust quiche
directions: Saute bacon in skillet until partially cooked.
Add onion and cook until onion is tender but not browned.
Pour off most of the fat.
In a separate bowl, combine eggs, salt, pepper and nutmeg; beat well.
Add milk and blend well.
Spread onion mixture in 4 pie pans or 2 (13 x 9-inch) pans.
Sprinkle evenly with cheese.
Pour egg mixture over cheese.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Serves 24.

title: mashed potato rolls
directions: Soften yeast in some warm water with 2 tsp. sugar.
Combine the warm water/potato water with the sugar and salt.
Add the yeast mixture, eggs and shortening.
Add the warm mashed potatoes and 7 c. flour.
Knead until smooth, adding more flour as/if needed.
At this point, the dough may be refrigerated if you're not ready to continue with making the rolls.
When ready to bake, form rolls and let rise until doubled in size.
Bake at 400° for 12-15 minutes.

title: gina's fresh apple cake
directions: Add ingredients in order. Use tube or Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: pickle burgers
directions: Combine beaten egg with onion, prepared horseradish, Worcestershire sauce, salts and pepper.
Add ground beef and mix well.
Divide beef mixture into 6 portions and shape around the pickles into patties.
Broil 3 inches from the heat for 6 minutes. Flip burgers and broil 4 to 6 minutes more.
Serve in toasted buns.

title: spicy barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Add rest of ingredients. Freezes well.

title: swiss steak
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper and pound it into steak.
Brown the steak in Dutch oven or deep skillet.
Mix tomatoes and onion and heat to a boil.
Layer with steak and cook in moderate oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cover before cooking.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: french fried potato and onions
directions: Cut potato
in	strips and onions in strips; sprinkle a little sugar
over
them.	Let
stand
10 minutes.
Put enough Carnation milk over them to moisten real good.
Put flour over and mix well.
Put	in
deep oil and cook until golden brown. Drain on paper towel.

title: appetizer pie
directions: Sprinkle top with pecans.
Heat and serve with crackers or Melba toast.
A good dip to munch on while watching the Oilers beat the Cowboys.

title: hamburger buns
directions: Dissolve and soak yeast in water.
Scald the milk.
Cool to lukewarm.
Cream butter, sugar and salt until light.
Add cooled milk, eggs and 4 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add yeast and water.
Mix thoroughly.
Turn out onto 1 cup flour.
Knead until light and elastic.
Place in greased bowl and cover.
Let rise until doubled.
Punch down.
Shape into hamburger buns.
Put in pan and let rise until double.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: diabetic brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt chocolate chips over low heat. Place all ingredients in bowl and stir until blended.
Turn into lightly greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes.
Cut into 16 (2-inch) squares while warm.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
While still warm, add cream cheese until it is softened and mixed well.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, lay one can of rolls to create crust.
Squeeze seams together.
Spread sausage and cream cheese mixture on top of rolls.
Cover with the other can of crescent rolls to create a top crust.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sugar cookies(non-roll)
directions: Cream sugars with oil, butter and eggs.
Add vanilla. Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture and mix well.
Chill dough for 2 hours for easy handling.
Roll a teaspoonful into ball and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Using a small glass, dip into sugar and flatten each cookie ball.
Cookie press or glass with pattern on bottom can also be used.
Bake at 350° about 10 to 12 minutes until slightly golden brown. Makes about 90 cookies.

title: aunt estelle's orange salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add oranges, crushed pineapple and all juices.
Pour in 13 x 9 x 2-inch Pyrex dish.
Put miniature marshmallows all over top.
Let jell.
Add 1/2 cup mayonnaise to 1/2 pint of whipping cream (whipped).
Pour on top and put grated cheese on top.
Let sit overnight.

title: "she" crab soup
directions: Mix all ingredients lightly.
Add sherry.
Cook over low heat 25 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate-peanut butter balls
directions: Mix all ingredients except chocolate in large bowl, by hand is best.
Form into small balls and dip into melted chocolate.
Set on waxed paper.
Makes 4 dozen medium sized balls.

title: apple and berry bread pudding
directions: Mix apples, berries, water and sugar in saucepan; bring to a boil, add tapioca.
Mix milk, eggs, sugar, vanilla and bread cubes. Pour fruit mixture into oiled 8 x 12-inch pan.
Gently spoon milk-egg-bread mixture over fruit to make a separate layer.
Bake at 350°, about 50 minutes.

title: spice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
In a separate bowl combine buttermilk and baking soda; add to butter and sugar mixture.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into greased and floured baking pan and bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Cool cake completely and frost with Brown Sugar Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix ingredients in order.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: squash and apple bake
directions: Cook squash until slightly tender and cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Mix ingredients (sugar, flour, salt and cinnamon). Arrange squash in ungreased baking dish (11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch).
Top with apple slices.
Sprinkle sugar mixture over top.
Cover with foil.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until squash is tender.
Serves 6.

title: rice krispie balls
directions: Cook sugar, egg yolks, butter and dates until sugar is melted, stirring constantly.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Remove from heat and add Rice Krispies.
Stir until mixed well.
When cool enough to handle, shape into small balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Makes approximately 36 balls.

title: chocolate chip cookie cake
directions: Blend the eggs, sugar and cheese together.
Cut the roll of chocolate chip cookies in half.
Cut the first half in thin slices and place at the bottom of the pan.
Pour the batter on top, then cut the second half in thin slices and place on top of the batter.
Place the pan in the oven at 350° for about 45 minutes. Let chill for 15 minutes.
Serve in squares.

title: turkey breast on the grill
directions: Remove turkey from bone.
Mix wine, soy sauce, salad oil, salt, pepper, garlic salt to make marinade.
Place turkey and marinade in bowl and refrigerate
4 to 6 hours or overnight.
Turn occasionally.
Cook on grill flesh side down first.
Turn every 10 to 15 minutes, basting with marinade.
Usually takes 1 to 1 1/4 hours. Test by cutting; pink color indicates it is not yet done. The skin will loosen and can be easily removed near the end of cooking.
Heat marinade and serve with turkey, if desired.

title: rolls
directions: Beat shortening into sugar and unbeaten egg whites.
Beat thoroughly, the mix this with yeast mixture.
Sift flour and salt; stir in gradually into yeast mixture.
Mix well.
Put in bowl to rise.
Do not knead.
Make in rolls about 1 hour before baking. Will keep several days in refrigerator.

title: mousecapades
directions: Cream together sugar and cream cheese until well blended. Stir in vanilla and salt.
Shape into tiny balls and roll in coconut or pecans.
Let set a few minutes before serving.

title: meatloaf
directions: Beat thoroughly.
Put into loaf pan.
Pour over all one 8 oz. can tomato sauce.
Bake one hour at 350°.
Serves six.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar; add egg yolks one at a time, then add flour and sour cream, starting with flour and ending with flour.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300° in a large tube pan.

title: ginger shrimp wrapped in snow peas
directions: Bring a large pot of water to boil.
Add shrimp; cook 1 to 2 minutes.
Drain and refresh with cold water.
Chill, peel and devein.
Mix olive oil, vinegar, mustard, ginger, salt, pepper and garlic.
Pour over shrimp; refrigerate for 24 hours.
Blanch snow peas; refresh in cold water.
Split peas and remove strings. Place 2 shrimp in each pea pod; secure with a toothpick.

title: yeast doughnuts
directions: Combine milk, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sift flour, add 4 cups to milk and sugar mixture; beat well.
Beat in the yeast, then shortening and eggs. Add remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Knead on floured surface.
Place in greased bowl, turn dough over.
Let rise until double.
Roll out dough 1/2-inch thick, cut out with biscuit cutter and work between hand until round.
Cut center out with small bottle mouth.
Cover and let rise until light, about 40 minutes.
Deep fry in vegetable shortening at 375°, until light brown; turn once.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Makes about 4 dozen doughnuts.

title: tasty casserole
directions: For a tasty, easy tuna casserole combine soup, 1 cup crushed potato chips, green peas, milk and tuna.
Mix well.
Place in well-greased casserole.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup crushed potato chips.
Bake 20 minutes at 325°.

title: cheese broccoli casserole
directions: Defrost broccoli.
Put in a casserole pan.
Add onion; saute in 1/2 cup butter.
Salt and sprinkle uncooked rice; spread soup, 1/2 cup water and 1/2 cup milk.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes (covered).
Uncover; stir together, then place cheese slices on top.
Put back in oven for a few minutes to melt cheese.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In saucepan, combine first 7 ingredients; simmer until vegetables are tender.
Add cooked beef, 3 ounces of the cheese and rice, stirring until cheese melts.

title: rice broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter to soften; mix all ingredients together thoroughly. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: breast of chicken fiesta
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and seasoning mix, stirring well. Dredge chicken in crumb mixture.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan sprayed with vegetable cooking spray.
Saute green onions in butter in a skillet until tender.
Stir in cream and remaining ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Crumble cooked hamburger meat in 13 x 9 pan. Cover with cream of chicken soup, spreading evenly. Salt and pepper to taste. Starting in corner of pan, lay tater tots across the top in lines that touch one another until entire top of casserole is covered. Cook in 350° oven for 30 minutes, then turn oven on broil 375° for 5 minutes to ensure that the tater tots are crispy.

title: garbanzo bean salad
directions: Mix package of garlic salad dressing as per instructions. Drain all the beans and add dressing.
Mix well.
Is best if allowed to marinate several hours before serving.

title: pineapple rice
directions: Blend pudding mix with pineapple and juice. Stir until blended. Add rest of ingredients.
Ready to eat or will store nicely.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Make pudding (use cooked pudding mix).
Add coconut; set aside. In saucepan, mix pineapple and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and cook 10 minutes more.
Set aside.
Make cake.
Remove from oven and immediately poke holes in cake.
Pour pineapple mixture over cake and then the pudding; let cool.
Cover with Cool Whip and nuts.

title: gingered carrots
directions: Fill a saucepan with water.
Add carrots. Bring to a boil. Cook 5 to 6 minutes until tender.
Drain and dry on paper towels. Return to saucepan.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill dough.
Roll into balls the size of large walnuts.
Place 3-inches apart and flatten with fork dipped in sugar.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375° until set but not hard.
Makes 3 dozen (2 1/2-inch) cookies.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar; stir in butter and vanilla.
Mix well. Add flour and chips; mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb sour cream coffee cake
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar, pecans, butter and cinnamon. Mix with fork until crumbly; set aside. Cream brown sugar, shortening and egg until light and fluffy. Combine flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture, alternating with sour cream, mixing well after each addition. Stir in rhubarb. Spoon into a well greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Sprinkle with sugar mixture on top. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: layered taco dip
directions: Mix sour cream and taco seasoning together.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch pan in order given and chill.
Serve with chips.

title: chopped apple bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar and oil.
Mix in egg whites and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into loaf pan sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake approximately 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken with bay leaf, celery, salt and onion.
Remove chicken from broth.
Break into small pieces.
Mix chicken, soup and sour cream.
Crumble Ritz crackers and mix with butter.
Put chicken mixture in casserole dish and top with Ritz cracker mix. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chippy dippy bars
directions: Melt margarine; mix with graham crackers and pat evenly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan. Combine chips, nuts and coconut and spread on top of graham cracker crust. Pour sweetened condensed milk over mixture and bake in 375° oven for 25 to 35 minutes. Cut into pieces while still warm. If you plan on freezing some so that you won't eat them all, I found that they are just as good frozen.

title: julekage
directions: In a saucepan scald milk; stir in sugar, butter, salt and cardamon.
In a large bowl dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in milk mixture, egg and half the flour; beat to mix well.
Stir in candied fruit, raisins and enough remaining flour to make dough stiff enough to knead.
Turn out dough on floured surface; cover dough with bowl and let rest 10 to 15 minutes.
Knead until smooth.
Place in greased bowl; let rise until double.
Punch down and divide in half.
Shape in ball.
Place in greased pie tin. Let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: raisin m-m-m-mumbes
directions: Put ingredients in saucepan and stir over low heat until thickened, about 5 minutes.
Cool.

title: orange pecans
directions: Combine sugar, cream of tartar and orange juice in a saucepan. Cook over low heat, stirring gently, until sugar dissolves. Cover orange mixture and cook over medium heat 2 to 3 minutes to wash down sugar crystals from sides of pan. Uncover and cook over medium heat to soft ball stage (240°).
Remove from heat and beat with a wooden spoon just until mixture begins to thicken.
Stir in pecans and orange rind.
Working rapidly, drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto wax paper; let cool.
Yields about 2 dozen.

title: cheese dip
directions: Microwave sausage on Medium-high for 7 minutes or until done. Drain grease.
Chop sausage into small pieces, then add cheese and salsa.
Microwave for 5 minutes.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: jellied cranberry salad
directions: Mash cranberry sauce with fork and heat to boiling point.
Add Jell-O and stir until dissolved.
Add cold water and salt.
Stir well.
Pour into a clear dish or mold and chill until partly thickened, 30 minutes.
Fold in remaining ingredients and chill until firm, 3 to 4 hours.

title: rye and rice muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients well.
Pour oil and water into dry ingredients together.
Mix quickly until smooth.
Makes 12 small muffins.
May use paper cups or lightly oiled muffin tin.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
May add 1/4 cup diced fruit for variety.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix together sugar and flour in a large bowl.
Mix and bring to a boil margarine, cocoa and water.
Pour over flour mixture. Mix well and add buttermilk, eggs, soda, cinnamon and vanilla. Mix and pour onto a cookie sheet with sides.
Bake 20 minutes. Start icing 10 minutes before cake is done.
Bake at 350°.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Mix oil, dill weed and dry Ranch dressing together and pour over crackers.
Stir occasionally and enjoy the next day.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli. Saute onion in butter. Add other ingredients. Mix well and put in casserole dish.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: cheese soup for microwave
directions: Combine carrots, onion and butter in 2-quart glass mixing bowl.
Microwave (High) uncovered, 6 to 7 minutes, or until carrots are just tender.
Blend in flour, mustard and bouillon; stir in milk.
Microwave (High) uncovered, 14 to 16 minutes, or until mixture boils, stirring several times during the last half of cooking time.
Crumble processed cheese and add to soup, along with Cheddar cheese.
Stir until blended.
Stir in wine or beer. Microwave (High) uncovered, 2 to 3 minutes, or until heated through.
Makes about 5 servings.

title: glazed raspberry-orange turkey
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a 9 x 9-inch or 11 x 7-inch shallow baking pan, place turkey breast roast.
Pour orange juice over turkey; sprinkle with sage, thyme, pepper, salt and orange peel. Bake, basting occasionally, for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Combine raspberries and sugar.
Place around turkey breast.
Continue baking for 10 to 15 minutes or until thermometer pops up.
Let stand 10 minutes before slicing.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: easy italian eggplant
directions: Slice eggplant into 1/3 to 1/2-inch thick slices (cut crosswise).
Dip slices in margarine and then bread crumbs. Sprinkle slices with oregano if desired.
Spoon spaghetti sauce on top of each slice.
Top eggplant with a slice of cheese.
Place eggplant in a 400° oven for about 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese is slightly brown.

title: delicious barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour over chicken, ribs, pork chops or your favorite meat.
(If you want only a cup, use 1/8 cup vinegar, 1/8 cup soy sauce, 1/4 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup catsup.)

title: corned beef
directions: Place in roasting pan at 350°. Baste frequently. Bake 2 to 3 hours.

title: flop cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 35 minutes at 325°.
Leave in pan.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Mix well and stuff into peppers.
Place in a deep baking dish, covered, and bake at 350° for about 1 to 1 1/2 hours (can do ahead).
Stuff your peppers and freeze until needed.

title: easy time squares
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add flour and lemon juice. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place cherries evenly on batter.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cut into squares.

title: tabouli(lebanon)
directions: All ingredients can be chopped very fine by hand, except for the parsley.
It could be chopped in a food processor.
Mix all vegetables together.
Just before serving, soak the cracked wheat (burgul) in a little water; add to vegetables and add salt, pepper, peppermint, lemon juice and olive oil.
Mix very well. Ready to eat!
Makes enough for 6 people.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Boil noodles and empty into a large bowl add diced cucumbers, tomatoes, bell pepper.
Mix well.
Pour Zesty Italian Dressing over it and let sit.
Can eat right away, however, "The longer it sits, the better it gets".

title: lazy man's lasagna
directions: In large Dutch oven, cook noodles as directed.
Drain; set aside.
In same pan, brown meat.
Remove from heat; stir in Ricotta and next 5 ingredients and half of sauce until well mixed. Add noodles and toss gently to coat well.
Spoon into 3-quart lasagna pan.
Pour remaining sauce over top and sprinkle with cheese over sauce.
Bake for 20 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.

title: microwave hot deli melt
directions: Spread insides of rolls with mayonnaise.
Layer the bottom half of each roll with the meat, sprouts, tomato slice, mushrooms, onion, green pepper and cheese.
Add top half of roll.
Place both sandwiches on a paper towel lined plate.
Microwave at 50% (Medium) for 3 1/2 to 6 1/2 minutes or until cheese is melted and bread is warm to the touch, rotating plate once during cooking time.

title: apple cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, cream together margarine and both sugars.
Beat in eggs and vanilla until blended.

title: apple stack cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together like biscuit dough. Divide dough into 6 parts. Roll thin or pour in pan and bake at 400° until brown. When cool, spread apple butter or applesauce between layers.

title: rice 'n chicken(good backpacking meal)
directions: At Camp:
Boil water.
Add dry ingredients and chicken. Simmer 5 minutes.

title: honey walnut drop cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, honey, sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients alternately with sour cream.
Stir in vanilla, nuts and coconut.
Drop by teaspoonful onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
If desired, top each cookie with walnuts or coconut.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Yields 7 dozen.

title: beans, beans, beans
directions: Drain all beans.
Brown bacon in skillet.
Remove with slotted spoon.
Saute onion in bacon drippings.
Combine all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 15 servings.

title: mom's chicken teriyaki
directions: Mix soy sauce, sugar, sherry, garlic and ginger.
Brush bottom of pan with oil.
Broil chicken in pan until golden.
There is no need to season it.
When chicken is golden, poke it with a kitchen fork and brush on teriyaki sauce.
Turn a few times, brushing with sauce.
Sprinkle with onion for garnish.

title: cheesy pita pizza appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly brush bread with dressing.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned. Top each pita with 2 slices cheese and desired pizza toppers. Drizzle with additional dressing.
Bake 1 to 2 minutes or until cheese begins to melt. Cut into quarters.

title: italian casserole
directions: Heat corn oil in large skillet.
