Add green pepper, onions, garlic and ground beef.
Cook over medium heat until lightly browned.
Remove from heat.
Add tomatoes, corn, tomato paste, salt, pepper, oregano and macaroni.
Mix well. Turn into 3-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour, shortening and salt together.
Then add egg, water and vinegar together to first mixture.

title: texas millionaires
directions: Put caramels and water in top of double boiler and melt. Add pecans,
stir
and
drop
on spoon onto waxed paper.
Chill until firm.
Melt
Hershey
bar
and paraffin;
dip the caramel patties in melted chocolate.
Place on waxed paper to cool.

title: frosty punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except ginger ale and sherbet.
Chill. Add ginger ale and sherbet just before serving.
Yields 1 1/2 gallons.

title: birch's beef stew
directions: Cut all ingredients into bite sized pieces.
Put into covered pot, holding mushrooms aside until last 1/2 hour of covered cooking.
Bake covered at 325° for 2 1/2 hours.
Stir occasionally during cooking.
Remove cover after 2 1/2 hours and continue cooking for 1/2 hour to brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: ella berger's mock chow mein
directions: Brown hamburger.
Mix all together, except chow mein noodles. Place in baking dish and bake, uncovered, for 1/2 hour at 350°. Reduce heat to 300° and sprinkle chow mein noodles on top.
Bake 1/2 hour longer.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve salt, sugar and yeast in warm water. Mix flour and baking powder. Cream the shortening; mix with yeast mixture. Add buttermilk, then stir in flour mixture, mixing well. Place in large bowl and cover. Put in refrigerator and use as needed. Makes 6 dozen biscuits. Roll out on floured surface; using a large biscuit cutter, cut out circles and fold over. Place on slightly greased cookie sheets and bake at 400° in oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Use graham cracker crumb crust and make in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Whip the cream.
Add marshmallows and pour on crust.
Chill an hour.
Mix gelatin, strawberries and water and pour on top of whipped cream mixture.
Chill.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: hamburger barbecue
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients and brown in a large skillet. Drain off fat.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes.
Stir frequently.
Fills about 12 hamburger buns.

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into 10 x 9 x 1 1/2-inch Pyrex dish.
Freeze.
Remove from freezer about 25 minutes before serving.
Cut into squares.

title: herman sourdough starter mix
directions: Stir together the milk, flour, sugar and dry yeast.
Place in large non-metallic container, loosely covered, in a warm place and let stand overnight.
The next day, stir and refrigerate, loosely covered.
Stir at least once a day.

title: chocolate cream cheese frosting
directions: Beat milk
into the cream cheese a tablespoon at a time. Gradually beat
in
most
of
the sugar, then the chocolate and vanilla.
Beat in enough sugar to make a good spreading consistency.
Frost any layer cake.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix and roll into a ball.
Keep in refrigerator at least one hour.
Roll out and cut in strips.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cook in a moderate 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix together sugar and flour, add to beaten eggs and pineapple.
Pour mixture into buttered casserole.
Melt butter or margarine in frying pan.
Cut bread in small cubes.
Stir in hot butter until brown.
Put on top of pineapple mixture.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes in moderate oven.

title: cashew pea salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and let set overnight.
Next day add remaining ingredients.
Just before serving add one package of salted cashew nuts.

title: tuna in a basket
directions: Scoop out centers of hard rolls.
Save centers for bread crumbs.
Mix next 6 ingredients with enough mayonnaise to hold together.
Fill hard rolls with tuna mixture.
Garnish top with pimentos.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix and bake at 375° until done.

title: coffee cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar in bowl with electric mixer.
Add eggs and coffee; mix until well blended.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until center almost set.
Cool on wire rack.
Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cut onion and green pepper into large slices or strips.
Saute both in butter or margarine over medium heat until tender.
Add stewed tomatoes and tomato paste.
Simmer over low heat for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add spices to taste.
Simmer for 5 more minutes. Drain and clean cooked shrimp and add to tomato mixture; just heat through.
Serve over cooked rice.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix together, cake mix, butter and 2 eggs; spread in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix together cream cheese, 3 eggs, vanilla and powdered sugar; spread on top of crust.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a saucepan.
Heat over low heat until cheese melts.
Do not boil.
Best served in a chafing dish to keep warm while serving.
Serve with crackers, potato chips, corn chips or whatever to your liking.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix instant pudding as directed. Add the Cool Whip. Blend well. In large square casserole dish, layer bananas, wafers and pudding mixture until almost topping the casserole dish.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Cook onion and celery in butter.
Make sauce with soups and cheese.
Add onion, celery, and broccoli to sauce.
Season to taste.
Add mixture to rice and pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Slowly add milk while stirring.
Add vanilla and lemon juice.
Spread over pie crust and add cherry pie filling.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Bring to a boil and reduce heat.
Add a little Karo syrup or lemon juice or cream of tartar (I prefer Karo syrup).
This keeps them from crystalizing.
Boil gently until juice is thick and syrupy, stirring to keep from sticking.
Put into sterilized jars and seal.
I prefer the smaller figs to the larger ones, and I only cook about a gallon at a time.

title: aunt leanne's easy beef stew
directions: Saute meat in soy sauce and garlic powder.
In big cooking pot, melt butter, 1 cup beef bouillon and 1/4 cup red wine. Bring to a boil.
Add flour with wire whisk, whisking until sauce is thickened.
Lower heat; add meat, carrots, potatoes, green beans and cinnamon stick.
Bring back to a boil; cover and simmer until veggies are done.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pickled beets
directions: Cook beets until tender or use sliced, canned beets.
Bring to a boil. Add salt, sugar, vinegar and water.
Pour hot mixture over beets. Seal.

title: steak and veggies
directions: Salt and pepper each steak if desired.
Tear off about 4 pieces of aluminum foil (big enough to wrap each steak and veggies). Start with layer of sliced onions, sliced or chunks or carrots (whichever you prefer); amount is up to you.
Slice potatoes as if for French fries.
Dot butter as desired.
Layer onions, carrots and potatoes, ending with steak.
Bake at 350° until done, about 1 hour.

title: chili soup
directions: Cook hamburger meat, onion, and gr. pepper until done. Put chili beans, ministroni, and tomatoes in large sauce pan, add hamburger mixture to this and simmer for 30 min. If too thick add beef broth or tomatoes.

title: cheese rolls
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk and cheese.
After mixing, drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Melt stick of butter in microwave in a bowl.
Add garlic salt (about a teaspoon or so). Brush rolls with mixture.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes. Remove from oven; brush with butter mixture again.
Great with lasagna.

title: chickey dickey
directions: Cover chicken with Saucy Susan and drained pineapple chunks; bake, uncovered, at 350° for an hour or until done.

title: summertime delight
directions: Combine 8 oz. Cool Whip with cream cheese, sugar and lemon juice.
Blend well.
Spoon into pie shell.
Add remaining Cool Whip.
Garnish with fresh fruit.
Chill for 2 hours before serving.

title: patty's peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine shortening, peanut butter, sugars, salt, vanilla and eggs; beat thoroughly.
Sift dry ingredients, flour, soda and baking powder together; add to shortening mixture and blend. Measure level tablespoons of dough on shortening coated cookie sheets; press with fork.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes. Makes 6 dozen.

title: fantasy chocolate fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in a heavy 2 1/2-quart saucepan.
Boil to a full rolling boil, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and immediately add chocolate chips.
Stir until they are melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cool at room temperature.
Cut into squares.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in butter.
Stir in flour and pepper; add milk and bring to a boil stirring constantly.
Reduce heat; add cheese and mayonnaise.
Stir until cheese melts. Combine ham, potatoes and sauce.
Pour into baking dish; bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: harvest round steak
directions: Cut steak into 6 portions.
Combine 3 tablespoons flour, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Dredge meat in seasoned flour.
Brown meat in grease.
Add cinnamon, onions and 1/2 cup water; cover tightly and bake in slow oven at 325° for 2 hours.
Add sweet potatoes in last hour.
Remove onions and add cinnamon sticks if used.
Add apples, cover and bake 15 to 20 minutes or until meat and apples are done.
Remove meat, yams and apples to serving platter.
Sprinkle apples with sugar, if desired.
Measure cooking liquid.
Add water to make 1 1/2 cups of liquid.
Blend 2 tablespoons of flour with 1/2 cup additional water.
Add to cooking liquid.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Season with 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Serve gravy with meat, yams and apples.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Add milk to soups; heat until warm.
In large roasting pan, greased with oil, add rice.
Pour soup mixture over rice.
Place chickens on top of rice mixture.
Take dry soup and sprinkle over chicken.
Cover pan with aluminum foil or lid.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Dissolve jello in hot water. Add ginger ale and juice; chill until slightly thick.
Fold in pineapple.
Pour into an 8-inch square pan or mold.
Chill until firm.
Serves 9.

title: fruit dip
directions: Cook sugar, eggs, pineapple juice, orange juice, flour and lemon juice until thick.
Chill.
Add Cool Whip.

title: lemon supreme cake
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Gradually beat in oil until creamy. Add nectar and cake mix; beat 2 minutes.
Pour into tube pan. Bake at 325° for one hour, or until wooden pick inserted comes out clean.

title: anthony's special secret cheese sauce
directions: Combine mushroom soup and cheese in a double boiler and melt over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Add pepper and Tabasco sauce.
Remove from heat and pour into bowl. This dish may be used as a cheese sauce with enchiladas, tacos or as a nacho dip.
The tomatoes may be added as an option for a different, more colorful flavor.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Bake cake in sheet pan as directed and cool.
Prepare pudding mix with 3 1/2 cups milk and 1/2 cup Kahlua.
Set aside.
Crush candy bars; set aside.
Cut 1/3 cake into bite-size pieces.
Place in large glass or crystal bowl.
Pour 1/3 pudding mixture over cake.
Spread 1/3 of Cool Whip over pudding, then 1/3 of candy over Cool Whip.
Continue layering.
Chill several hours, then serve.

title: cherry crepes
directions: Mix flour, milk, salt and eggs until well mixed.
Batter will be thin.
Cook crepes in small amount of butter in hot pan.
Swirl pan to make crepe thin.
As crepes are done, put 1 to 2 tablespoons cherry pie filling in center and roll up.
Top with sour cream or whipped cream and sprinkle with a little powdered sugar.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Roll in balls about the size of walnuts.
Place on buttered platter.
When ready to bake, place on greased tins; flatten with fork and bake.

title: dolce de la namorati*("sweetheart cookies")
directions: Beat eggs, evaporated milk, orange juice and rind, and oil of anise until foamy.
Sift together flour, sugar, powdered sugar and baking powder.
Cut in shortening and margarine.

title: artichoke pickles
directions: Cook ingredients for 10 minutes.
Add artichokes and seal into hot jars.

title: tex-mex meat loaf
directions: Combine all but chili sauce and cheese.
Spread in ungreased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake one hour, covered.
Spoon chili sauce over cooked loaf and cover with cheese.
Bake an additional 15 minutes in 350° oven.

title: company chicken
directions: Roll each chicken breast in lunch meat; wrap with bacon slice. Arrange in baking dish.
Combine mushroom soup with sour cream; pour over chicken breasts.
Bake, covered, at 275° for 2 1/2 hours.
Uncover, top with sliced almonds; bake 30 minutes more.

title: mimi's meatballs
directions: 1. Mix the ingredients together in a bowl.
Mimi suggests using your hands (washed of course!) to really do a good job.

title: cookies n candy kisses
directions: Combine all ingredients except candy kisses.
Mix on low speed with mixer until dough forms.
Shape dough into balls.
Place balls on ungreased sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Put candy kisses on cookies while hot and they will sink slightly into cookie.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Combine and fill fresh mushroom caps.
Place on baking sheet and broil until bubbly, about 3 minutes.

title: best brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and stir.
Add flour, cocoa and vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Add pecans if desired.

title: pound cake
directions: Add sugar, margarine, eggs and vanilla together.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Add milk, flour, baking powder and salt to first mixture. Beat 2 additional minutes.
Grease and flour pan.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in 3 layers at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Add ingredients together and refrigerate.
Break bacon into small pieces.

title: jiffy rolls
directions: Mix cake mix and yeast together.
Dissolve salt in warm water. Add water to cake mix.
Add flour, mix well.
Put in greased bowl.
Cover and let rise for 1 hour.
Shape into rolls.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix noodles and vegetables together.
Mix together the oil, vinegar, sugar, garlic salt, pepper, parsley and mustard.
Mix noodles and vegetables with marinade.
Marinate for 7 hours or overnight in the refrigerator.

title: fruit dip (i)
directions: Mix until you have a nice consistency.
Good dip for melon and strawberries.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and milk.
Melt margarine and add with egg mixture.
Then add coconut and vanilla.
Mix and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until done or golden brown.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Brown garlic in 4 tablespoons oil.
Remove garlic.
Then add lightly floured chicken and saute on each side until lightly browned.
Remove to baking dish.
Add mushrooms to oil, adding a little more oil, if necessary.
Saute mushrooms, stirring constantly, for a few minutes.
Then add Marsala wine, stir together for a minute or two and then pour over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: carl's chili
directions: Brown onion, green pepper and garlic in butter.
Brown meat and drain off fat, then add other ingredients and bring to a boil. Simmer for 2 hours.

title: spareribs
directions: Place all ingredients in a large skillet.
Cover and simmer for 40 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: pizza
directions: Mix together in large bowl the yeast and warm water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add flour and salt to yeast mixture.
Knead dough with hands about 15 times.
Let rise in a warm place for 5 minutes.
Spread dough on oiled cookie sheet or pizza sheet.
Bake at 425° for 5 minutes.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and margarine and press in bottom of greased 9 x 12-inch pan. Mix cream cheese, sugar and 2 to 3 eggs. Pour over mixture. Bake at 300° until brown, about 1 hour. Cool and cut in squares.

title: sesame waffles(healthful eating)
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, instant nonfat milk, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In a small mixing bowl, combine eggs, olive oil and water.
Make a well in the flour mixture; add egg mixture and blend.
Fold in sesame seed and vanilla extract.
Pour 2/3 cup of mix into waffle iron and bake 3 minutes.

title: hamburger dinner
directions: Fry bacon; cool and crumble for topping.
Brown meat until it changes color.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with crumbled bacon.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: kids clay (not edible)(microwave)
directions: Combine flour, salt and cream of tartar in 2-quart bowl. Gradually stir in water and oil until just about smooth. Microwave (High) uncovered 4 1/2 to 5 minutes or until mixture is very thick, stirring every minute (mixture will be very lumpy). Cool enough to handle.
Turn onto countertop and knead until smooth, about 2 minutes.
Divide dough into 4 sections and knead in food coloring.
Store each color separately in airtight container in refrigerator.
Makes 4 balls.
Zipper top bags make handy storage containers.

title: shortbread
directions: Cream butter until almost white (about 10 minutes).
Blend in sugar and beat vigorously.
Stir in salt and flour in 4 parts, working into dough thoroughly.
Add vanilla.
Roll out dough or press into 9-inch square pan, cutting into squares.
Prick each piece with fork tines.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Dough should turn golden, but not brown at all during baking.
If baked in square pan, cut cookies again after baking and separate.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: taco bake
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain grease. In bowl mix beef, tomato paste and taco seasoning.
Spread evenly over baking pan.
Spread corn over beef mixture.
Add layer of cheese.
Pour Bisquick mixture and milk together.
Mix. Then pour over Cheddar cheese evenly.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes or until Bisquick mixture is done.
Serve with tomatoes, lettuce and sour cream.

title: mexican pie
directions: Mix corn meal, milk, cream-style corn and bacon drippings; set aside.
Brown the ground beef and drain.
Place 1/2 meal mixture in a cast-iron skillet.
Next place meat, chopped onion, cheese and green chiles.
Top with rest of corn meal mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Slice like pie when serving.
Top with sour cream, guacamole, hot sauce and black olives (things you like on Mexican food).

title: buffalo wings
directions: Cut chicken wings into three pieces, discarding tops.
Roll chicken in flour, salt, pepper, and garlic powder.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain.
Combine margarine, hot sauce, vinegar, and ketchup in pan.
Heat slowly.
Put chicken in large bowl with tight fitting lid.
Pour sauce over chicken and shake well.

title: cheesy chicken rolls
directions: In a 11 x 6-inch or 8-inch glass cake pan combine soup, milk and 1/2 of grated cheese.
Put into microwave and cook on High for 3 to 5 minutes (until cheese is melted).
While cooking, combine cubed chicken and 1/2 of remaining cheese (reserve about 1/4 cup for on top) and set aside.
Open crescents and separate into 8 triangles.
Put 1 large tablespoon of chicken mixture on the large end of triangle and roll up edges until sealed.
(I use an ice cream scoop and pack into a ball before I roll crescents up.) Place stuffed crescent rolls into your pan with prepared soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Remove and sprinkle remaining cheese on top and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: hodge podge
directions: Brown meat, onions and celery; saute until lightly wilted. Add other ingredients.
Cook in slow cooker or crock-pot several hours.

title: taco seasoning mix
directions: Combine ingredients.
This is equivalent to a 1 1/4-ounce package of taco seasoning.
May be made ahead in bulk and stored in tightly sealed container.
For longer storage, put in freezer. Three scant tablespoons of bulk mix equals one package.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add combined applesauce, soda and vanilla.
Do not be concerned if mixture separates.
It will blend as ingredients are added.
Add sifted flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well and turn into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: colonial easy cookies
directions: Cream
sugar and margarine well.
Sift flour with soda. On medium
speed, mix flour, oatmeal and flavoring with sugar mixture.
Mold
dough
into
small
balls
and
place
on
an ungreased
cookie
sheet.
On each cookie, press a pecan piece (1/4) after dipping into a slightly beaten egg white.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until slightly browned.
Yields 5 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: country captain chicken
directions: Shake breasts in flour mixture.
Brown in shortening.
Remove from pan.
Keep warm.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: In separate bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar, egg and flour until well blended.
Spoon mixture over brownie batter.
Swirl with knife to marbleize.

title: chicken divan
directions: Brown the chicken in the oil until cooked; about 5 minutes. Add the broccoli, broth and soup.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice, cover and remove from heat.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Top with Parmesan cheese.

title: black walnut cookies
directions: Cream butter and vanilla until softened.
Gradually add brown sugar, creaming until fluffy after each addition.
Add eggs in thirds, beating well after each addition.
Mix in walnuts.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix in order named.
Form in balls the size of walnut and bake 1-inch apart at 350°.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine shortening, peanut butter and sugar.
Add honey and egg.
Mix well. Add flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Mix well.
Roll into balls about the size of marbles.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet about 2-inches apart. Flatten with fork dipped in flour.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: a good layer cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add 1/2 of plain flour.
Add eggs, then rest of plain flour.
Add milk, self-rising flour and vanilla.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) layer pans or a long flat pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Add caraway seed and raisins.
Mix.
In small bowl, mix margarine, eggs and buttermilk. Add to dry
mixture; mix by hand.
Pour into well-greased loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.
Test by inserting knife.
When knife is dry, it's ready.

title: hot spiced tea(party size recipe)
directions: Mix and heat (simmer, don't boil).
Recipe makes approximately 2 gallons.
Can be stored in the refrigerator for up to 2 weeks. Best when served hot.

title: fruit punch drink
directions: Blend in blender.
Each serving contains 55 calories.

title: vegetable chowder
directions: Saute beef and onion in margarine until brown.
Add water, tomatoes, celery, salt, bouillon, bay leaf, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add vegetables, noodles and thyme.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: burger-mac casserole
directions: Brown meat lightly, add onions and seasoning.
Saute.
Add macaroni, sauce, corn and peas.
Toss together lightly, add olives. Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Remove and sprinkle with grated cheese to cover.
Bake 15 minutes.
Serves 25.

title: easy cherry dessert
directions: Mix pie filling, Cool Whip, marshmallows and nuts.
Pour into pie shell and chill 2 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: goofey bars
directions: Mix together cake mix, melted butter and 1 egg.
Spread in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts over top.
Mix together the cream cheese, sugar and 2 eggs.
Spread over top of nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cream the cheese and mayonnaise. Add garlic powder, turkey or chicken pieces and 1/2 cup pecans.
Mix well. Let chill overnight. Roll in chopped nuts and/or parsley. Serve with your favorite cracker.

title: blueberry cream muffins
directions: In large bowl sift flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Then add blueberries and toss gently.
Combine eggs, sour cream oil and vanilla.
Mix well and stir into dry ingredients just until moistened.
Fill cupcake papers or muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: lemonade cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Sift flour and soda and add alternately with 1/2 cup lemonade.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake in 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Brush hot cookies slightly with lemonade and sprinkle with sugar.

title: no fail pie crust(makes 2 double crust pies.)
directions: Mix flour and shortening. Mix water, egg and vinegar in cup, then add to flour mixture. To that add the sugar and salt. Divide into 4 balls and roll out each crust.

title: bonbons
directions: Mix the milk, butter and vanilla together.
Add the powdered sugar and coconut.
Add pecans until the mixture is hard to stir. Shape into small balls.
Place on a cookie sheet sprayed with Pam. Put into freezer for about 30 minutes.
Put toothpicks in each ball and dip in melted chocolate bark.
Place on wax paper. Remove toothpicks and seal the holes with some of the chocolate.

title: fat-free chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray a 9-inch square pan with nonstick cooking spray.
In a large bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Mix well.
In another bowl, whisk egg whites, water and corn syrup. Stir into dry ingredients until smooth.
Pour into pan. Bake 30 minutes or when cake springs back when touched. Cool on rack 10 minutes.
Contains 0 fat, 140 mg. sodium, 0 cholesterol, 130 calories per serving and 31 gr. carbohydrates.
Serves 16.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil and pumpkin.
Add the flour, cloves and cinnamon (sifted together) to the sugar, oil and pumpkin mix.
Add the vanilla to the whole mixture. Put this in five 1-pound coffee cans, not greased.
Fill cans half full.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Let cans cool completely, then remove.

title: taco soup(by daisy smithson)
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Put all ingredients in extra large pot.
Makes 6 quarts.
Simmer an hour or more.

title: sweet hot mustard
directions: Put mustard and vinegar in a good size stainless steel bowl and mix well.
Soak for 3 to 4 hours.
Next, add sugar or honey and mix very well. Add eggs that have been beaten very well to mustard mixture pouring it through a strainer.
Mix all ingredients very well and cook either in a double boiler or in the stainless steel pan in boiling water for 15 minutes until mixture thickens like pudding.
Pour in 1/2 pint jars and process in boiling water bath for 5 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all in casserole bowl and bake 1 hour in a 400° oven.

title: good fried chicken
directions: Let chicken sit overnight after salting and peppering (with both salts).
Cover.
Dip in buttermilk.
Roll in flour.
Fry until brown about 30 minutes in vegetable oil.

title: sour cream apple-pecan squares
directions: Combine flour and brown sugar; cut in butter with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Press 2 3/4 cups mixture into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add sour cream, egg, soda, cinnamon and vanilla to crumb mixture in bowl; beat well. Fold in pecans and apples.
Pour over crust in pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until filling is set.
Cool.
Cut into 2-inch squares.

title: warm bacon cheese spread
directions: Cut the top fourth off the loaf of bread, hollow out the bottom, leaving a 1 inch shell. Cut the removed bread and the top of loaf into cubes; set aside. In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese. Add the sour cream, cheddar cheese and worcestershire sauce until well mixed; stir in bacon and onions. Spoon into bread shell. Wrap in a piece of heavy duty foil. Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour. Serve with reserved bread cubes, crackers or tortilla chips.

title: squash pie
directions: Mix honey, salt and flour; set aside.
Mix milk, eggs and lemon; stir until blended.
Put squash into blender, then add to milk mixture, then add to honey mixture.
Pour into two unbaked pie crusts.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in a 400° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate torte
directions: Several hours before serving, preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, combine flour, butter and nuts.
Press mixture into bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake crust for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: mama's chocolate pie
directions: Cook mixture until it bubbles; pour into baked pie shells.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Add chopped broccoli and water.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add cream of chicken soup, Cheez Whiz, and milk. Blend well.
Then add the Minute rice.
Pour into casserole and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pork chop bake
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Season the chops and brown.
Lay flat in your pan.
On top of each chop, lay a slice of tomato, a slice of onion and a slice of green pepper.
Pour your cooked rice all around the edges.
Mix your water with the bouillon and then pour over the rice.
Cover with foil and cook 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: baked chicken
directions: Coat chicken with seasoned flour and brown quickly in a little shortening.
Put in baking dish.
Thin soup with milk and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, depending on size of chicken.
If more gravy is desired, add more soup.
Serves 6.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Unroll crescent rolls and place in a greased 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Bake as directed.
In a bowl, combine Hidden Valley Ranch dressing, Miracle Whip and softened cream cheese.
Mix well with blender until smooth.
Spread filling over cooled crescent roll crust.
Add desired chopped vegetables.
Top with shredded cheese. Refrigerate 12 to 24 hours or overnight.

title: chili cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Spray a small casserole dish with vegetable oil spray, 7 to 8 inches square or round. Line the pan with 1/2 inch layer potatoes. Beat eggs. Add dry ingredients and beat well. Blend in remaining ingredients. Batter will be lumpy. Pour in dish and bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Blend together and bake at 400° for 30 minutes in a greased 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.

title: mulled cider (hot) cider punch
directions: Bring to boil.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Can be made ahead.
Then reheat and serve warm.

title: pepper cheese
directions: Butter a 9 x 10-inch pan.
Cover bottom of pan with jalapeno peppers.
Cover top of peppers with Cheddar cheese.
Top with Colby cheese.
Beat eggs and add milk.
Pour over top of cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool slightly and cut into squares.
Serve with Triscuits or crackers of choice.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in fourths.
Dip in butter and cover with cinnamon and sugar.
Place in Bundt cake pan, stacking until pan is 3/4 of the way full. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: easy english trifle
directions: Stir almond extract into Cool Whip.
Line bottom of 3-quart trifle dish or glass bowl with pound cake which has been cut into small pieces.
Alternate layers of cake, strawberries, pudding, Cool Whip and almonds, ending with Cool Whip.
Garnish with almonds and whole strawberries.
Chill at least 8 hours.
Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: blueberry crisp
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cinnamon and ginger in a small bowl. Place margarine in a 9-inch glass pie plate.
Microwave on High for 30 seconds or until melted.
Add margarine to dry ingredients. Blend thoroughly.
Place blueberries in same pie plate.
Sprinkle lemon juice over top.
Sprinkle crumb mix over top of berries. Rotating dish midway through cooking, microwave on High for 4 to 5 minutes.
Let stand a few minutes before serving.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Pour all of the ingredients in blender and mix well.
Grease and flour pie plate.
Pour in plate and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until brown.

title: brownie pie
directions: In mixer bowl, combine eggs, sugar, butter, flour, cocoa, vanilla and salt.
Beat with electric mixer for 4 minutes.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Spoon into buttered pie pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Pie settles like meringue as it cools.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: lemon drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Add dry ingredients gradually.
Mix well.
Drop on baking sheet; flatten with fork.
Bake at 375°.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in regular pie crust.
Bake at 325° for approximately 50 minutes.

title: baked macaroni and cheese au vin
directions: Grease casserole with olive oil, including sides and bottom. This casserole is made in layers.
Start with macaroni, add cheeses, another layer of macaroni, and top with cheeses until casserole is full.
Combine eggs, wine, Worcestershire sauce, hot sauce, and salt.
Pour egg mixture over layered casserole and add water, if necessary, to barely cover.
Bake in 350 degree oven until top layer of cheese is golden brown.
Serves 8.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt margarine.
Add brown sugar to melted margarine; mix well.
Add slightly beaten eggs, vanilla and dry ingredients.
Add nuts and chips.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: irish cream liquor
directions: Put milk and eggs into blender; process for a minute.
Add chocolate syrup; fill milk can with vodka or rum and add to blender.
(A little more may be added for desired taste.) Process until well blended.
Store liquor in refrigerator for up to 1 month.
Makes 1 fifth.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients until crumbly.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Combine pumpkin, milk, eggs, sugar and spices.
Beat well.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Combine pecans, brown sugar and butter; sprinkle over filling.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until set.

title: rice pudding
directions: Put rice and milk in a large pan with lid. Spray the pan with cooking spray. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Remove from oven and add the rest of the ingredients and mix well. Pour into a pretty bowl and cover tightly with aluminum foil. This keeps the heat in to cook the egg. When ready to serve, sprinkle the top with some cinnamon and sugar.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake in greased casserole dish at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: hot butter rum
directions: Mix well all ingredients and freeze.
Add 1 to 2 teaspoons of mix to 1 cup boiling water and 1 jigger (1 ounce) of Myers dark rum.

title: fancy apple dessert
directions: Pour apple pie filling in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Sprinkle dry cake mix on top of apples.
Top with pecans and coconut.
Drizzle melted butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: carrot souffl
directions: Add margarine to carrots. Add flour, baking powder, sugar, salt and cinnamon. Add eggs and milk. Mix well and pour into 9 x 13-inch dish. Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: hallie's hens
directions: Split hens down middle.
Brown rice only 15 minutes in large Pyrex dish at 375°.
In separate bowl, mix water, package of seasoning from Rice-A-Roni and chicken soup.
After rice browns, lower oven to 350°; put hens over top of rice (will sizzle).
Pour mixture over hens; cover and cook 1 hour.
Uncover 30 minutes to brown.
Excellent side dish with this:
cut up fresh apples with poppy seed dressing.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together, then drop by rounded teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken; save 2 3/4 cups broth.
Add salt, carrots, peas, potatoes, celery, onion, pepper and poultry seasoning to broth. Cook 20 minutes.
Combine milk and flour with vegetable mixture. Simmer until thick.
Add chopped chicken and pour into casserole dish.
Top with refrigerated biscuits and bake for 25 minutes at 400°.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain all the beans.
Mix and pour the following over the beans:

title: sesame almond chicken
directions: *One-half teaspoon each dried parsley flakes, thyme leaves and 1 crushed bay leaf can be substituted for bouquet garni.

title: fruit cocktail drink
directions: Squeeze orange and lime juice into tumbler; add sparkling water.
Mix well.
Serves 1.

title: persimmon pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add other ingredients and pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes or until center is barely set.

title: savannah oysters
directions: Butter shallow casserole dish.
Layer 1/3 of crackers. Carefully place half of oysters on top of crackers and half of celery.
Add salt and pepper.
Place another layer of crackers, rest of oysters and celery.
Top with crackers.
Just before baking, add cream.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini brownies
directions: Ice with chocolate frosting.

title: graham cracker pralines
directions: Melt butter; add sugar.
Stir until smooth.
Add nuts. Arrange graham crackers on foil or cookie sheet; pour syrup over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool completely.
Break apart.
Store in covered tin in refrigerator or freezer.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together until smooth.
Pour into unbaked crust and bake for 35 minutes.

title: okra fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients, except the okra.
Stir in okra last.
In a deep, black skillet pour enough oil to make about 2 inches. Drop mixture by tablespoonfuls into hot oil and cook until golden brown.
Serve immediately.
Makes a bunch!

title: cabbage soup
directions: Place all ingredients in soup pot except rice and cover with water.
Cook until meat and cabbage are tender.
Add rice if desired.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together. Roll in 1 package dried beef, chopped.

title: grandma karas' pork roast and spaghetti
directions: Pork Roast Preparation:
Stuff roast with minced garlic.
Rub roast with olive oil, salt and pepper.
Place roast, fat side up, in a rack in a shallow pan.
Roast, uncovered, in a 325° oven for 40 minutes per pound, until done.
Approximately 1/2 into cooking time, place 1/2 cup of water into bottom of roasting pan.
When done, remove roast to carving board using two metal spatulas.
Do not use forks since they will cause some of the juices to be lost. Let the roast stand about 15 minutes before carving.
Reserve juices in bottom of roasting pan.

title: macaroni and cheese with corn
directions: Make macaroni and cheese mix as directed on box.
Add the milk and corn.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir soup, milk, soy sauce, pepper and optional seasonings until smooth.
Mix in beans and 1/2 can onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot.
Stir.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake 5 minutes more.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: butterfinger ice cream
directions: Mix together.
Pour into freezer can and freeze until firm.

title: cheese and clam dip
directions: Drain clams and add the cheese and lemon juice. If stronger clam taste is desired, add more clam juice to taste. Add enough good mayonnaise to form the desired consistency. Serve cold with potato chips or Fritos or tortilla chips. Yields about 1 pint.

title: muffins(light recipe)
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Combine corn oil and egg white; beat with rotary beater until thoroughly mixed.
Stir in milk.

title: cake pie dessert
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Line pan with pie filling.
Sprinkle cake mix on top of filling.
Sprinkle on almonds.
Pour melted butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour filling into shell and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: popcorn candy
directions: Microwave popcorn according to package instructions. Carefully weed out unpopped kernels.
Add peanuts and Rice Krispies to popcorn.
Melt white chocolate and peanut butter.
Add to popcorn mixture and stir until mixed well.
Lay on wax paper to cool.
When cooled, place in airtight container.
Enjoy!

title: norweigian butter cookies
directions: Melt butter. Add egg and sugar, beating until smooth.
Add vanilla. Add dry ingredients. Roll into 1/2-inch balls.
Bake on greased cookie sheet for 16 to 18 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: brownies
directions: Mix cocoa, shortening, sugar and all other ingredients except pecans.
Mix. Then add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: amaretto cake
directions: Heat in saucepan the oleo, sugar and Amaretto.
Drizzle on cake and bake 5 minutes more.
Cool cake for 15 minutes.
Invert on cake plate.
When cool, lightly cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Serve at room temperature with whipped topping or whipped cream.
Sprinkle with lots of coconut or chopped nuts.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, then flour, soda and vanilla.
Make into a ball and flatten with a glass.
Bake at 350°.
(Best to refrigerate overnight, then bake.)

title: sfingi with ricotta
directions: In a large bowl, mix eggs sugar and Ricotta cheese until smooth and creamy.
Add vanilla and mix in flour, salt and baking powder.
Blend until flour is moist.
If batter is dry, add a little milk.
Drop by teaspoon into hot oil until golden.
You will find that the puffs, when they are done on the bottom, will turn themselves.
Otherwise, you can turn them.
Drain on brown paper bags to absorb oil.
Place in serving dish and add a sprinkle of granulated sugar.
This is a great dessert or snack to make in a hurry when you want something fast.
They are a perfect accompaniment to coffee.

title: taco casserole
directions: Prepare meat and taco seasoning as directed on package and set aside.
Grease 9 x 9-inch glass dish and completely cover bottom with tortilla chips.
Bake at 300° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven, spread meat on top and bake 10 more minutes.
Remove, add shredded lettuce and cut up tomatoes.
Bake 10 minutes; remove from oven and sprinkle with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake until cheese melts; serve with sour cream and taco sauce.

title: quick, low fat delicious dessert
directions: Thaw some frozen fruit (no sugar added) like strawberries, blueberries, raspberries, etc.
Sweeten with Splenda.
Layer in parfait glass with Lite Cool Whip.
Yum!

title: giblet gravy
directions: On low heat, place cooked turkey or chicken giblets and eggs in 1 pint of broth.
Combine flour with 3/4 cup broth.
Add. Pour milk into mixture and salt and pepper to taste.
Stir constantly until gravy is thick and smooth, about 8 minutes.

title: cheesy sausage quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Fry sausage; reserve 2 tablespoons of fat.
Saute onion and pepper in fat for 2 to 3 minutes.
Slice sausage.
Combine cheese and flour.
Stir in sausage slices, green pepper and onion.
Spread in pie crust shell.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour into shell.
Bake on cookie sheet for 35 to 40 minutes or until browned and filling is set.
Serves 6.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift and thoroughly mix flour, salt, baking powder, sugar, cinnamon, cloves.
Add eggs, oleo and vanilla and mix well. Dissolve the baking soda in applesauce and mix well and add to above.
Add pecans and raisins (rubbed lightly with flour, so not sink to bottom) mix it all well and pour into a greased and floured tube pan and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Cream together butter and cream cheese.
Add powdered sugar, 1/2 cup at a time.
Beat well.
Add vanilla.
Frost.

title: louisiana pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly, then add rest of the ingredients.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Allow to cool before cutting.

title: easy pastry crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and oleo until consistency of meal.
Add cold milk.
Mix until it forms a ball.
Freezes well.

title: lemon-dill chicken
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet over medium heat.
Add mushrooms and next 5 ingredients; bring to a boil.
Add chicken in a single layer and return to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes or until tender, turning once.
Serve over rice.

title: beef and vegetable chili
directions: Cook beef in large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat until no longer pink.
Drain fat.
Stir in onion, chili powder, garlic, cumin and salt.
Cook, stirring, until onion gets soft.
Stir in remaining ingredients.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Grate Cheddar cheese and slice velveeta cheese. Drain most of the juice from tomatoes.

title: fruit bread puddings
directions: Combine bread cubes, milk, sugar, eggs, salt, vanilla, dates, walnuts and melted butter.
Pour into a greased 9 x 14 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with whipped cream.
Yield: 23 servings.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Make a sauce, combining tomatoes, tomato paste, oil, garlic, onion, salt and pepper.
Cook slow for 1/2 hour.

title: cream cheese pies
directions: Mix Dream Whip as directed on package.
Add sugar and cream cheese; beat until smooth.
Put in cooled pie shell.
Chill about 1 hour.
Top with pie filling and chill.

title: dill crunch sticks
directions: Mix together in a shallow pan.
Cut canned biscuits in half. Roll each half into pencil-thin stick, about 4-inches long.
Brush with milk.
Roll sticks in mixture.
Bake on greased baking sheet at 450° for 5 minutes or until golden brown.
These can be frozen, defrosted and baked.
If possible, serve these hot.

title: old fashioned strawberry preserves
directions: Scald berries in boiling water 2 minutes; drain.
Add 4 cups sugar and boil (rolling boil for 2 minutes).
Take off stove and slowly add 2 more cups of sugar.
Cook at rolling boil 5 minutes more.
Cool and pour in jars.
Seal with paraffin.

title: zucchini crescent pie
directions: Cook and stir for 10 minutes zucchini, onions and margarine. Stir in fresh parsley or parsley flakes, salt, pepper, oregano, garlic powder and basil.
Combine eggs and Mozzarella cheese or Muenster.
Stir into mixture.
Line an ungreased 10-inch pie pan with crescent dough to make the crust.
Spread with prepared mustard.
Pour zucchini mixture over dough.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Cover crust with foil the last 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix well and store in refrigerator.
Will keep approximately two weeks.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Have a 13 x 9-inch baking dish ready.
In a bowl mix Ricotta cheese, Parmesan, eggs, salt and pepper until blended.
Spread 1/4 cup spaghetti sauce in bottom of baking dish. Cover with a layer of cooked lasagna noodles.
Spread 1/2 the Ricotta mixture over noodles, then half the spinach and shredded Mozzarella and half the remaining sauce.
Continue to layer as directed.
Top with remaining noodles and sauce.
Sprinkle reserved Parmesan and Mozzarella cheese.
Cover and bake 30 minutes, then uncover and bake 20 minutes or until bubbly around edges.
Serves 6.

title: roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large plastic bowl, mix all ingredients; toss until potatoes are coated evenly.
Empty into a shallow baking dish or roasting pan.
Bake, stirring occasionally, 40 minutes or until tender and golden brown.

title: broccoli soup(hot or cold)
directions: In a 1-quart saucepan, combine 1 1/4 cups of the stock with the currants, cumin, turmeric and red pepper.
Bring to a boil. Stir in the couscous.
Remove from the heat.
Cover the pan and let stand for 10 minutes or until all the liquid has been absorbed.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Cream together shortening and sugar. Add eggs and beat well.
Sift together dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture, alternating with bananas, blending well after each addition.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into well greased pan.

title: mrs. horsman's pie!
directions: Mix pudding, pineapple and Cool Whip.
Put mix in pie crust. Chill for an hour and serve!
Awesome fast pie.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in greased pan or dish.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over apples.
Add topping.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Let first two ingredients stand overnight.
Rinse and drain. Bring remaining ingredients to boil in large kettle.
Simmer, uncovered for 30 minutes.
Pour into hot sterilized jars and seal. Makes about 7 pints.

title: jamaican meat pies
directions: To make the filling, heat the oil in a large skillet.
Add the onion, bell pepper and garlic.
Saute until the onion is translucent, but not browned, about 5 minutes.
Add the ground meat and saute until browned, breaking it into small pieces with your spatula.
Add the tomato sauce, tomato puree and hot pepper sauce; simmer 10 minutes.
Add the curry powder to the potatoes and stir the potatoes into the sauce to thicken it.
Add salt and pepper.
Taste the sauce and correct seasonings.
Cool.
If working ahead, cover and refrigerate filling.

title: four chip muffins(makes 12)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 12 muffin cups.

In a large bowl, stir together flour, brown sugar, baking powder and salt. In another bowl, stir together milk, butter, eggs and vanilla until blended. Make a well in center of dry ingredients; add milk mixture and stir just to combine.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Spoon batter into prepared muffin cups.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until a cake tester inserted in center of one muffin comes out clean. Remove muffin tin to wire rack; cool 5 minutes before removing from muffin tin.
Serve warm or cool completely.
They freeze well.

title: swedish pancakes
directions: Mix in order given.
Cook on hot griddle.

title: hot caramel sauce
directions: Mix and bring to boil except vanilla.
Cook until thick.
Add vanilla.
Store in refrigerator.
Warm to serve.

title: italian roast beef
directions: Place rump roast in a roasting pan.
Add all other ingredients to pan and mix around roast.
Cover and place in a 350 degree oven until medium doneness.
Remove roast from pan.
Next slice roast paper thin with a meat slicer or shred.
Then return to the roaster and stir together with broth and other ingredients.
Add water in needed to keep meat submerged in juices.
Continue to roast until tender and falling apart.
May serve as is, but it is best as a sandwich on hard rolls.

title: fresh vegetable pizza
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 4 long rectangles. Place rectangles crosswise in ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Press over bottom and 1 inch up sides to form crust.
Seal perforations.
Bake at 375° for 14 to 19 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.
In small bowl combine horseradish, salt and pepper; blend until smooth.
Spread evenly over cooled crust. Top with remaining ingredients.
Cut into small squares. Refrigerate.

title: parmesan chicken breasts
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Dredge the chicken breast in 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese, patting the cheese into the flesh.
Dredge them in flour, lightly shaking off the excess.

title: jello delight
directions: Empty all of the ingredients in a large bowl and stir together.
Enjoy!

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugars and margarine; add vanilla, bananas and eggs. Next, add baking soda, then flour and finally nuts.
Bake at 300° for approximately 1 hour in greased and floured pans.

title: mock sour cream dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of an electric blender. Cover and process until smooth and creamy.
Transfer mixture to a serving container.
Cover and refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.
This will keep up to two weeks.

title: bruce's favorite broccoli salad
directions: In a large salad bowl, combine broccoli, cauliflower, bacon, onion and tomatoes; set aside.
Combine mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar; mix until smooth.
Just before serving, pour dressing over salad and toss.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into a pan.
In separate bowl, mix 1 cup sugar with 2 1/2 or 3 tablespoons of cocoa and pour on top of other ingredients.
Pour 1 cup of boiling water on top and bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Boil the chicken breasts until meat falls apart.
Use the same water and add the spaghetti. Cook until most of the liquid boils out.
Saute the pepper and onions in butter.
Pour mixture into the spaghetti mixture. Add the Ro-Tel.
Debone and cut chicken in small pieces and add to mixture.
Add the cheese to the mixture. Heat on low until cheese melts, about 10 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice casserole(heritage recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Saute onion in oleo until tender.
Add soup, cheese, rice and broccoli.
Pour into greased casserole and bake for 30 minutes.
If desired, add topping of mixture of ritz crackers and butter.

title: layered cauliflower salad
directions: Cut cauliflower into flowerets.
Layer lettuce, onion, cauliflower and bacon in a 3-quart bowl.
Combine mayonnaise, sugar and cheese.
Spread evenly over top, sealing to edge of bowl.
Sprinkle with more cheese.
Refrigerate.
Toss gently before serving.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: hot 'n sour sauteed cabbage and apples
directions: Combine butter and onions in a 3-quart microwave proof casserole dish. Cook on High to melt butter. Add cabbage and apples. Cover tightly and cook on High for 6 minutes or until tender-crisp; stir well. Let stand, covered, while cooking the sauce.

title: sweet and sour slaw
directions: Chop all vegetables fine.

title: helen's blackberry cobbler
directions: Blend flour, shortening and salt as for a pie crust.
Mix vinegar, egg and cold water.
Blend with other ingredients and roll out thin to fit a large baking dish with crust left hanging over the sides of baking dish.

title: witches brew
directions: Mix together and heat over low heat until ready to serve.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Cream oleo with sugar.
Add vanilla until light and fluffy. Add 1/2 of the nuts.
Blend in flour and remaining nuts.
Shape into small balls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.
When cool, roll in powdered sugar. Yields 2 dozen.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut up squash and cook with carrot, onion and salt until tender.
Drain well.
Add sour cream and chicken soup.
Mix well. Put in casserole dish.
Melt margarine, add stuffing mix and put on top of squash mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Chop squash, onions and pepper.
Mix all ingredients and let set 1 hour.
Bring to boil and boil 15 minutes.
Add 1 tablespoon salt and 1 teaspoon turmeric.
Can.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix and roll into 2 rolls.
Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate for 3 hours or overnight.
Slice and bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Remove from pan.
Cool and frost with powdered sugar frosting.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: In an ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan, dump both cans of pie filling and spread evenly.
Dump pineapple on top and spread evenly.
Dump cake mix and spread evenly over top.
Cut up butter and spread evenly over top.
Pour 1 tablespoon of water over top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Makes a crisp cherry cobbler type dessert.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Coat cutlets with flour, shaking to remove excess.
In large skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat.
Cook chicken cutlets, 2 at a time, if necessary, until browned on both sides.
Remove from skillet to plate.
Add chicken broth, butter and lemon juice to skillet.
Cook, stirring, until mixture boils.
Return cutlets to skillet.
Cover and cook about 2 minutes, basting once with pan juices, until cooked through.
Before serving, sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 4.

title: cinnamon pickles
directions: Peel and core cucumbers; cut in strips.
Add 2 cups lime and cover with water.
Soak for 24 hours.
Drain and wash well.
Cover with cold water and ice for 3 hours and drain.
Mix 1 cup vinegar and alum, 1 small bottle of red food coloring and enough water to cover cucumbers.
Simmer for 2 hours.
Drain and throw juice out. Mix 2 cups vinegar, 2 cups water, sugar, cinnamon sticks and cinnamon extract (or red hots dissolved in warm water 1 hour).

title: sweet potato surprise
directions: Melt 3/4 c. margarine and marshmallow cream in pan over low heat, stirring constantly, until smooth.
Beat potatoes, marshmallow mixture, eggs and milk at medium speed in batches until smooth.
Spoon into 9 x 13 baking dish.
Melt 1/3 c. margarine and brown sugar over medium-low heat.
Stir in cereal and pecans.
Sprinkle over potato mixture and bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: down under chicken
directions: Heat olive oil in a saute pan.
Cook chicken breasts until golden brown on both sides and remove from pan.
Pour off excess oil from pan, add sugar and cook until sugar has caramelized.
Add sherry, bouillon cubes, garlic and peach halves.

title: munster cookies
directions: Cream butter or margarine; gradually add other ingredients. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly brown. Cool and eat.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Place rice in bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Spread cream of chicken soup over rice.
Add water.
Stir.
Place skinless chicken on top of rice mixture.
Sprinkle dry onion soup on top. Cover tightly with foil.
Bake for 2 hours on 350°.
Turn oven off and let rice sit in oven for 30 minutes.
Steam finishes cooking rice.
Before serving, stir chicken into rice.
During cooking, do not lift the foil.
No peeking!!!!!!!!!!

title: primavera salad
directions: Cook tortellini according to package directions.
Drain. Rinse with cold water.
Drain well.
In a large mixing bowl, combine tortellini, pepper, broccoli, carrot, olives and pepperoni, if desired.

title: strawberry lemon balm butter
directions: In food processor combine butter and confectioners sugar; process until creamy.
Add strawberries and lemon balm.
Pulse with on/off turns just until combined.
If strawberries are particularly tart, add another tablespoon of sugar.
Serve with biscuits, fruit muffins or waffles.
Yields 1 1/3 cups.

title: coconut peanut cookies
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients.
Sift and add flour, soda, baking powder and salt to creamed mixture.
Stir in peanuts and coconut. Drop cookies onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 dozen.

title: honey glazed wings
directions: Cut off and discard wing tips; cut wings in half at joint. Place wing pieces in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over wing pieces.
Turn to coat.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Transfer wings to lightly greased pan.
Bake for 45 minutes in a 375° oven, uncovered.
Turn once during baking.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots and drain; boil together the sugar, oil and vinegar.
Add mustard, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and soup.
Beat with hand mixer.
Add green pepper, onion, celery and carrots.
Let sit overnight.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix beans, onion, salt and pepper in a 1 1/2-quart bowl.
Add oil, vinegar and sugar.
Mix well; cover and refrigerate several hours, stirring occasionally.

title: marie's shrimp salad
directions: Combine 1/4 cup Miracle Whip and 4 ounces cream cheese.
Mix all ingredients together.

title: payday cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cake mix, 1/3 cup butter and egg. Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan for 12 to 18 minutes.
When baked and still hot, top with marshmallows.
Heat in microwave the corn syrup, 1/4 cup butter, chips and vanilla (about 30 seconds and then 30 seconds).
When smooth, add peanuts and Rice Krispies. Pour over top of cake.

title: quiche lorraine(makes 2 pies!)
directions: Prick bottom and sides of pie shells.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Combine ingredients and mix in blender.
Pour into cooled pie shells.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 45 minutes until knife comes out clean.
Let stand 15 to 30 minutes before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: frankfurter bean casserole
directions: Heat margarine in a
large skillet.
Saute frank slices and onion, stirring occasionally. When onion is tender, add all other ingredients except chips.
Mix well.
Place in 2-quart casserole and top with chips.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry jello salad
directions: Mix the 3-ounce cherry jello according to directions.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and place in fridge until firm.
Whip the cream, sugar and cream cheese.
Spread over set jello.
Chill well.
Mix the 6-ounce cherry jello with 2 cups boiling water, then add the cherry pie filling.
Do not add cold water.
Cool slightly and spoon gently over cream cheese layer.
Chill several hours or overnight before serving.

title: chicken divan
directions: In casserole dish sprayed with Pam, place cleaned broccoli. Put chicken next on top of broccoli.
Sprinkle with garlic salt, cut up margarine and 1/2 of almonds.
Mix rest of ingredients together and pour over top.
Sprinkle with rest of almonds.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Mix together all the ingredients except the mushrooms.
Fill mushrooms with mixture.
Bake at 450°, approximately 15 minutes, until done.

title: katie's dessert
directions: Measure juice from pineapple and oranges.
Need 2 1/2 cups. Add to vanilla pudding.
Cook until thick. Cool completely.
Add fruit and cut up 2 bananas.
Make a day ahead.
I have also used canned peaches and the peach juice instead of mandarin orange juice.

title: bran muffins
directions: Cream the sugar and oleo.
Add the eggs and butter.
Mix, then add the boiling water and 100% Bran.
Sift and add the flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Add the Bran Buds.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.

title: five minute fudge
directions: Combine milk, butter and sugar in saucepan; heat to boiling. Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly and then remove from heat. Add marshmallows, nuts, chocolate chips and vanilla.
Stir until marshmallows are melted.
Pour into buttered 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: dill onion dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and put in bottom of Pyrex dish.
Mix together the next 4 ingredients.
Pour over bottom layer.
Crush one stack Ritz crackers; toss crackers in 1 stick melted butter. Place on top of casserole; cook at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Boil the chicken for one hour.	Cool.
Melt cheese, Boil noodles until tender.
Tear chicken into pieces.
Mix cheese, noodles, rotel and chicken together.
Put into casserole dish and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: easy chili
directions: Cook beef and onions in large skillet until brown and crumbly. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Can be used for chili beans.

title: ham casserole
directions: Cook rice and broccoli according to package directions. Spread rice in buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with broccoli.
Combine ham, mushrooms, water chestnuts, Cheddar cheese, soup, mayonnaise, mustard and curry; spread over broccoli layer.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Casserole can be refrigerated until ready to bake.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Leftovers are great, especially over holidays.

title: pineapple cheese bake
directions: Combine pineapple and cheese.
Combine sugar and flour.
Mix with pineapple and cheese.
Put in 8 x 8-inch baking dish. Sprinkle crackers over the top and drizzle with melted butter. Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: italian green beans
directions: Cook beans as directed; drain.
Saute onion and garlic in butter until tender.
Add lemon juice, cheese and pepper.
Pour over hot beans.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: good and easy cake
directions: Mix together shortening, flour, salt, sugar, baking powder and 1/2 cup milk.
Beat the eggs, vanilla and 1/2 cup milk for 2 minutes.
Mix everything together for 2 minutes and bake at 350° until done.

title: herb 'n cheddar butter
directions: Mix.
Use with breads, baked potatoes, sandwiches, omelets, bagels.

title: surprise bran muffins
directions: Combine cereal and milk.
Let stand 2 minutes.
Add margarine and egg.
Mix well.
Add combined dry ingredients, mixing just until moistened.
Spoon into greased medium size muffin pan.
Make a deep indentation in top of batter for each muffin.
Fill with preserves.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: cheesy microwave meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients, except Heinz 57 sauce and brown sugar.
Blend and spread in microwave baking dish.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave on High 18 to 20 minutes.
Uncover and brush on mixture made from Heinz 57 and brown sugar.
Microwave on Low five more minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Drain green beans.
Put in casserole in order of recipe (hamburger, beans, soup, onion).
Top with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt butter.
Add cocoa, sugar and milk.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Boil one minute.
Remove from burner, add vanilla, oatmeal and peanut butter. Stir well.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Make about 4 dozen cookie.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Saute celery, onion and pepper in small amount of butter.
Mix turkey, rice and mushroom soup together.
Add to celery mixture; add pimento and orange.
Place in baking dish, sprinkle with 1/2 cup shredded Cheddar over top.
Sprinkle with 1 cup or more crushed potato chips.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 16 to 20.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Combine chunks, flour and sugar.
Mix well.
Add cheese and mix well again.
Pour mixture into casserole dish.
Add crushed crackers to melted margarine and mix well.
Spread over pineapple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
(I add a little of the pineapple juice to the mixture, about 1/2 cup.)

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into buttered baking dish.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: volcano cake
directions: Mix pecans, margarine and coconut and put in 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix cake mix with vanilla according to directions on box.
Pour this over pecan and coconut mixture.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix well and drop by tablespoon on top of cake mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hamburger hash
directions: Cook potatoes and onion together until potatoes are soft and falling apart.
Brown hamburger in nonstick skillet.
Add to potatoes with seasonings and simmer slowly for a couple of minutes.
Good with garlic bread.

title: arabic omelet(ijee)
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter.
Place 1 1/2 tablespoons butter in pan and heat.
Drop 1/2 of the mixture in a skillet. When set, turn the omelet on the other side.
Fry until golden brown.
Repeat with the rest of the mixture to yield two omelets. Serves 4.

title: teriyaki sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Soak beef or chicken in sauce for 1 or 2 days.
(Heat extra sauce and serve on rice.)
Grill meat as desired.

title: loaf bread
directions: Combine 1/3 cup warm water,
yeast,
2/3 tablespoonful of sugar and set aside. Combine 1-2/3 cups water, 1-1/2 cups milk, 1/2 cup butter, 2 tablespoons salt and 1/2 cup sugar; beat until sugar and butter are melted.
Cool.
Add yeast mixture.
Using 6 cups of flour, mix and knead 15 minutes.
Let rise once in bowls and once in pan after making loaves.
Bake at 350° until brown. Butter tops when removed from oven.
Yield:
2 loaves.

title: meringue
directions: Beat the three egg whites until stiff.
Add one tablespoon of sugar slowly, beating constantly.
Then add one tablespoon of marshmallow cream.
Mix well into meringue.
(Marshmallow cream helps meringue to stay soft.)
Top pie and sprinkle with coconut. Brown in hot oven until golden brown.

title: pork chop-potato casserole
directions: Brown pork chops over medium heat.
Arrange 2 cups potatoes in a 2-quart casserole.
Season with salt and pepper.
Slice 1 onion into very thin slices and arrange on top of potatoes.
Pour 1/2 can of mushroom soup over all.
Repeat procedure.
Place browned pork chops on top.
Cover.
Bake about 1 hour at 350° or until tender all the way through.
This casserole is very easy to prepare.

title: no-fat brownies
directions: * May use more if desired.

title: deviled ham-cheese ball
directions: In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients except nuts.
Mix well until blended.
Refrigerate until firm enough to handle. Form into a ball and roll in the nuts until completely covered. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: grandkids popsicle treats
directions: Mix all the ingredients but do not beat. Pour into popsicle containers or paper cups.
Put in freezer until solid.

title: glorified pork chops
directions: Roll pork chops in egg, using 1 egg per 2 pork chops.
Then roll in bread crumbs.
Then roll in soup mix.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour in long casserole dish (one layer only).

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl; mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Drain corn.
Mix cream cheese and butter.
Add milk, salt, flour and peppers.
Mix with corn.
Bake at 350° until hot, about 30 minutes.
This recipe can be put in your crock-pot on low until thoroughly heated.
It takes from 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Cut sweet potato into dice.
Puree with coconut milk in the blender.
Pour blended mixture into a bowl and add all the other ingredients, except margarine.
Pour into a well-greased 8-inch square baking tin.
Dot with margarine.
Bake on center shelf at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve hot or cold.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Cream the cream cheese and add the mayonnaise and whipped cream.
Fold in the pineapple, nuts and cranberry sauce.
Freeze.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter, milk and marshmallow whip and bring to a boil.
Boil for 4 minutes stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 8 x 8 dish and chill. Cut into 1 inch squares.

title: peachy low calorie chicken
directions: Arrange chicken pieces in a single layer in a shallow 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Drain peach syrup into a cup and add lemon juice and soy sauce to peach syrup.
Brush about half over chicken.
Bake in a hot oven at 400°, brushing every 15 minutes with remaining peach syrup mixture and pan juices, 1 hour until chicken is tender and richly browned.
Place peach halves around chicken; brush with pan juices.
Bake 5 minutes longer to heat peaches.

title: mahogany chiffon cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Combine boiling water and cocoa.
Cool. Sift flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Make a well in dry ingredients; add oil, egg yolks, cocoa mixture and vanilla.
Beat until smooth. In large bowl, beat egg whites and cream of tartar until very stiff.
Pour egg yolk mixture gradually in egg whites.
Gently fold with spatula until well blended.
Pour in tube pan.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes.
Hang until cool.

title: broccoli fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cook fettuccine according to package directions. Meanwhile, in a saucepan over medium heat, cook broccoli in a small amount of water until crisp-tender, about 5 minutes; drain. In a saucepan over medium heat, melt butter. Stir in flour until smooth. Gradually whisk in milk. Bring to a boil ; cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened. Remove from heat; stir in the Parmesan cheese and broccoli. Drain fettuccine; top with the broccoli mixture. Yield: 4 servings.

title: heath bars
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add sugar, water and corn syrup. Cook, stirring, until sugar dissolves.
Cook, not stirring, over medium heat to "hard crack".
Stir in 1 cup nuts; pour in greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top, spreading evenly over top as they melt.
Sprinkle on remaining nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: good stuffing chicken
directions: Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Lay cheese slices over chicken.
Mix soup and wine and pour over chicken and cheese. Spread stuffing mix over all and spread out evenly.
Drizzle butter over stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
This can be made the night before and baked the next day for 50 minutes if cold.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: squash patties
directions: Mix squash, onion and salt in colander.
Let drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Make in patties and drop.
Fry until brown.

title: broccoli and rice supreme
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Saute celery, onion, frozen broccoli and mushrooms.
Add soup, cheese and rice.
Remove from heat and place in casserole.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter with extract.
Gradually add sugar and cream. Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition. Beat in chopped pecans, corn syrup and salt.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350° and arrange pecans over top of filling.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until set.
Cool.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil all the ingredients.
Remove from the heat and add oats and peanut butter.
Spoon onto a cookie sheet and let cool.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Melt margarine and mix with Oreo mixture.
Pack in bottom of spring-form pan.
Do not build up sides.
Mix Fluff and creme de menthe.
Beat cream until stiff.
Fold with mixture of Fluff and creme de menthe.
Freeze until firm.
Remove from freezer 10 minutes before serving.

title: microwave chocolate fudge
directions: Melt chocolate in small glass bowl in microwave oven (about 3 minutes on High); set aside to cool.
Soften cream cheese in 1 1/2-quart glass bowl in microwave oven, 30 to 60 seconds at Medium setting.
Beat cheese until fluffy; blend in the cooled chocolate and vanilla extract.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Pour fudge into buttered 8-inch square dish.
Chill in refrigerator until firm; cut into squares.
Makes about 36.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream
butter and sugar together.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add
eggs,
one
at a time and beat well.	Add flour, mix and
beat	in lemon extract and 7-Up.
Pour batter into a well-greased
and floured jumbo Bundt pan.	Bake at 325° for 1 hour
and 15 minutes.
Cool in pan 1/2 hour and turn on a cake dish.
Sprinkle with 10x sugar. Do not preheat oven.

title: easy scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a buttered 9 x 13 pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: chuck wagon beans
directions: Fry sausage and bacon.
Mix all other ingredients together. Crumble sausage and bacon with the other ingredients.
Add barbecue sauce.
Mixture will be a little dry at first.
Put in dish and place in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until juice is thickened.
If you like baked beans, you'll love this.

title: warm potato salad
directions: Place potatoes in a saucepan; add water and cover.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes or until potato is tender; drain.
Place potato and onion in a bowl.
Combine vinegar and remaining ingredients; stir well.
Add to potato mixture; toss gently to coat.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: corn souffle
directions: Mix together and pour into greased baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: no crust pecan pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add baking powder, then sugar gradually.
Fold in graham crackers, pecans and vanilla.
Bake in greased pie pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
When cool, top with whipping cream or Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs. Refrigerate.

title: chili sauce
directions: Put tomatoes and onions through a food chopper.
Add all ingredients.
Boil 2 hours or until thick, stirring frequently to keep from scorching.
As soon as sauce is thick as desired, pour into sterilized jars and seal.

title: orange candy cake
directions: Mix the dates, pecans, coconut and candy (coated with flour before cutting up).
Cream together the Crisco, oleo, sugar, eggs, salt and soda.
Add the 2 1/2 cups flour, alternating with buttermilk to the creamed mixture, then add the first mixture to all and mix well.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate quickies
directions: Melt chocolate chips, corn syrup and water together in microwave about 2 minutes on High or on stove until able to stir smooth. Stir in cereal. Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper. Chill until firm. Makes 30 to 36 pieces.

title: poppy seed salad dressing
directions: Put above ingredients inside a blender.
Turn on high until dressing gets frothy.
Put it in a jar and refrigerate overnight.

title: chewy cake
directions: Mix together brown sugar and butter. Add remaining ingredients. Blend well. Spread thin on greased baking pan. Bake at 325° until firm and brown.

title: polish apple cake
directions: Cream together sugar, eggs and oil.
Sift together all dry ingredients.
Mix apples and creamed mixture alternately with dry ingredients.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: layered ice cream dessert
directions: Melt chocolate and 1/2 cup butter in top of double boiler; stir in sugar, milk and salt.
Bring mixture to a boil; reduce heat and cook 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Let cool.

title: 3 rivers chicken in sour cream
directions: Mix flour with sour cream, then mix in all other ingredients, except chicken.
Pour into baking dish and submerge chicken into mix.
Bake, uncovered, 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over rice or couscous.

title: dole pineapple juice sparkle
directions: Combine ingredients in pitcher.
Makes 10 (6 ounce) servings.

title: ham rolls
directions: Spread softened cream cheese on each slice of ham; add slice of pickle.
Roll up and cut in desired pieces.
Place toothpick in each roll-up.

title: cherry squares
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Add vanilla and evaporated milk and beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients. Add more flour, if needed, to make smooth dough.
Knead dough until smooth.
Roll out dough to thickness of pie crust for double layer. Place bottom crust in lightly greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan. Pour pie filling over it.
Cover with top crust or make lattice top, if desired.
Brush with milk.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar in large bowl until light and fluffy, add eggs 1 at a time, beating well after each.
Add milk and vanilla wafers, beating well after each addition.
Stir in pecans and coconut.
