Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan for several minutes.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco and oleo.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one.
Add flour and Seven-Up.
Beat well.
Pour into well-greased tube pan.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: brunch eggs
directions: Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan and refrigerate a few hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 10 people.
Great for Christmas morning.
Can be prepared night before.

title: egg noodles
directions: Mix and knead 10 minutes.
Cover for 10 minutes.
Roll out and let dry 1 hour or longer.
Cut in thin strips and dry for 2 hours or longer.

title: copper penny carrots
directions: Cook carrots in salted water until medium done.
Rinse in cold water.
Arrange layers of carrots, green pepper and onion in a bowl.

title: pierogi casserole
directions: Cook noodles; drain and rinse.
Cook potatoes; drain and mash. Add cheese to mashed potatoes.

title: jerry's roast
directions: Use tenderizer according to directions on label.
Mix salt, mustard, garlic salt and pepper and rub on roast.
Mix the catsup, Worcestershire and wine; pour over roast.
Can place roast in baking bag which is floured and pricked as directed, then pour catsup mixture over it.
Roast at 325° until desired doneness.

title: crab meltaways
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients.
Spread mixture over the English muffins.
Cut into fourths.
Freeze
at least 30 minutes. Broil until browned.

title: apple jelly
directions: Combine juices, cloves and cinnamon in heavy pan.
Bring to a boil and simmer 10 minutes.
Then, soak gelatin in cold water. Remove juice from heat; discard cloves and cinnamon.
Add gelatin and sugar substitute; mix well to dissolve.
Pour into 2 hot, clean 1/2 pint jars.
Cover lightly until cool, then cover tightly and store in the refrigerator.

title: quesadillas
directions: Heat skillet over medium heat.
Mix together pork chops, corn, beans, pineapple and tomatoes.
Place tortilla in pan. Spoon mixture over half of tortilla.
Sprinkle cheese over the mixture.
Fold tortilla over.
Cook until tortilla is browned and slightly crispy on both sides and cheese is melted.
Serve with salsa and sour cream.

title: kringla
directions: Mix baking soda into sour cream.
Add whipping cream and sugar.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Roll out and bake at 350° for 7 to 9 minutes. Burns easily so don't overbake.

title: pineapple pistachio pudding
directions: Mix undrained pineapple with the pudding powder. Fold in the Cool Whip.
Fold in the marshmallows and nuts.
Refrigerate 3 hours or more before serving.

title: i m f cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften for easy mixing.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Batter will be runny.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Delicious moist cake.

title: mom's raisin-spice cake
directions: Boil together first 4 ingredients.
Let cool, then add cinnamon, cloves, flour and shortening.
Dissolve baking soda in boiling water and add to batter.
Add vanilla or lemon flavoring (lemon juice is best).
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: classic spinach dip
directions: Squeeze spinach until dry. In medium bowl, mix spinach, sour cream, mayonnaise, soup mix, water chestnuts and onion. Cover; refrigerate for 2 hours before serving. Serve with crackers or with Hawaiian bread.

title: braunschweiger ball(appetizer)
directions: Mix until smooth sausage, mayonnaise, pickle juice, hot pepper sauce, garlic salt and 1/3 package cream cheese.
Add pickles and 1/4 cup onion.
Mix well.
Line bowl with plastic wrap.
Fill with mixture and refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: crab bisque
directions: In saucepan, melt butter; blend in flour.
Cook until bubbly. Gradually stir in half and half.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until slightly thickened.
Add remaining ingredients. Heat thoroughly, stirring frequently.
Garnish with paprika.

title: brown sugar glaze
directions: Put ingredients
in
saucepan and boil 3 minutes.
Pour over warm apple cake.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate for at least 6 hours.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Separately blanch first four vegetables until barely tender. Drain.
Saute tomatoes in 1 tablespoon of butter and set aside. Heat cream, cheese and remaining butter.
Keep warm.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, cream cheese and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Add flour gradually. Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: simple yeast rolls
directions: Mix well; stir in self-rising flour to desired thickness (about 4 cups).
Let rise.
Make out into rolls on greased baking pan.
Let rise and cook at 325° to 350° until brown.

title: salsa
directions: For a smooth salsa, process ingredients in blender.
For a chunky salsa, chop ingredients and mix.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: ro-tel chicken
directions: Heat both cans of soup and milk.
Boil chicken.
Melt cheese and mix with soup.
Combine all ingredients except Doritos.
Line casserole dish with Doritos (usually the whole bag), then pour the mixed ingredients over the chips.
Bake at 350° until bubbly or cook in microwave.

title: old fashion tea cakes
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs together. Mix dry ingredients together and add to butter, sugar and egg mixture. Roll out on floured surface very thin. Cut with cookie cutter. Place on cookie sheet and bake about 20 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.

title: the best chocolate syrup brownies(how to microwave)
directions: Cream together butter and sugar until smooth and creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add salt.
Stir in chocolate syrup, flour and vanilla.
Add nuts and stir to blend well.
Turn into greased and lightly floured 8-inch square microwave-safe pan or dish.

title: glorified rice
directions: Make jello according to package directions.
Make rice according to package directions.
Put pineapple in refrigerator. Chill jello, rice and pineapple in their separate containers for 24 hours.
Next day, fold together jello, pineapple and rice. Then blend together pineapple juice, pudding mix and Cool Whip. Fold into jello mixture.
Chill 2 hours before serving.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream
butter, sugar, egg, milk and vanilla.
Sift flour and add
to
creamed mixture.
Chill, roll out; cut and bake on greased baking sheet in 375° oven for about 8 minutes.

title: bonnie's cast-a-role(uses up your leftovers)
directions: Cook rice in 1 cup of chicken broth and 1 1/2 cans of water. Bring to a boil and boil for 10 minutes.
In a large casserole dish, mix all ingredients.
Top with 12 to 15 round Ritz-style crackers (crushed).
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 45 minutes. Will serve 8 to 10 people.

title: little jane's buttermilk pound cake
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, eggs, buttermilk, flour, soda, baking powder, salt and lemon extract.
Beat at high speed for three minutes. Put in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in preheated oven for 1 hour at 325°.

title: deep fried brussel sprouts
directions: Run hot water over frozen brussel sprouts; drain; cut large ones in half.
Put 1 cup flour in a grocery bag or large paper sack.
Dump in Brussel sprouts and shake quickly to coat all sprouts.
Mix remaining dry ingredients.
Beat eggs and milk with a fork.
Dip Brussel sprouts in egg mixture and roll in dry mixture.
Drop into hot oil, frying until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot, warm or cold.
Serve plain or with favorite sauce; Ranch dressing, horseradish sauce, salsa or Catalina.
They are even good smeared with pimento cheese.
Serve as an appetizer, snack or as a vegetable to compliment a meal.

title: fry bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together. Cut in shortening, adding water to make dough (consistency of biscuit dough).
Roll out dough about 1/2-inch thick and cut into 3-inch squares.
Cut hole in center. Fry in deep fat.

title: chocolate or lemon cooler
directions: Mix butter, flour and nuts.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, 1 cup Cool Whip and powdered sugar and spread on cooled crust. Mix instant pudding with milk; pour over cream cheese mixture.
Cool.
Top with 1 cup Cool Whip; sprinkle with nuts.

title: sour cream mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in salt water, mash but do not add milk.
Grease casserole with butter.
Combine all ingredients, put into casserole dish and sprinkle heavily with grated Parmesan cheese. Dot with butter.
Refrigerate overnight.
(This brings out the flavor.)
Take out of refrigerator 1/2 hour before baking.
Bake in 350° oven for 1/2 hour or longer until top is golden brown.

title: easy beet pickles
directions: Put sugar and vinegar in pan and bring to boil. Add beets and cloves. Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.

title: larry's hamburger helper
directions: Use either the Italian seasoning or the oregano, sweet basil, rosemary and basil.

title: easy apple cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine apples, 3/4 cup of sugar, 2 tablespoons of flour, cinnamon, salt and 1/4 cup of water in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Dot with butter.
Cover with foil and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: kolachy - slovak filled cookies
directions: Mix water, yeast and sugar.
Let raise while making dough. Mix margarine and flour until crumbled.
Add beaten egg yolks and mix well.
Add to yeast mixture.
Blend well.
Place dough in refrigerator overnight.

Roll out size of walnut on powdered sugar; place spoonful of filling (jam) in center and roll loosely. Sealing edges slightly, make into crescent shape on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli by directions on box. Finely chop onion and mix with eggs, mayonnaise, mushroom soup and broccoli.
Sprinkle with cheese and cover with Ritz crackers. Melt margarine and pour over top.
Cook at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hearty meat ball casserole
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients and form 8 large meat balls. Place in a round 2-quart casserole.
Combine the remaining ingredients to make the sauce and pour over the meat balls.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate frosted brownies
directions: Sift flour 1 time.
Add baking powder and salt and sift together.
Add butter to chocolate and melt over slow fire or in a microwave.
Combine sugar and eggs, add chocolate mixture, beating thoroughly.
Mix in flour mixture.
Then add vanilla and chocolate morsels.
Bake in a greased 8-inch square pan at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: artichoke appetizer
directions: Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Use crackers for dip.

title: grandma's chicken pie
directions: Combine all ingredients; place in pan on burner.
Cook very slowly; thicken with flour paste.
Pour into greased casserole and top with drop biscuits.
Bake at 350° until biscuits are nicely browned.

title: creamed turkey in confetti rice
directions: Cook onion in margarine until tender, but not brown.
Blend in flour.
Slowly stir in broth and milk.
Add salt.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture thickens.
Stir small amount of hot mixture into egg yolks, return to hot mixture, cook and stir over low heat about 1 minute.
Add turkey and mushrooms; heat just until hot through.
Let set.
Prepare rice.

title: slim chicken
directions: Brown chicken breasts.
Put in baking dish.
Cover with tomatoes and zucchini.
Add slices of onion and mushrooms.
Bake 1 hour at 350° uncovered.

title: barbecue sauced ribs
directions: For sauce, spray a cold medium skillet with nonstick cooking spray.
Cook and stir the onion and garlic over medium heat for 2 to 3 minutes until onion is tender.
Stir in tomato sauce, water, honey, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, celery seed and pepper.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Simmer uncovered for 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: avocado surprise
directions: Combine mayonnaise, chili sauce and relish in small bowl. Stir a generous amount of dressing into crabmeat to moisten it well.
Cut avocados in half lengthwise; remove pits.
Fill each half with a portion of the crabmeat mixture.
Mix eggs and dill together; sprinkle over crabmeat.
Spoon the remaining dressing over the chopped eggs.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: creamy coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in pie shell. Place in freezer.

title: baked fish fillets
directions: Cut fish into 50 portions. Mix fat, salt, pepper and lemon juice. Dip each portion into seasoned fat. Dredge fish with flour. Place close together in a single layer in a greased baking pan. Mix butter or margarine and milk and pour over fillets. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: deviled rolls
directions: Roll out crescent roll dough.
Butter and spread with deviled ham.
Slice dough into 16 triangles.
Roll each one separately. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: applesauce-oat muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottoms only of 12 medium muffin cups.
Mix cereal, flour, brown sugar, cinnamon, baking powder and baking soda in large bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients, just until moistened.
Bake 18 to 22 minutes.

title: fruit nut snack
directions: Combine ingredients and store in an airtight container. Yields 4 cups.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Butter a large pan.
Mix all liquids together and pour into buttered pan.
Sprinkle rice over liquids.
Put onion soup mix over the rice.
Place salted and peppered chicken on top.
Cover with heavy foil.
Bake for 2 hours at 325°.
Remove foil. Return to oven and brown lightly.

title: lasagna vegetable roll
directions: Cook noodles as directed, omitting salt.
Drain and pat dry. Saute mushrooms and onions in margarine, until tender.
Combine cottage cheese, spinach, carrots, eggs and 4 tablespoons Parmesan cheese.
Add mushrooms and onions and pepper.
Mix well.
Spread 1/3 cup filling along each noodle.
Roll up and place in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.

title: cranberry jello salad #2
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve jello in boiling water. Stir in pineapple with juice and cranberry sauce. Refrigerate for 30 minutes. After 30 minutes, stir in the grapes and pecans. Pour into serving bowl. Refrigerate until set firm.

title: caramel puffs
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together; microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Add to corn puffs.
Put in a brown bag.
Microwave for 1 1/2 minutes on High.
Shake well and put back in the microwave for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove and shake well.
Cool and serve.

title: karen's infamous vegetable pizza
directions: Press crescent dough in 13 x 9 pan and bake according to package directions. Cool completely. Mix together cream cheese and dressing. Spread evenly over cooled crust. Cover with vegetables, then top with shredded cheese. Cut into bars.

title: green pea salad
directions: Drain peas.
Mix in mayonnaise, mustard, chopped celery and onion and pimento.
Chill 1/2 hour and serve.
(Option: Lay a few boiled egg slices on top.)
Serves 4.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Bake in skillet just like you would any regular bread at 400°.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle coconut and pecans in pan. Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Pour over nuts and coconut. Melt butter, then mix cream cheese and sugar.
Pour this over the cake.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: fruit smoothie
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend well.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Break tortillas into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Pour chicken broth over chips.
Mix chicken, onion, pepper, soups and chopped Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Add chili powder.
Pour chicken mixture over chips. Top with cheese.
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes.

title: shore shrimp creole
directions: Cook and peel shrimp.
Cut celery, green pepper and mushrooms. Add diced onions and saute in butter. Add crushed tomatoes, mild pepper rings and pepper ring juice.
Add spices (pepper, garlic salt, parsley and oregano).
Simmer. Serve over rice.

title: piquant meatballs
directions: Combine beef, egg, bread crumbs and seasonings.
Shape into balls the size of a walnut.
Heat chili sauce, jelly and lemon juice in a heavy skillet or a Dutch oven until blended.
Add meatballs; cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Remove first batch and drop in the rest.
Stir to prevent sticking.
Makes about 40 small balls.
You do not need to brown meatballs first.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Melt shortening in skillet.
Brown onions, celery, salt, pepper, bouillon, soy sauce and sugar.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add frozen vegetables and diced chicken.
Cook about 8 minutes and remove from heat.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all cake ingredients together and bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: stuffed squash
directions: Cut squash in half lengthwise.
Remove seeds.
Bake cut-side down in baking dish at 350° for 40 minutes.
Mix apple, celery, walnuts, sugar and cinnamon.
Turn squash cut-side up and sprinkle with salt.
Put apple mixture in squash halves and bake covered about 25 minutes or until apple is tender.
Serves 4.

title: caramel cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions for layer cake.
Mix other ingredients well.
Cook over low heat 30 minutes or until thickened.
Spread on cooled cake layers.

title: cornbread broccoli pie(a quick meal in a pie form)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Prepare cornbread mix according to package directions.
Stir in Spam.
Spread into greased 9-inch pie pan. Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until cornbread is done.
Arrange broccoli spears on top of cornbread, sprinkle with cheese.
Return to oven, continue baking for 5 to 10 minutes or until cheese is melted and cornbread is completely baked.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: norwegian prune pudding
directions: Pour 1 3/4 cups water over prunes.
Cover and cook until tender.
Cool and drain, reserving liquid.
Chop prunes and add to prune liquid.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown ground beef; pour off fat.
Stir in one can of pizza sauce, then sprinkle with garlic salt and oregano, to suit your taste.
Let meat mixture cool, then place on buns and top with a slice of Mozzarella cheese.
Wrap in foil.
Heat in oven until cheese melts.

title: dixie pork chops
directions: Brown chops in hot fat. Sprinkle with salt and sage.
Place in baking dish. Top with apples and sprinkle with brown sugar.
Add flour to fat in skillet and blend. Add water and vinegar; cook until thickened.
Add raisins and pour over chops.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or more.
Serves 8.
(Ha! Ha!)

title: horseradish jelly
directions: Combine all ingredients except pectin.
Bring to a boil, then add the liquid pectin, stirring constantly.
Boil hard for 30 seconds. Pour into clean, warm jelly glasses.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: About 1 hour before serving, in 9 x 13-inch pan, spread 1 cup sour cream; set aside.
In 2-quart saucepan, flake chicken.
Add 1/2 cup sour cream, mushrooms, chilis, onion flakes, chili powder, salt, garlic powder and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally just until thoroughly heated.
Preheat oven to 450°. In 8-inch skillet over medium heat, fry tortilla in 1/2-inch hot oil a few seconds on each side until soft.
For each enchilada along center of tortilla, spread 1/4 cup chicken mixture.
Fold sides of tortilla over filling and place seam side down in sour cream pan.
Spread remaining sour cream over enchiladas and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 8 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes in water, broth and cream of celery soup until soft.
Add milk.

title: barbecue pork and beans
directions: Brown hamburger. Mix all ingredients and bake in preheated 350° oven.

title: coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package; then cool cake.
Mix together next 3 ingredients.
Punch holes in cake all over.
Then pour Eagle Brand mixture in holes of cake.
Refrigerate 25 minutes, then top with Cool Whip and coconut.
Refrigerate leftover cake.

title: fruit punch
directions: Place sherbet in large punch bowl.
Pour pineapple juice over. Add ginger ale or Sprite.
Stir and serve immediately.
Yields 50 servings.

title: eggplant karashizuke
directions: Cut eggplants in halves lengthwise and cut into small triangles.
Soak in salt water overnight with weight on it.
Next day, put the eggplants in a strainer and pour boiling water over them.
Let it cool, squeeze gently.

title: honey mustard chicken in a hurry
directions: Bring the first seven ingredients to boil and cool.
Mix together remaining ingredients; combine with cooled mixture.
Put in greased 7 1/2 x 11 1/2-inch or 8 x 8-inch dish.
Sprinkle slivered almonds on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: super burgers
directions: To every pound of crumbled, cooked burger you use, add these ingredients.
Heat through and serve on big buns with slices of onion, pickle and tomato.

title: toffee phe's
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 15 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan; set aside.
In large bowl of electric mixer, at high speed, beat butter with sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolk and vanilla; beat until blended.
At low speed, beat in flour.
With spatula, spread mixture in prepared pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Cook broccoli until tender and can break apart with fork. Drain broccoli and mix all ingredients and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan, 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.

title: gram's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together well with a little water to moisten.
Shape in greased baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Pour over loaf 1/2 cup ketchup and 1/2 cup water. Continue baking for another 30 minutes.

title: orange fluff
directions: Dissolve orange Jell-O in boiling water.
Stir in orange juice.
Add undrained pineapple.
Mix well.
Chill until partially set.
Stir in Mandarin oranges.
Pour into serving bowl.
Chill until set.
Combine pudding mix and milk in bowl; beat well.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spread over top of congealed Jell-O mixture. Chill until serving time.
Makes 12 servings.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Over medium heat, cook and stir butter, sugar, milk and salt until it is blended and melted.
Turn off heat.
Put 1/4 cup of very hot water in a small bowl and add the yeast.
Cover and set aside for 15 minutes.

title: angela's apple dumplings
directions: Roll out biscuits and divide pie filling between the 10 biscuits.
Pinch the dough up over pie filling and place in baking dish.
Melt margarine; add sugar and water.
Pour over biscuits. Bake about 30 minutes at 350° or until brown.
Spoon liquid over dumplings before serving.
You may also use cherry, peach or blueberry pie filling.

title: old-fashioned carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a spring-form Bundt pan.
With shredding disc of food processor or by hand, grate enough carrots to yield 3 cups.
Using steel blade of the processor, chop enough nuts to yield 1/2 cup.
Set carrots and nuts aside.
With electric mixer or by hand, mix together sugar, oil and eggs.

title: all-purpose cake(for dessert or coffee cake)
directions: Mix together cake mix, oil, eggs, vanilla and sour cream; blend well.
Pour 3/4 of batter in bottom (of oblong pan); mix together nuts, sugar, cinnamon and enough butter or margarine to make crumbs.
Sprinkle this
over the butter; add remaining batter.
Cut through batter to marble.
Bake at 350° approximately 1 hour.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and Crisco.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix flour, baking powder and soda; add to batter.
Add buttermilk as you add flour.
Beat well.
Add sour cream and flavor.
Grease and flour a tube pan.
Add batter.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: one dish spaghetti
directions: Mix ground beef, onion, salt and pepper in a large baking dish.
Microwave until meat loses its red color, stirring about every 4 minutes.
Layer spaghetti, one layer one way, the next layer crosswise to prevent spaghetti from sticking together as it cooks.
Pour on tomato sauce and water.
Cover and microwave 15 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes.
This may be made on top of stove in a large saucepan using the same directions.

title: cheese cake
directions: Allow cream cheese, eggs and sour cream to sit at room temperature before mixing.
In large bowl at medium speed, blend cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually add sugar with mixer on low speed.
Add other ingredients and continue to beat for 3 minutes. Pour mixture into sprayed (Pam) 10-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour or until lightly brown.
Turn off oven and leave cheesecake in oven for 30 minutes, cooling in pan on oven rack.

title: savory chicken bites
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients, mixing until well blended. Stir in chicken, celery and pimiento and set aside. Separate crescent dough into 8 rectangles. Press perforations to seal. Spread about 1/4 cup cream cheese over each dough rectangle, leaving 1/2-inch margin on one long side and no margin on the other sides. Roll dough, jellyroll fashion, starting at long side with filling spread to edge. Pinch seams to seal. Brush with egg and sprinkle with sesame seeds. Cut each roll into 5 pieces. Place seam side down onto lightly greased baking sheets. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown. Yield: 40 appetizers.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Beat eggs slightly.
Beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Bake about 45 minutes.

title: spinach lasagne
directions: Combine cottage cheese, 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, egg, spinach, salt, pepper and oregano.
Mix well.
Spread 1/2 cup sauce in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch Pyrex dish.
Place 1/3 uncooked noodles over sauce. Spread with 1/2 cheese mixture. Repeat layers. Top with remaining noodles, sauce and 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Pour water around edges.
Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients and let set. Mix the jello in the hot water and let cool. Mix with fruit and chill until set.

title: garbage casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a medium skillet, brown ground beef, onion, bell pepper and garlic.
Drain.
Add tomato sauce.
Cover; simmer for 10 minutes on low heat.
In a small bowl, combine cream cheese and sour cream.
In an 8-inch (2-quart) casserole, alternately layer the meat mixture, sour cream and cream cheese mixture, macaroni and Cheddar cheese until used up.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes, or until casserole is hot and bubbly.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Blend together flour, margarine and coconut.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: summer tomato salad
directions: Toss all ingredients in bowl.
Cover and refrigerate at least 30 minutes.
With slotted spoon dish into lettuce cups.
Serves 6.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Spray pan with Pam, then spread biscuits out, but not flat. Spread Ragu over to your taste and sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese.
If using Parmesan, sprinkle over the Cheddar.
You can always add other things, like pepperoni, onion and pepper.

title: cream of mushroom soup(zupa grzybowa)
directions: Saute onions and mushrooms together in butter until soft, but do not brown.
Add flour and stir until smooth.
Cook about 5 minutes.
Add chicken stock gradually, stirring until smooth. Simmer 7 to 8 minutes until thickened and smooth.
Whip as necessary.
Add hot milk and cream and season to taste.
Serve with garnish of chopped parsley.
Makes 3 gallons.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream together oil, sugar and flour. Stir together flour, salt, baking powder, soda and cinnamon.
Mix flour mixture with creamed mixture.
Add 1 1/2 cups chopped pecans. Peel and slice apples very thinly and add to mixture.
Pour mixture into greased and floured Bundt cake pan and bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until done.
Let set for 1 hour and gently remove from pan.

title: glazed turkey kabobs
directions: Preheat broiler.
Add water to pineapple juice to make one cup.
Combine juice, brown sugar and soy sauce in small saucepan. Boil over high heat.
Reduce heat to low.
Simmer 2-3 minutes. Set glaze aside.

title: dutch oven strawberry dumplings
directions: In
a
12-inch	Dutch
oven,
combine 2/3 cup sugar and water; bring
to a boil.	Reduce heat; lightly simmer, uncovered,
for 5
minutes.
Stir
in
vanilla.
Mix in a bowl the flour,
6 tablespoons
sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in margarine until mixture is crumbly.
Add milk; stir until well combined. Place
strawberries
in
hot
syrup.
Drop dumpling dough over strawberries.
Sprinkle dumplings with sugar.
Bake in a very hot oven at 450° for 25 to 30 minutes, using 6 to 10 coals on bottom and 18 to 22 coals on top.

title: wild rice soup
directions: Cut sliced onion into quarters.
Cook onion and mushrooms in butter until onion is transparent.
Add flour and stir until blended.
Slowly add chicken broth and cook 10 minutes, stirring until smooth.
Add wild rice, cream and meat, stirring until heated thoroughly.
Can be frozen.

title: drunken mushrooms
directions: Mix all ingredients well in large jar.
Marinate several hours or days in fridge.
Can be drained and added to green salad or eaten alone.
Marinade can be used over and over.

title: amber's overnight cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until foamy and gradually add sugar and salt.
Beat until stiff.
Add nuts and chocolate chips.
Place aluminum foil on a cookie sheet and drop mixture by teaspoon on foil.
Place in preheated oven and turn off oven.
Leave in unopened oven overnight (8 hours) and next morning, remove from foil.
Makes 24 to 30 cookies.

title: candied peanuts
directions: Boil sugar and water until sugar melts.
Add peanuts and boil until water evaporates.
(Peanuts will be sticky.) Preheat oven to 300°. Spread peanuts on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes; stir and sprinkle with salt.
Bake 15 minutes longer.
Stir and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: square molasses cake
directions: Soak raisins in hot water.
Mix the sugar, oil, egg and molasses.
Add flour, salt, soda and raisins.
Spread into greased oblong pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: mrs. nixon's hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except almonds, cheese and potato chips.
Place in large rectangular baking dish.
Top with cheese, potato chips and almonds.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli in 1/2 cup boiling water; do not drain.
Set aside.
Melt butter in a saucepan over medium heat.
Stir in flour to make paste.
Cook 2 to 4 minutes, stirring constantly with a wire whisk.
Add water to flour mixture, stirring constantly. Reduce to low heat.
Add broccoli, cheese, half and half and seasonings.
Heat gently, but do not boil.
Serve warm.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Boil oil, vinegar and sugar; pour over vegetable mixture while hot.
Let stand 1 day.
Can add 1 cup green and red sweet pepper for color at Christmas time.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Work flour, sugar and Crisco together.
Let buttermilk set while mixing water with yeast.

title: baked chicken with sauce
directions: Mix all except chicken together.
Place chicken in Pyrex dish or pan and pour mixture over it.
Cover and bake 2 hours at 400°.

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Butter a 10-inch springform pan and dust with graham cracker crumbs.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, eggs, flour, salt, pumpkin and spice.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour 30 minutes.
Decorate top with whip cream and candied walnuts.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in large pan; cover, bring to a boil and simmer until potatoes are tender, about 20 minutes.
Mash potatoes slightly; add milk and butter and heat through.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Pour into pie crust.
Cut other crust into 1/2-inch strips to form lattice for top crust.
Cook at 400° until golden brown.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Grate cheese; add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Add Miracle Whip to taste.

title: five cup fruit salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: crown dog with corn stuffing
directions: Place green pepper, onion and 4 tablespoons butter in a 1 1/2-quart ovenware casserole dish with straight sides.
Cook 5 to 8 minutes.
Add corn, eggs, bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Mix lightly.
Cover.
Continue cooking for 15 minutes.
Combine remaining 2 tablespoons of butter with 1/2 cup dry bread crumbs. Cook 30 seconds; stir to blend.
Mound corn mixture in casserole. Stand hot dogs, cut side down, in a crown around outside edge of stuffing.
Sprinkle top with buttered bread crumbs.
Total cooking time is 27 minutes.
Recipe yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: broccoli-onion deluxe
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
In saucepan, melt half of the margarine.
Blend in flour, salt and a dash of pepper.
Add milk. Cook, stirring constantly, until thick.
Reduce heat; blend in cream cheese until smooth.
Place broccoli and onions in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour sauce mixture over and mix lightly. Top with cheese.
Melt remaining butter; toss with bread crumbs. Sprinkle atop casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fain ney's rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over shortening, sugar and salt; when cool, add beaten eggs.
Sprinkle the yeast into warm water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add to first mixture.
Add flour slowly; blend well. Cover and place in refrigerator for at least 4 hours.
(Can be made the night before.)
Roll into shape using extra flour.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Roll in small balls and press out on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
They freeze well.

title: vanilla wafer pound cake
directions: Combine together margarine, sugar, eggs, milk and crushed wafers.
Add to mixture.
Add coconut and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake in tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: lefse
directions: Heat water to boiling; remove from stove and immediately add shortening, milk and potato flakes. Mix well and place in refrigerator until cold. When ready to bake, add the salt, flour and sugar. Mix well. Roll thin and bake on hot lefse grill.

title: super meringue
directions: For each egg white use 1 heaping tablespoon of marshmallow cream.
Beat egg whites until almost stiff.
Add marshmallow and beat until mixture stands in peaks.
Pile on pie or pudding.
This is superior meringue.
Will not weep or fall.

title: easy quiche
directions: Fit pastry into a 9-inch pie pan, fluting rim.
Cook bacon until crisp; drain thoroughly, then crumble.
Sprinkle bacon and cheese into prepared pastry shell.
Beat eggs lightly, then blend in whipping cream, milk and seasonings.
Pour mixture over cheese and bacon in crust.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 45 minutes or until custard is firm and crust and custard are browned.

title: crab spread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake in a greased casserole.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: mom's best zucchini fritters
directions: Blend the Bisquick, cheese, salt and pepper.
Add the 2 eggs. Grate the zucchini and add to the mixture, making a batter.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter over medium heat and pour batter into pans. Griddle into pancakes.
Cook 3 minutes on each side.
Serve while warm.
They are a delicious new way of serving a vegetable.

title: oven-fried fish
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in 13 x 9-inch (3-quart) glass baking dish in oven.
In shallow pan, combine flour and onion salt.
In medium bowl, combine egg, water and lemon juice. Place corn flakes in another medium bowl.
Coat fish fillets with flour mixture; dip in egg mixture.
Coat with corn flakes.
Place fish in baking dish; turn to coat with melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork.

title: honey or sorghum cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Stir in molasses or honey, beaten with eggs.
Resift flour with other dry ingredients.
Add other ingredients together, alternating with milk.
Beat batter after each addition until well blended.
Bake in a greased 9-inch tube pan in moderate oven for 22 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: hodgepodge soup
directions: Fry hamburger with onion and celery.
In large pan, combine stewed tomatoes, tomato soup, water, pork and beans and mixed vegetables; cook 7 minutes.
Mix together with hamburger, add chili powder and sugar to taste.

title: apricot glazed turkey breast slices
directions: With whisk or spoon, blend first six ingredients well, breaking up apricot pieces.
Place turkey in shallow baking dish. Pour sauce over turkey and marinate in refrigerator 2 hours to 24 hours.

title: garden toss taco
directions: Brown beef; drain fat.
Add seasoning mix, onions and water. Simmer 5 minutes.
Toss vegetables and beans with dressing.
Put on plate; top with meat and tortilla chips.
Sour cream is optional.
